INSERT INTO `tbl_additional` VALUES (1,34,'Membership and service questions','How much is MedicAlert Membership?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>MedicAlert membership is just ==membership_fee== for one year which gives you real peace of mind knowing you can be protected in a medical emergency.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>The overall cost to join MedicAlert is affected by the medical ID you choose plus postage:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Membership - ==membership_fee==</p>\r\n<p>Medical ID with free engraving &ndash; products starting from <strong>==medical_id_price==</strong></p>\r\n<p>Postage &ndash; starting from ==postage==</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>TOTAL: ==mintotal_membership_cost==*</p>\r\n<h5><em>*Minimum cost to join, including product and postage. This cost is based on our cheapest medical ID &ndash; the </em><a href=&quot;/wristband-tag-&quot;>Wristband Tag</a><em>. Cost is affected by the </em><a href=&quot;/products&quot;>product</a><em> you choose.</em></h5>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/cost&quot;>Learn more about MedicAlert fees and benefits></a></p>',0,1,'2016-08-23 16:06:47','2016-10-25 01:29:55',NULL),(2,34,'Membership and service questions','Why should I join MedicAlert Foundation?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>If you have any medical condition that may put you at risk in an emergency, then you need a MedicAlert medical ID. The MedicAlert medical ID ensures that emergency service &amp; healthcare personnel can immediately access the right information to assist in providing prompt, precise diagnosis and medical treatment.</p>',0,2,'2016-08-23 16:08:23','2016-10-10 03:32:14','2016-10-10 13:56:32'),(3,34,'Product questions','Other than the website, can I view the jewellery at a location?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>You may view the jewellery range at our National Office located in Adelaide, South Australia:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>National Office</p>\r\n<p>Level 1, 210 Greenhill Road<br /> Eastwood SA 5063</p>\r\n<p>Monday - Friday, 8:30am &ndash; 5:30pm CST</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>For all other states, please <a href=&quot;/products&quot;>click here</a> to view the full range.</p>',0,1,'2016-08-23 16:09:14','2016-10-24 00:48:17',NULL),(4,34,'Product questions','How much information can be engraved on the back of the medical ID?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Your unique identification number along with your most critical conditions or specials needs and our 24/7 emergency hotline will be engraved on the back of your medical ID. The amount of space for this will be determined by the size of the medical ID you select.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Bracelet: small = 3 lines; standard = 4 lines, large = 5 lines</p>\r\n<p>Necklace: small = 5 lines; large= 7 lines</p>\r\n<p>Dogtag = 5 lines</p>\r\n<p>Wristband Tag: small = 3 lines; large = 6 lines</p>\r\n<p>Rectangle = 4 lines</p>\r\n<p>Large Square = 5 lines</p>\r\n<p><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/emblem-size.png&quot; alt=&quot;emblem-size.png (83 KB)&quot; width=&quot;279&quot; height=&quot;592&quot; /></p>\r\n<p>Any additional information will be included on your wallet card and in your secure electronic health record.</p>',0,2,'2016-08-23 16:10:57','2016-10-10 05:55:17',NULL),(5,25,NULL,'Medical conditions',NULL,'/uploads/why-medical.png','Including diabetes, asthma, heart disease, epilepsy, special needs','<p>Alzheimer&#039;s, dementia, anaphylaxis, asthma (cold, allergy, exercise induced), attention deficit hyperactivity disorder, pervasive developmental disorder, autism, asperger syndrome, cancer, diabetes, deep vein thrombosis, epilepsy, seizure disorders, haemophilia, heart disease, hypothyroidism, language impaired (second language, stutter), malignant hyperthermia, no speech, renal failure, steroid therapy, streptokinase, tourette syndrome or transient ischaemic attack</p>',0,1,'2016-08-24 11:39:45','2016-10-13 07:11:12',NULL),(6,25,NULL,'Allergies',NULL,'/uploads/why-allergies.png','Including an allergy to nuts, latex, bees or penicillin','<p>Chemicals: Latex, Perfumes<br /> Drugs: Penicillin, Morphine, Ceclor, Sulpha Antiobiotics <br /> Food/Drink: Nuts, Eggs, Gluten, Fish, Milk/dairy, Peanuts <br /> Insects/Animals: Bees/wasps, Dogs/cats <br /> Environment: Dust, Grasses, Mould, Pollen</p>',0,2,'2016-08-24 11:41:11','2016-08-24 03:12:13',NULL),(7,25,NULL,'Implants or devices',NULL,'/uploads/why-implants.png','pacemaker, cochlear implant, stents','<p>Artificial knees or hips, artificial heart valve, cochlear implant, contact lenses, coronary stents, hearing aids, lens implants, insulin pump, pacemaker, stents, shunts, catheters, metal pins, plates or clips</p>',0,3,'2016-08-24 11:42:16','2016-10-13 07:10:13',NULL),(8,25,NULL,'Medical requirements',NULL,'/uploads/why-req.png','anticoagulants, insulin, steroid therapy','<p>Anticoagulants, beta blockers, chemotherapy, epinephrine auto injector, immunosuppressants, insulin, monoamine oxidase inhibitor (MAOI), steroid therapy or streptokinase</p>',0,4,'2016-08-24 11:42:41','2016-10-13 07:11:12',NULL),(9,25,NULL,'Identification needs',NULL,'/uploads/why-ID.png','dementia, autism, organ donor','<p>Children, elderly or travellers</p>',0,5,'2016-08-24 11:43:00','2016-10-13 07:10:58',NULL),(10,25,NULL,'An Advance Care Directive or management plans',NULL,'/uploads/why-advance.png',NULL,'<p>MedicAlert Members can store their Advanced Health Care Directive or other health and well-being documents with the Foundation as part of their health profile. Please contact our Membership Services Team on free call <a href=&quot;1800 88 22 22&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a> (8.30am - 5.30pm CST, Monday to Friday) or email us at <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a>.</p>',0,6,'2016-08-24 11:43:15','2016-10-13 07:10:13',NULL),(11,25,NULL,'Other',NULL,'/uploads/why-other.png',NULL,'<ul>\r\n<li>Blood group</li>\r\n<li>No known medical conditions or allergies</li>\r\n<li>Organ Donor</li>\r\n<li>Scuba Diver</li>\r\n<li>Sole Carer</li>\r\n</ul>',0,7,'2016-08-24 11:43:24','2016-10-24 04:34:02',NULL),(12,39,NULL,'Bupa',NULL,'/uploads/partners/bupa.jpg','http://www.bupa.com.au/','<p>Bupa members can receive a 2 year MedicAlert&reg; membership plus a medical ID of your choice* for just $100. That&rsquo;s a saving of up to 20%!</p>\r\n<p>*Selected products only. Price includes standard postage and handling and a 12-month standard Australia MedicAlert Foundation product warranty..</p>',0,1,'2016-08-24 14:00:05','2016-10-19 02:08:31',NULL),(13,2,NULL,'Ms Margaret Gehrig',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director1.png','Appointed May 2013','<p>Chair</p>',0,1,'2016-08-24 14:43:13','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(14,2,NULL,'Mr John Bell AM',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director2.png','Appointed November 2000','<p>Director</p>',0,2,'2016-08-24 14:44:26','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(15,2,NULL,'Mr Des Collinson',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director3.png','Appointed March 2009','<p>Director</p>',0,3,'2016-08-25 06:25:41','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(16,2,NULL,'Prof. Gerard (Gerry) Fitzgerald',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director4.png','Appointed August 2012','<p>Director</p>',0,4,'2016-08-25 06:26:59','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(17,2,NULL,'Dr Elizabeth Lewis AM',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director5.png','Appointed May 2004','<p>Director</p>',0,5,'2016-08-25 06:27:42','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(18,2,NULL,'Mr Gerrard Malcom',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director6.png','Appointed February 2013','<p>Director</p>',0,6,'2016-08-25 06:28:22','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(19,2,NULL,'Dr Rod Pearce AM',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director7.png','Appointed June 2015','<p>Director</p>',0,7,'2016-08-25 06:29:01','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(20,2,NULL,'Mr Keith Driscoll',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director8.png','Appointed August 2015','<p>Director</p>',0,8,'2016-08-25 06:29:45','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(21,34,'Membership and service questions','How does MedicAlert membership work?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>MedicAlert members wear a medical ID around their neck or on the wrist that is custom-engraved with their key medical condition(s) or vital details, membership number as well as the 24/7 hotline telephone number for emergency services and healthcare professionals to call for more information if required.</p>\r\n<p>In an emergency, ambulance paramedics and healthcare professionals are trained to look for the MedicAlert emblem and the information it holds. If needed, they can call the 24/7 support hotline for further important medical and personal details held on our secure national database - from anywhere in the world.</p>',0,999,'2016-08-25 08:16:14','2016-10-10 03:32:14','2016-10-10 13:56:30'),(22,34,'Membership and service questions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Your MedicAlert membership is much more than a piece of jewellery. It is a comprehensive system of protection and support that is with you, always. We offer peace of mind in those critical first moments of a medical emergency when you may be unable to speak for yourself. Learn more ></p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert membership provides extra peace of mind and includes our internationally recognised emblem, a 24/7 hotline for emergency services to access related information stored on our confidential database, customised engraved medical information on the back of your emblem and an individual member number that is unique to you. Learn more ></p>',0,999,'2016-08-25 08:16:43','2016-10-10 03:32:14','2016-10-10 13:56:31'),(23,34,'Membership and service questions','What is my risk if I don&#039;t purchase a genuine MedicAlert medical ID?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>For over 40 years the MedicAlert emblem remains the most recognised medical identification across all states in Australia. The Foundation has an active brand awareness campaign and maintains contact with ambulance professionals to ensure personnel recognise the genuine emblem. Ambulance personnel are trained to look around the neck and on the wrist for medical ID&#039;s.</p>',0,999,'2016-08-25 08:17:05','2016-10-10 03:32:14','2016-10-10 13:56:28'),(24,34,'Medical questions','How much information should I provide?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Consider the critical health information you need to let people know about in an emergency or if you can&#039;t speak for yourself.</p>\r\n<p>This includes your medical conditions, medications and any allergies you may have.</p>\r\n<p>You can also let us know about any specific wishes you have such as an advance care directive, if you&#039;re an organ donor or any next of kin details. We can also scan documents such as health management plans and advance care directives to hold safely on your electronic health record.</p>\r\n<p>We can ensure the vital details are engraved on your medical ID that meet MedicAlert standards and guidelines and that your full medical information is accessible and stored on our confidential electronic health record should it be required in an emergency.</p>\r\n<p> </p>',0,1,'2016-08-25 08:17:40','2016-10-10 04:58:55',NULL),(25,34,'Medical questions','How do I update my medical record if my medical information changes?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>You can change your medical record information via one of the following options:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Log in to the <a href=&quot;/update-my-profile&quot;>My MedicAlert Dashboard</a> to update your profile</li>\r\n<li>Call our Membership Services Team <a href=&quot;tel:1800 88 22 22&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a>. Monday - Friday, 8:30am &ndash; 5:30pm CST</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>If we have your email address on file:</p>\r\n<p>Go to the <a href=&quot;/login&quot;>My MedicAlert</a> title on our website and log in to the dashboard with your membership number and password. If you have forgotten your password or never been given one, enter your membership number and then click on &lsquo;Forgotten your password or never had a password?&rsquo; link. An email will be sent to your registered email address with a temporary password to sign in. Once you have signed in we recommend you change your password. Click on &lsquo;Update my Profile&rsquo; which gives you access to your membership profile to verify and/or update the information held on file for you. Once you have checked every tab of information, click on Save and Submit. Once our Membership Services team has reviewed and processed your changes a confirmation email will be sent to you confirming the changes have been completed.</p>\r\n<p>If we do not have your email address on file:</p>\r\n<p>Call Membership Services on <a href=&quot;tel:1800 88 22 22&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a> (Mon-Fri, 8:30am-5:30pm CST) to register your email address. We will then send you an email with a temporary password to sign in. Once you have signed in we recommend you change your password. We will only register your email address via telephone so we can verify your identity and ensure the security of your information.</p>\r\n<p>If your information changes significantly, we may recommend you re-order a new medical ID.</p>',0,2,'2016-08-25 08:18:54','2016-10-24 00:52:33',NULL),(26,34,'Other questions','I&rsquo;m a healthcare professional, can I get order an education pack?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Yes, we encourage the healthcare industry to continue to support the nationally recognised MedicAlert service and can provide a free education pack including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A supply of <a href=&quot;/uploads/Pages/pdf/2016-membership-catalogue.pdf&quot;>Membership catalogues (DL)</a></li>\r\n<li>A3 Poster</li>\r\n<li><a href=&quot;/uploads/resources/membershipcardimage2.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Sample membership card</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you would like to arrange sample medical ID&rsquo;s and membership catalogues, please contact Kara Reek on <a href=&quot;mailto:kreek@medicalert.org.au&quot;>kreek@medicalert.org.au</a> or by calling <a href=&quot;tel:1800 88 22 22&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a> (Mon-Fri, 8.30am-5.30pm CST).</p>',0,1,'2016-08-25 08:20:25','2016-10-24 00:52:33',NULL),(27,39,NULL,'Thomas Farms',NULL,'/uploads/partners/footer-logo.png','http://www.thomasfarms.com.au/',NULL,0,2,'2016-09-13 11:11:36','2016-09-30 03:41:08','2016-09-30 13:10:59'),(28,39,NULL,'Tunstall',NULL,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/tunstall-logo-1.jpg','http://www.tunstallhealthcare.com.au/','<p>Discounted Alarm Rental &amp; Monitoring.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert members have access to discounted alarm rental and monitoring, starting at $35.30 per month (usually $43.50 per month). A saving of 19%! <a href=&quot;/personal-alarms-and-monitoring&quot;>Read more ></a></p>',0,999,'2016-10-04 10:35:52','2016-10-24 00:54:56',NULL),(29,39,NULL,'Healthcare rebates',NULL,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo-members.jpg',NULL,'<p><span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;>Some health funds provide rebates for full or part of the MedicAlert membership fee and/or medical ID. To see what you&rsquo;re covered for, please contact your health fund provider.</span></p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/cost&quot;>Healthcare rebates ></a></p>',0,999,'2016-10-04 10:36:36','2016-10-24 00:54:46',NULL),(30,39,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,999,'2016-10-04 10:37:35','2016-10-04 00:09:19','2016-10-04 10:38:53'),(31,34,'Membership and service questions','How do I become a Member?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>You can join as a member by any of the following ways:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Online &ndash; Use our online signup process to join today by purchasing a <a href=&quot;/products&quot;>medical ID</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Phone &ndash; Call us on 1800 88 22 22 (Monday-Friday, 8:30am-5:30pm CST)</li>\r\n<li>Return completed form &ndash; <a href=&quot;/uploads/documents/maf_membership_form.pdf&quot;>download</a> application form now.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Post - MedicAlert Foundation, GPO Box 9963, ADELAIDE SA 5001</li>\r\n<li>Free Fax - 1800 64 32 59</li>\r\n<li>Email - <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>A membership pack (including your individually engraved medical ID) will be posted to you. Please allow approximately 20 working days for delivery.</p>',0,2,'2016-10-10 14:02:55','2016-10-24 00:48:17',NULL),(32,34,'Membership and service questions','Can I purchase jewellery without the full MedicAlert Membership?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Your MedicAlert membership is much more than a piece of jewellery. It is a comprehensive system of protection that is with you, always. As space is limited on your medical ID your full medical information is stored on your electronic health record and can be accessed via our 24/7 emergency hotline when required by healthcare professionals. Should healthcare professionals need to access your electronic health record they will be able to gain information such as emergency contact/s, doctor, medications, allergies, Advance Care Directive, Action Plans and full health/medical records. This is your peace of mind in those critical first moments of a medical or other emergency when seconds count and you may be unable to speak for yourself. Therefore, both your medical ID and the 24/7 emergency hotline provides you with comprehensive protection.</p>\r\n<p><a title=&quot;membership process&quot; href=&quot;/how-to-become-a-member&quot;><u>Learn more about the MedicAlert Membership process></u> </a></p>',0,3,'2016-10-10 14:10:36','2016-10-24 00:48:17',NULL),(33,34,'Membership and service questions','I may need help paying for MedicAlert Membership',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Please call our Membership Services Team to discuss membership options on <a href=&quot;tel:1800 88 22 22&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a>. Monday - Friday, 8:30am &ndash; 5:30pm CST.</p>\r\n<p>Did you know that some health funds provide rebates? You may receive the full or part cost of your membership and/or medical ID through extra&rsquo;s in your health cover which makes joining even more attractive. If you are a DVA Gold Card holder the Department of Veterans&#039; Affairs will pay your annual MedicAlert membership service fee as well as the full cost of a stainless steel medical ID.</p>\r\n<p><a title=&quot;membership cost&quot; href=&quot;/cost&quot;><u>Learn more about Membership Rebates></u> </a></p>',0,4,'2016-10-10 14:13:11','2016-10-24 00:52:33',NULL),(34,34,'Membership and service questions','Why should I join MedicAlert Foundation',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>MedicAlert membership is essential for anyone with a medical condition, allergy, identification needs or who takes regular medication that needs to be known in an emergency or you want your Advance Care Directive or treatment plans known in an emergency. The MedicAlert medical ID ensures that emergency service and healthcare personnel can immediately access the right information to assist in providing prompt, precise diagnosis and medical treatment.</p>',0,5,'2016-10-10 14:14:12','2016-10-10 03:44:30',NULL),(35,34,'Membership and service questions','Where can I find my Membership number?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>our membership number is located at the bottom on the back of your medical ID:</p>\r\n<p><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/benefits-frontback.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;benefits-frontback.jpg (43 KB)&quot; width=&quot;598&quot; height=&quot;274&quot; /></p>',0,6,'2016-10-10 14:14:34','2016-10-10 05:53:18',NULL),(36,34,'Membership and service questions','Will you let me know when it is time to renew my membership?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>You will receive a renewal notice approximately 4 weeks prior to your renewal date in the chosen method at the time of joining. If you selected email as your preference for contact, you will receive an email. If you selected mail, you will receive a notice in the mail.</p>\r\n<p>In addition to the above, when you log into to the website to purchase jewellery and have not yet renewed your annual membership, this will automatically be added to your shopping cart as a reminder.</p>\r\n<p>You will also notice on your MedicAlert membership dashboard area a new traffic light system that highlights when your annual fee is due by highlighting the days in the following system:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Green &ndash; Membership just paid up to 89 days remaining.</li>\r\n<li>Orange &ndash; 90 days remaining before your annual membership fee is due.</li>\r\n<li>Red &ndash; 10 days remaining before your annual membership fee is due and Membership is over due by &lsquo;X&rsquo; amount of days.</li>\r\n</ul>',0,7,'2016-10-10 14:16:20','2016-10-10 03:46:47',NULL),(37,34,'Membership and service questions','Why do I have to notify MedicAlert of changes to my health conditions and/or medications?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>It&rsquo;s important that you review your personal and medical information at least once a year to ensure your information on file is accurate in the event of an emergency.</p>',0,8,'2016-10-10 14:17:22','2016-10-10 03:47:35',NULL),(38,34,'Membership and service questions','How do I send you my Advance Care Directive or Health Plan/Medical Summary?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Should you wish to add these types of documents to your My MedicAlert profile please send to our Membership Services Team with your name and membership number via email or post:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Email: <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a></p>\r\n<p>Post: MedicAlert Foundation</p>\r\n<p>National Office</p>\r\n<p>Level 1, 210 Greenhill Road<br /> Eastwood SA 5063</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>The documents will then be reviewed by our Membership Services Team and you will be notified once these have been confirmed. This is so our team can ensure your documents contain all the vital information necessary in an emergency.</p>',0,9,'2016-10-10 14:17:38','2016-10-10 05:53:18',NULL),(39,34,'Product questions','How much is postage and handling?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>We use Australia Post to send your MedicAlert jewellery and medical ID to you. Standard postage and handling is ==postage== throughout Australia.</p>\r\n<p>All items valued at $160 or more are sent via Australia Post&rsquo;s registered post service.</p>',0,3,'2016-10-10 14:25:47','2016-10-24 00:11:58',NULL),(40,34,'Product questions','How long does it take to receive my MedicAlert medical ID?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Please allow 20 working days to receive your order throughout Australia. This allows time for the customisation of your medical ID plus delivery via Australia Post.</p>',0,4,'2016-10-10 14:26:06','2016-10-10 03:56:20',NULL),(41,34,'Product questions','What happens if I lose my jewellery or medical ID?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>You are responsible for the safe keeping of your jewellery and medical ID and therefore need to cover the expense for any replacements. Lost medical ID&rsquo;s are sometimes returned to us. If we are contacted by someone who has found a medical ID, we will contact the member to arrange for it to be returned.</p>',0,5,'2016-10-10 14:26:25','2016-10-10 03:56:37',NULL),(42,34,'Product questions','What if my jewellery is faulty or gets damaged?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>To maintain warranty, all repairs and alterations must be made by the MedicAlert Foundation. If your jewellery is faulty during your warranty period, firstly please send us a photo via <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a>. A Membership Services team member will advise if your jewellery or medical ID can be repaired. If a repair is not possible whilst under warranty, we can replace the jewellery. We may then ask you to send us your medical ID at the below address for repair.</p>\r\n<p>Return address:</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation</p>\r\n<p>GPO Box 9963</p>\r\n<p>ADELAIDE SA 5001</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>If your jewellery or medical ID is damaged outside of the warranty period, we can repair or replace your jewellery at your cost.</p>\r\n<p><a title=&quot;terms and conditions&quot; href=&quot;/terms-and-conditions&quot;><u>Learn more about product warranty in our Terms and Conditions></u> </a></p>',0,6,'2016-10-10 14:26:43','2016-10-24 00:48:17',NULL),(43,34,'Product questions','Can I change the details engraved on my medical ID?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Solid gold and sterling silver medical ID&rsquo;s can be buffed and re-engraved for a small fee (or at no charge for DVA Gold Card members). Please note there may be some limitations to the engraving requests.</p>\r\n<p>Stainless steel medical ID&rsquo;s and gold-filled medical ID&rsquo;s cannot be re-engraved but there may be space to add additional details if required.</p>\r\n<p>Any engraving changes or additions to your medical ID must be completed by MedicAlert Foundation to ensure the accuracy of information held on your electronic health record as well as on your medical ID.</p>',0,7,'2016-10-10 14:27:35','2016-10-10 03:57:53',NULL),(44,34,'Product questions','Can I change the length of my jewellery once I receive it?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>If your jewellery does not fit you upon receiving it, please contact our membership services team to discuss whether your jewellery can be altered on <a href=&quot;tel:1800 88 22 22&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a>. Monday - Friday, 8:30am &ndash; 5:30pm CST.</p>',0,8,'2016-10-10 14:27:58','2016-10-24 00:52:33',NULL),(45,34,'Product questions','What medical ID do you recommend for babies and toddlers?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Necklaces are not recommended for children aged 12 years and under. We recommend the stainless steel curb chain bracelet for use by babies and toddlers. It is lightweight, low maintenance and difficult for children to remove. It can also be customised to fit a small wrist. As the child grows, you can either purchase a new chain or transfer the engraved MedicAlert medical ID to a sports band.</p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/products/kids&quot;>View the children&rsquo;s product range></a></p>',0,9,'2016-10-10 14:28:24','2016-10-24 00:48:17',NULL),(46,34,'Product questions','What guarantees do you offer on your products?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Extensive research ensures that our products are high quality, stylish and durable. The material and workmanship of our products are guaranteed for 12 months, except the coloured enamel medical IDs, neoprene necklet, gemstone bracelet, Swarovski elements, sports band, pearl, beaded leather and braided bracelet which have a 6 month warranty. If you notice damage to a Product at the time of delivery you should notify the Foundation within 14 days of delivery and return that product to the Foundation. There are no refunds on our products due to the customised engraving of the medical ID.</p>\r\n<p>Warranty does not cover the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Damage resulting from normal wear and tear accidental damage or breakage misuse or alteration.</li>\r\n<li>Tarnishing or scratching of the medical ID, chain and attachment.</li>\r\n<li>Loss of any kind.</li>\r\n<li>Normal wear and tear with leather products.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/terms-and-conditions&quot;>View our Product Warranty Statement for more information></a></p>',0,10,'2016-10-10 14:29:03','2016-10-24 00:48:17',NULL),(47,34,'Product questions','What happens if I can&rsquo;t read the engraving on my medical ID?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>If your medical ID engraving is difficult to read it is time to purchase a one. You can do so via the MedicAlert website www.medicalert.org.au/products or by calling Membership Services on <a href=&quot;tel:1800 88 22 22&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a>. Remember, if you can&rsquo;t read your medical ID, it&rsquo;s unlikely that emergency services can either. Stay protected and ensure you update your medical ID if it&rsquo;s difficult to read.</p>',0,11,'2016-10-10 14:29:49','2016-10-24 00:50:05',NULL),(48,34,'Product questions','Why does MedicAlert have engraving standards and guidelines?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>To ensure that engraving is easy to read and the terminology of the medical condition, medications or allergy is easily read and understood in an emergency. This is what makes us different to our competitors as we ensure that the information you provide us is recognised in emergency situations.</p>',0,12,'2016-10-10 14:32:18','2016-10-10 04:04:58',NULL),(49,34,'Medical questions','What happens if I don&rsquo;t renew my membership but still wear my medical ID?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>In accordance with our Terms and Conditions, you are required to pay all fees due to the Foundation. If you do not pay your annual service fee, your membership will cease and we will remove and deactivate your personal electronic health record. This means Emergency Services will not have access to this information from our 24/7 emergency hotline.</p>\r\n<p>Your valued membership helps us to maintain the 24/7 emergency hotline (connected to a electronic health record) for emergency services personnel to access in an emergency and also assists us to continue to ensure the MedicAlert brand remain well recognised around Australia.</p>',0,3,'2016-10-10 14:39:34','2016-10-10 04:59:04',NULL),(50,34,'Other questions','How do donations help MedicAlert?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>Australia Medic Alert Foundation is a non-profit, member-based organisation that receives no government funding.</p>\r\n<p>You can help us to continue to help those in need of our vital services. Donations also allow us to keep the cost of our service to a minimum for all members and maintain our awareness programs for emergency professionals and the healthcare community. All donations $2.00 and over are tax deductible.</p>',0,2,'2016-10-10 14:41:50','2016-10-10 05:00:14',NULL),(51,34,'Other questions','How can I make a donation?',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<p>No matter how big or small, your donations will help us continue our mission to provide all Australians with essential medical protection when seconds count.</p>\r\n<p>All donations $2.00 and over are tax deductible.</p>\r\n<h3>Make a donation</h3>\r\n<p>If you&#039;d like to make a donation, simply click on the link below to head to our website to make an online donation.</p>\r\n<p>You can also donate by mailing a cheque or money order payable to:<br /> Australia Medic Alert Foundation<br /> Level 1, 210 Greenhill Road<br /> Eastwood SA 5063.</p>\r\n<p>Or by calling us <a href=&quot;tel:1800%2088%2022%2022&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a> (Monday-Friday, 8:30am-5:30pm CST).</p>\r\n<p><a title=&quot;donate&quot; href=&quot;/donate&quot;>Donate Now> </a></p>',0,3,'2016-10-10 14:42:11','2016-10-24 00:54:33',NULL),(52,2,NULL,'Ms Nell Anderson',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director-nell.jpg','Appointed May 2016','<p>Director</p>',0,9,'2016-10-11 11:54:07','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(53,2,NULL,'Mr Raj Khatri',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director-raj.jpg','Appointed May 2016','<p>Director</p>',0,10,'2016-10-11 12:01:38','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(54,2,NULL,'Mr Wayne Harvey',NULL,'/uploads/directors-chair/about-director-wayne.jpg','Appointed May 2016','<p>Director</p>',0,11,'2016-10-11 12:02:36','2016-10-19 04:43:09',NULL),(55,265,NULL,'Bupa',NULL,'/uploads/partners/bupa.jpg','http://www.bupa.com.au/','<p>Bupa members can receive a 2 year MedicAlert&reg; membership plus a medical ID of your choice* for just $100. That&rsquo;s a saving of up to 20%!</p>\r\n<p>*Selected products only. Price includes standard postage and handling and a 12-month standard Australia MedicAlert Foundation product warranty..</p>',0,1,'2016-08-24 14:00:05','2016-10-24 02:14:08',NULL),(56,265,NULL,'Healthcare rebates',NULL,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo-members.jpg',NULL,'<p><span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;>Some health funds provide rebates for full or part of the MedicAlert membership fee and/or medical ID. To see what you&rsquo;re covered for, please contact your health fund provider.</span></p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/cost&quot;>Healthcare rebates ></a></p>',0,999,'2016-10-04 10:36:36','2016-10-24 02:14:08',NULL),(57,265,NULL,'Tunstall',NULL,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/tunstall-logo-1.jpg','http://www.tunstallhealthcare.com.au/','<p>Discounted Alarm Rental &amp; Monitoring.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert 