connection with these Terms and Conditions even if the Foundation knew they were possible, or they were otherwise reasonably foreseeable; and</p>\r\n<p>c) all liability to you in negligence for acts or omissions of the Foundation, its employees, agents and contractors arising out of or in connection with these Terms and Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>23.3 To the extent permitted by law, the Foundation will not be liable or otherwise responsible for any loss, accident, damage or injury arising in connection with the Products, or any discrepancies in the Member Information, whether or not caused by a defect or fault in the Products or due to the Foundation&#039;s negligence. You unconditionally free, release and discharge the Foundation and its officers, agents, contractors and employees from any claim or cause of action arising in connection with the use of the Products, the Member Information or the Site by You, to the fullest extent permitted by applicable law.</p>\r\n<p>23.4 To the extent permitted by law, the Foundation&rsquo;s liability to You for breach of any Non-excludable Condition which is applicable is limited to any one of, at the Foundation&rsquo;s option:</p>\r\n<p>a) in the case of goods, including Products - repairing or replacing the goods in respect of which the breach occurred, supplying equivalent goods, payment of the cost of replacing the goods or acquiring equivalent products, or payment of the cost of having the goods repaired; and</p>\r\n<p>b) in the case of services - the supply of the services again, or payment of the cost of having the services supplied again.</p>\r\n<p>23.5 Use of this Site is at your own risk. The Foundation does not accept responsibility for any loss or damage howsoever caused, whether through negligence or otherwise which you may directly or indirectly suffer in connection with the use of this Site, or the Products or the Member Information, nor does the Foundation accept any responsibility for any such loss arising out of your use of or reliance on information contained on or accessed through this Site.</p>\r\n<p>23.6 Given the nature of the internet, the Foundation cannot guarantee that the Site is free from viruses or other conditions which could damage or interfere with your computer systems and the Foundation does not warrant that your access to the Site will be uninterrupted, error free or that any defects will be corrected. You access the Site at your own risk and must ensure that you have in place your own precautions so that the accessing of this Site does not expose you to the risk of viruses or other forms of interference which may damage your own computer system.</p>\r\n<p><em>24. Other Businesses</em></p>\r\n<p>There are links on the Site which direct you to a third party website owned and operated by another organisation other than the Foundation. The terms and conditions of those sites are separate to these Terms and Conditions, and individual to the site that you are visiting and should be reviewed by you and agreed upon as required. We are not responsible for examining or evaluating, and we do not warrant the offerings of, any of these businesses or individuals or the content of their web sites even though there may be a link to the site on the Site. Any link does not constitute our endorsement or approval of the contents of those websites, and the Foundation does not assume any responsibility or liability for the actions, product, and content of such sites or their third party operators. We may enter into collaborative agreements with third parties to promote products or services and may receive a small commission. To see details of the parties from whom we presently receive a commission, please <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au/third_parties&quot;>click here</a>.</p>\r\n<p><em>25. Definitions</em></p>\r\n<p>Terms that are capitalised are specifically defined in these Terms and Conditions. In these Terms and Conditions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Annual Member</strong> means a member who joined the Foundation on or after 1 January 1998.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Account</strong> means your login access to the Members Area on the website.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Application</strong> means an application for Membership.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Business Hours</strong> means 9am to 5pm Monday to Friday (CST).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Delivery Address</strong> means the address specified by you during the customer registration process or listed in an Order for the delivery of products that we will supply to you under these Terms and Conditions.</li>\r\n<li><strong>GST</strong> has the meaning it has in the <em>A New Tax System (Goods and Services Tax) Act 1999</em> (Cth).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Life Member</strong> means a member who joined the Foundation before 1 January 1998.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Member Medical Information</strong> means all health information (as defined in the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em>(Cth)) held by the Foundation about you.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Member Personal Information</strong> means all personal information (as defined in the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth)) held by the Foundation about you.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Member </strong>means a person with Membership of the Foundation.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Membership </strong>means your membership of the Foundation, as either an Annual Member or Life Member.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Product</strong> means each good or service that is advertised as being available for supply by the Foundation from time to time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Version 5.3 | Date: 25 February 2016</p>\r\n</div>','<div id=&quot;service-communication&quot;>COMMUNICATION SERVICE GUARANTEE - ADD TITLE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>The Australia Medic Alert Foundation (AMAF) is committed to providing high quality services, and adopts the following service standards, guided by our core values of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Accountability</li>\r\n<li>Commitment</li>\r\n<li>Community</li>\r\n<li>Equity and Diversity</li>\r\n<li>Integrity</li>\r\n<li>WH&amp;S</li>\r\n<li>Innovation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>When you contact us</h1>\r\n<h2>Telephone enquiries</h2>\r\n<p>If you call us we will answer your calls promptly and courteously and aim to answer your queries on the spot.</p>\r\n<p>We recognise that you may have queries that are unique to your own specific</p>\r\n<p>circumstances or are complex. In these instances we may need to arrange a call back so that we can research the query sufficiently to ensure a specific and thorough response is given.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, if your query is not straight forward, please email us. We aim to provide you with a response within 3 business days for queries sent to <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a></p>\r\n<h2>Correspondence (letter or email)</h2>\r\n<p>We will acknowledge your correspondence within 24 hours of receipt (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply). We aim to give you a full response to general correspondence within 3 business days of receiving all of the required information. In some cases, we may request further information from you to ensure that we understand your reason for contact fully and to give you a full response.</p>\r\n<p>For more complex correspondence, the exact timing and content of our response will depend on each case and the request.</p>\r\n<h2>Social Media Channels</h2>\r\n<p>We will acknowledge your correspondence within 4 - 6 hours of receipt during</p>\r\n<p>business hours (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply). We aim to give you a full response to general correspondence within 3 business days of receiving all of the required information. In some cases, we may request further information from you to ensure that we understand your reason for contact fully and to give you a full response.</p>\r\n<p>For more complex correspondence, the exact timing and content of our response will depend on each case and the request.</p>\r\n<h2>AMAF membership application forms</h2>\r\n<p>When you lodge a form to become a member or update your details we aim to process the request within 3 business days of receipt of all of the required information.</p>\r\n<h1>When you provide us with feedback</h1>\r\n<h2>General</h2>\r\n<p>We take your feedback seriously. We will listen and work with you to reach a resolution where we can.</p>\r\n<p>If you provide feedback, we will act immediately where there is a serious risk to public trust and confidence and/or they relate to AMAF&rsquo;s compliance requirements.</p>\r\n<p>We aim to provide a substantive response to your feedback within 3 business days.</p>\r\n<h2>Product</h2>\r\n<p>All AMAF products offered to our members are supported by <u>Product Warranty Statement</u>.</p>\r\n<p>If you provide feedback about a product we will work with you to reach a resolution where we can within the warranty guidelines.</p>\r\n<p>We aim to address any product queries or concerns on the spot, but where the issue is unique or complex we may need to arrange a call back so that we can research the query sufficiently to ensure a specific and thorough response is given. In all cases, we aim to address the issue within 3 business days.</p>\r\n<h1>When you request information we hold  </h1>\r\n<h2>General information requests</h2>\r\n<p>We aim to acknowledge all requests for access to information within 24 hours receipt (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply).</p>\r\n<p>We aim to provide a response to requests not falling under the Freedom of Information Act and Privacy Act within 14 business days.</p>\r\n<h2>Freedom of Information Act requests</h2>\r\n<p>We aim to respond to requests for information falling under the Freedom of Information Act within 30 calendar days (plus statutory extensions). Where third party consultation is required; we aim to provide you with a full response within 60 calendar days.</p>\r\n<h2>Privacy Act requests</h2>\r\n<p>If you raise an issue with us that falls under the Privacy Act, we aim to provide a response within 30 calendar days.</p>\r\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Terms and Conditions',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-04 15:37:14','2016-10-24 02:07:51','2016-10-24 12:37:51'),(11,11,1,0,0,'Privacy policy',NULL,NULL,'privacy-policy',1,'<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p>Australian Medic Alert Foundation (&ldquo;<strong>MedicAlert Foundation</strong>&rdquo;) [ACN 050 542 455] is committed to protecting the privacy of our members. MedicAlert Foundation has adopted this Privacy Policy to ensure we handle personal information in accordance with the Australian Privacy Principles (&quot;<strong>APPs</strong>&quot;) set out in Schedule 1 of the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth) (&quot;<strong>the Act</strong>&quot;). The APPs are a common set of requirements that regulate the handling of personal information by both Australian government agencies and businesses.</p>\r\n<p>More specifically, the APPs set out the way organisations such as MedicAlert Foundation can collect, use, disclose and provide access to personal and sensitive information. Personal information is specifically defined in the Act, and refers to any information that identifies or could identify a person, whether it is true or not. It includes, for example, your name, age, gender and contact details. Personal information can also include sensitive information (another specifically defined term in the Act), which is information about your health and health services provided to you. We are also bound by the Australian Direct Marketing Association Privacy Code for direct mail activities.</p>\r\n<p>The privacy of our members&rsquo; personal information is important to us and we conduct our business with the highest standards of personal and corporate integrity. We aim to provide the best possible service, whilst ensuring you are aware of how your personal information is used within MedicAlert Foundation.</p>\r\n<p>This Privacy Policy applies to all employees, consultants, contractors and agents of MedicAlert Foundation, and covers all information collected on the MedicAlert Foundation website as well as information supplied to MedicAlert in person, by phone, in writing (including email) or in any other way.</p>\r\n<p><em>1. Collection of Personal Information</em></p>\r\n<p>We will always be open and honest in our dealings with you and will only collect information about you that we believe is necessary to undertake our legitimate business activities. We will always collect your personal information by fair and lawful means (for example when you complete an application form, in person, online or by telephone). Most often we will collect your personal information directly from you or your doctor (where we have obtained your consent to do so).</p>\r\n<p><strong>1.1 Type of Information<br /></strong>Member&rsquo;s personal information is collected through information provided by you (or your representative for purposes of joining the Foundation) and is stored on your current membership file. The information may include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>your name, date of birth and membership number;</li>\r\n<li>your mailing address, contact number(s), email address(es) and emergency contact details;</li>\r\n<li>information on any health conditions and personal needs you may have, together with details pertaining to your doctor&rsquo;s name, address and where your hospital records are kept;</li>\r\n<li>your credit card details (as required to execute the payment of membership fees and purchases);</li>\r\n<li>information on the products and services we have provided to you;</li>\r\n<li>a record of any queries you have made; and</li>\r\n<li>transactional history relating to your usage of our services.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We also collect sensitive information about you such as medical conditions, allergies, medications taken, blood group and other such relevant information (e.g. special needs and requests), and store this on your membership file.</p>\r\n<p>We will only collect any other personal information, including sensitive information, in accordance with the Act.</p>\r\n<p><strong>1.2 Cookies<br /></strong>The MedicAlert Foundation website and its pages use software known as &lsquo;cookies&rsquo; to record your visit to our website and collect some statistical information. We use this information to help administer and improve our websites. We do not use this information to personally identify you. Information we may collect includes:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>your server address;</li>\r\n<li>your domain name;</li>\r\n<li>the date and time of access to the website;</li>\r\n<li>pages accessed and documents downloaded;</li>\r\n<li>the items you have ordered in your online shopping cart;</li>\r\n<li>the previous site visited;</li>\r\n<li>if you have visited the website before; and</li>\r\n<li>the type of browser software in use.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You may set your web browser to disable cookies from when visiting our websites. However, some website functions may be unavailable if you choose to do so.</p>\r\n<p><em>2. Use and Disclosure</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>2.1 Collection and Use of Information<br /></strong>MedicAlert Foundation collects personal information directly from you wherever possible, however sometimes we may collect personal information about you from a third party, e.g. a friend who has provided your details to us so we can send you a membership form, or your doctor where you have consented to us communicating with him/her.</p>\r\n<p>Any personal information collected about you is used for the following purposes:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>to contact you directly about MedicAlert Foundation&#039;s activities, special offers and other promotions;</li>\r\n<li>to reward you for being a loyal member;</li>\r\n<li>to approve transactions you wish to make;</li>\r\n<li>to confirm your identity;</li>\r\n<li>to provide you with products and services you have requested;</li>\r\n<li>to follow up or pursue any queries you make;</li>\r\n<li>to conduct consumer research;</li>\r\n<li>to notify you of the outcome of specific promotions;</li>\r\n<li>to service and administer your membership entitlements; and,</li>\r\n<li>to ensure you are aware of various membership benefits and to offer specific products and services we consider may be of particular interest to you.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>2.2 Disclosure and Use of Information by Third Parties<br /></strong>Any information collected by MedicAlert Foundation is kept strictly confidential and is only accessed by authorised MedicAlert Foundation staff, agents, contractors or service providers with whom we have a contractual agreement, in the course of them undertaking their legitimate duties in providing a given product or service.</p>\r\n<p>If your membership of MedicAlert Foundation lapses or is cancelled by you voluntarily, we will not disclose your information except in the circumstances outlined below, and will take steps to delete your information from our system.</p>\r\n<p>Member or customer information will not be disclosed to any external third party organisation except as set out in this document, and will only be made available to an outside entity where:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>MedicAlert Foundation has contracted an external service provider (under strict privacy terms) to assist in the execution of MedicAlert Foundation&rsquo;s activities;</li>\r\n<li>MedicAlert Foundation is acting as an agent or representative of another entity;</li>\r\n<li>the purpose of disclosure to the third party is related (or, in the case of any sensitive information (as defined in the Act), directly related) to the primary purpose for which the information was collected;</li>\r\n<li>there exists a permitted general situation (as specifically defined in the Act) in relation to the collection, use or disclosure of personal information to the third party;</li>\r\n<li>a permitted health situation (as specifically defined by the Act) exists in relation to the collection, use or disclosure of health information;</li>\r\n<li>if disclosure is required by or authorised by law; or</li>\r\n<li>if you consent to the disclosure of specific information.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em>3. Anonymity</em></p>\r\n<p>It is your choice to provide information to us. Wherever it is lawful and practicable, you have the option not to identify yourself when interacting with us. You can remain anonymous when using some parts of the MedicAlert Foundation website and its pages.</p>\r\n<p>However, it may be necessary for us to collect your personal or sensitive information if you would like to access certain materials or services we offer. If you choose not give us the information we require, we may not be able to provide the services you have requested.</p>\r\n<p><em>4. Data Quality</em></p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation will take all reasonable steps to ensure that the personal information we collect, use and disclose is accurate, complete and up-to date. However the accuracy of that information depends to a large extent on the information you provide. That&rsquo;s why we recommend that you contact us and:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>let us know if there are any errors in your personal information; and</li>\r\n<li>keep us up to date with changes to personal information such as your name and address.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Each year you will receive a copy in the mail of your medical information (sent with your annual subscription fee, if you are required to pay this to maintain your membership) that you can use to check your details are accurate. If you do not pay your annual fee (if applicable) and confirm the accuracy of your information, or advise us of any changes, we will no longer consider you a member of MedicAlert Foundation, and will delete information we hold in respect of you. We will use all reasonable steps to notify you before we delete your information, to give you one final chance to recommence membership and provide us with current information.</p>\r\n<p><em>5. Data Security</em></p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation will take appropriate steps to protect your personal and sensitive information and keep this information secure. This includes physical security, computer and network security, communications security and personnel security.</p>\r\n<p>We will request sufficient identification to permit authorised access to the existence, use or disclosure of members&rsquo; personal information when required, as per our Operating Standards and Emergency Management Call Protocol. Any such identification information shall be used only for this purpose unless we have your consent to use or disclose it for other purposes.</p>\r\n<p>If we no longer require your personal information, including if your membership lapses (including as a result of you not contacting the Foundation annually to confirm the personal information we hold about you, or request that we update the personal information we hold about you), or, is cancelled by you voluntarily, we will take reasonable steps to either destroy the information we hold about you in a secure manner or remove identifying features from the information. We will however, retain basic details such as your name and date of birth to enable us to advise any future callers that we no longer provide services to you. This is also subject to any legal obligations we have to keep information for a certain period of time.</p>\r\n<p><strong>5.1 Order and Pay Online Securely<br /></strong>Our online payment systems use encryption technology to ensure your credit card and contact details are kept safe and secure when transmitted across the internet. This makes it very difficult for third parties to intercept and misuse your details but, as with all internet transmissions such as internet banking, there always remain some risks. We take all reasonable steps to minimise these risks and will notify you as soon as we reasonably can if and when we become aware of any unauthorised access of your personal or sensitive information via the internet.</p>\r\n<p><em>6. Marketing</em></p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation complies with permission based direct marketing requirements under the Act and the <em>Spam Act 2003</em> (Cth). When collecting your personal information, we will request your permission to use that information to send you information on products and promotions or other health-related materials and will give you the opportunity to &ldquo;opt out&rdquo; of receiving such marketing material. Where you indicate your consent, MedicAlert Foundation may enter your details into a database for the purpose of contacting you directly about our brands, special offers, consumer research and other promotions.</p>\r\n<p><em>7. Access and Correction of Personal Information</em></p>\r\n<p>We will take reasonable steps to ensure that all personal information that we collect, use or disclose is accurate, up-to-date, complete, relevant and not misleading. Please see Section 4 above, for the part you play in assisting us with ensuring this is the case.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation respects the rights of individual members and customers to access and correct their own personal information that is in our possession. Simple access requests can usually be actioned over the telephone by asking for the Privacy Officer on <span class=&quot;AVANSERnumber&quot;>1800 88 22 22</span> (Monday &ndash; Friday 9am &ndash; 5pm CST) as per our Operating Standards. However detailed requests may need to be submitted in writing addressed to the Privacy Officer at:</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation<br />GPO Box 9963<br />In Your Capital City</p>\r\n<p>or by email sent to: <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a></p>\r\n<p>We will respond to your request to access or correct your personal information, or to withdraw your consent, no later than thirty (30) days after receipt of such requests. If for any reason your request is refused, we will give you a written notice that sets out the reasons for refusal and how to dispute the decision.</p>\r\n<p><em>8. Transfer of Information Overseas</em></p>\r\n<p>By providing personal and/or sensitive information to us, you consent to the transfer of that information to any jurisdiction in which we conduct our business activities, for the purpose of enabling us to provide services to you. With effect from the date of this Policy, this includes transfer by us into the United States of America and disclosure to MedicAlert Foundation United States, Inc (MedicAlert US), for the purposes of including your information in MedicAlert US&#039;s database to enable worldwide provision of services to you outside of Australia as needed. You can at any time remove your consent to the disclosure of your information to MedicAlert US and inclusion in its database, by contacting our Privacy Officer using the contact details set out in Section 7 above.</p>\r\n<p>We will otherwise only transfer your personal or sensitive information overseas if the transfer is to you or to one of your authorised representatives (including your treating medical practitioner located overseas), with your express consent or otherwise in accordance with the Act. We will not send your information outside of Australia in any other circumstances.</p>\r\n<p><em>9. Complaints and enquiries</em></p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation is committed to the protection of your privacy. If you have any questions about how we handle personal information, would like to complain about how we have handled your information, or would like further information about our Privacy Policy, please submit a written query or complaint to our Privacy Officer, using the contact details set out in Section 7 above.</p>\r\n<p>Our Privacy Officer will assess any complaints and liaise with you to resolve any issues within a reasonable time (usually within 30 days). If you are unhappy with the outcome, you may lodge a complaint with the Australian Information Commissioner. See <a href=&quot;http://www.oaic.gov.au/privacy/making-a-privacy-complaint&quot;>http://www.oaic.gov.au/privacy/making-a-privacy-complaint</a> for further information.</p>\r\n<p><em>10. Additional Information</em></p>\r\n<p>Further information on privacy is available at the website of the Office of the Federal Privacy Commissioner: see <a href=&quot;http://www.oaic.gov.au/&quot;>http://www.oaic.gov.au/</a>.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation reserves the right to change this Privacy Policy at any time and to notify its customers by posting an updated version of the policy on our website: <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au/&quot;>www.medicalert.org.au</a>. Any revised version will be effective from the date of posting, or such future date as is specified in the document.</p>\r\n<p>This Privacy Policy replaces all previous MedicAlert Foundation privacy policies.</p>\r\n<p>Dated: 1 July 2015</p>\r\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Australian Medic Alert Foundation Privacy Policy | MedicAlert ','At MedicAlert Foundation we take privacy very seriously. Read our privacy policy to learn about how we collect, use and protect your personal information.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-04 15:40:14','2016-10-26 06:37:30',NULL),(12,12,1,0,0,'Shopping cart',NULL,NULL,'shopping-cart',0,'<p>All MedicAlert jewellery is backed by a vital MedicAlert membership. When you become a member, you&rsquo;re taking control of your health by ensuring you&rsquo;ll receive fast and effective treatment in an emergency. MedicAlert members also receive access to a range of exclusive <a href=&quot;/benefits-of-membership&quot;>member-only benefits</a>. Together, your MedicAlert membership and identification jewellery provides you with peace of mind knowing you&rsquo;re protected when seconds count.</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>To complete this purchase, you&rsquo;ll need your billing and shipping address, and a VISA or MasterCard for payment. All transactions made through the Australia Medic Alert Foundation checkout are secure and encrypted. When processing a purchase your credit card details won&rsquo;t be stored on our database, so your information is safe. View our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>privacy policy</a> to find out more.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Shopping cart | MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1,'2016-07-04 15:46:09','2018-07-06 01:19:14',NULL),(13,13,1,0,0,'Checkout',NULL,NULL,'checkout',0,'<p>Your membership fee of ==membership_fee== has been added to your cart. This fee gives you access to a range of exclusive <a href=&quot;/benefits-of-membership&quot;>member-only benefits</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Together, your MedicAlert membership and identification jewellery provides you with peace of mind knowing you&rsquo;re protected when seconds count.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Shopping Cart Checkout | MedicAlert','View your MedicAlert shopping cart here and checkout to purchase your new medical identification jewellery. ',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1,'2016-07-04 15:46:31','2016-10-26 06:39:14',NULL),(14,14,1,0,0,'Password recovery',NULL,NULL,'password-recovery',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Password recovery | MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1,'2016-07-04 15:48:41','2016-10-26 06:40:55',NULL),(15,15,1,0,0,'403 - Access Denied/Forbidden',NULL,NULL,'403-access-deniedforbidden',0,'<p>You are not authorised to view this resource.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'403 - Access Denied/Forbidden',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1,'2016-07-04 17:22:42','2016-09-16 06:11:36',NULL),(16,16,1,0,0,'Search',NULL,NULL,'search',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Search | MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-04 17:27:44','2016-10-26 06:42:20',NULL),(17,17,1,0,0,'News and resources',NULL,NULL,'news-and-resources',1,'<p>We&rsquo;re committed to providing MedicAlert members and friends with the latest news and information. Be sure to check back regularly for updates.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Latest News and Resources | MedicAlert','Stay up to date with the latest news from MedicAlert Foundation and view our other resources here including newsletters and videos. ',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/newsdet-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-05 11:55:09','2016-10-26 06:01:11',NULL),(18,18,2,0,17,'MedicAlert Foundation asks, &#039;what would you do if?&#039;',NULL,NULL,'medicalert-foundation-asks-what-would-you-do-if',0,'<p>You&rsquo;re enjoying after work drinks with work colleagues when suddenly the new team member you&rsquo;re speaking with &ldquo;zones out&rdquo;, turns pale, begins acting strangely, their limbs begin to twitch and </p>\r\n','<p>You&rsquo;re enjoying after work drinks with work colleagues when suddenly the new team member you&rsquo;re speaking with &ldquo;zones out&rdquo;, turns pale, begins acting strangely, their limbs begin to twitch and they fall to the floor.</p>\r\n<p>What would you do? Perhaps assume they&rsquo;ve had too much to drink or taken drugs? Wonder if they are mentally ill? Perhaps move away in embarrassment and decide it&rsquo;s time to leave?</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;These behaviours and physical symptoms are often the signs that someone is about to have or is having an epileptic seizure,&rsquo;&rsquo; MedicAlert Foundation Chief Executive Officer Heidi Jones said.</p>\r\n<p>At the start of national Epilepsy Awareness Month, and in support of its Go Purple awareness campaign, Ms Jones says there is low community awareness and understanding about epilepsy.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Research suggests that due to the social stigma and misconceptions associated with epilepsy, many people do not disclose their condition,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;This is of great concern to us as it may mean that people do not get fast and effective emergency treatment.&rsquo;&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>Melbourne resident, Emma Gaffy, 31, knows firsthand the misconceptions surrounding the condition and lack of knowledge about how to deal with an emergency situation.</p>\r\n<p>As a result and in preparation for overseas travel, Ms Gaffy recently obtained a MedicAlert medical identification bracelet.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve had some very difficult experiences over the years, including in 2006 I was on the Gold Coast shopping alone and had a seizure in a store,&rsquo;&rsquo; she said. &ldquo;I had no time to warn anyone and the store staff were completely unsure of what to do. Then in 2007 I was in Venice and collapsed and had a seizure. Even the hospital staff weren&rsquo;t sure what was going on during it, even though my sister tried to explain.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I feel a lot safer now with the MedicAlert medical ID and I know that if anything happens, it&rsquo;s there and it can speak for me, if I can&rsquo;t.&rsquo;&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>Ms Gaffy was diagnosed with tonic clonic epilepsy, as a result of a brain haemorrhage and stroke when she was only 19. Aside from a five minute warning just before the stroke &ndash; a tingling sensation down her right side &ndash; she had no warning signs.</p>\r\n<p>She spent six months in hospital following the stroke and needed 24/7 care to learn to walk, talk and function again. During this time, she had multiple seizures, but now with daily medication she has few seizures a year, but lives in constant fear of having a seizure and is unable to get her driver&rsquo;s licence.</p>\r\n<p>Ms Jones said a MedicAlert medical identification bracelet or necklace plays a critical role in informing first responders in an emergency that a person has a medical condition, particularly when someone is not able to communicate.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;A medical ID can save lives and in the case of children with epilepsy, they also give parents great peace of mind that if something happens when your child is not in your care, they have the protection of a medical ID.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Not only are paramedics and healthcare professionals trained to look for the MedicAlert emblem, they can also call the the 24/7 emergency hotline for further important medical and personal details, held on its secure national database.&rsquo;&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>Epilepsy facts from Epilepsy Action Australia:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>According to the World Health Organisation, epilepsy is the world&rsquo;s most common serious brain disorder. It is not a mental disorder;</li>\r\n<li>Approximately 25,000 people in Australia are diagnosed with epilepsy each year;</li>\r\n<li>An estimated 800,000 people in Australia will be diagnosed with epilepsy at some stage in life;</li>\r\n<li>An estimated 250,000 Australians are living with epilepsy and</li>\r\n<li>It is commonly thought that epilepsy always involves convulsions. There are infact around 40 different types of epilepsy and epilepsy syndromes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Epilepsy is a spectrum disorder ranging from severely challenging, frequent seizures that do not respond to medication, as mainly seen in children, to seizures that readily respond to treatment allowing the person to continue life seizure-free.</strong></p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert has been supporting Epilepsy Awareness Month for three years now. This year MedicAlert is offering a $5 discount and will make a $5 donation on all purple MedicAlert products sold during March 2016. To receive this discount and provide a donation to Epilepsy Australia, please quote the special promotional code EPILEPSY16.</p>\r\n<p>Anyone with a medical condition, allergy, implants, using medication and with complex treatment plans, advance health directive and palliative care requests or those with a medical condition planning to travel should have a MedicAlert medical ID.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation is Australia&rsquo;s only not-for-profit organisation providing 24/7 personal medical emergency information and identification service. Established in 1971, it has provided protection and peace of mind to 300,000 Australians.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'MedicAlert Foundation asks, &#039;what would you do if?&#039;',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-3.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2016-03-01','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-08 19:54:23','2016-10-03 00:11:15','2016-10-03 10:41:01'),(19,19,2,0,17,'Heidi Jones announced as new Chief Executive Officer',NULL,NULL,'heidi-jones-announced-as-new-chief-executive-officer',0,'Australia Medic Alert Foundation is pleased to announce the appointment of Ms Heidi Jones as Chief Executive Officer of the national not-for-profit organisation.','<p><strong>Australia Medic Alert Foundation is pleased to announce the appointment of Ms Heidi Jones as Chief Executive Officer of the national not-for-profit organisation.</strong></p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation Chair, Ms Margaret Gehrig, said Ms Jones&rsquo; extensive senior management, strategic planning, and business development experience made her a well-credentialed choice for this critical role.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Heidi comes to the MedicAlert Foundation after working for many years in a senior lead consultant role with Hender Consulting, where she provided HR and business support to clients nationally,&rdquo; Ms Gehrig said.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;She offers a strong understanding of the strategic challenges and opportunities facing our organisation and her successful track-record in business development will support MedicAlert on the next stage of its growth journey,&rdquo; she said.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I am confident that under Heidi&rsquo;s leadership our small but dedicated national team of highly-trained and passionate individuals will see our organisation go from strength to strength.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;MedicAlert Foundation has an enviable reputation as a market leader, and I want to develop and implement strategies that will achieve continued national growth and build on the services that are currently provided to our membership,&rdquo; Ms Jones said.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Strengthening working relationships with leading professional bodies and other not-for-profit agencies and organisations across Australia is a critical area of focus, because it will ultimately create a far more integrated service model for the people we support,&rdquo; she said.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;When you look at successful organisations, a common theme is a commitment to innovate, and it is important to identify new opportunities that will enhance our membership services and consider how emerging technologies could be used to assist with emergency identification.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Prior to her Hender role, Ms Jones spent four years as the Director of Corporate Services for South Australian disability service provider, scosa, where she managed an extensive corporate services team.</p>\r\n<p>She also spent more than four years in a General Manager role at the Adelaide Eye &amp; Laser Centre, where she led the change of business from an ophthalmic practice to a specialised, licensed day surgery facility. Her other responsibilities included marketing, HR, contract management and procurement, and finance.</p>\r\n<p>Ms Jones also spent several years as a non-medical executive at Adelaide North East Division of General Practice where she managed all aspects of the business, and was pivotal in implementing the start-up phase of Commonwealth-funded entity.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About Australia Medic Alert Foundation</strong></p>\r\n<p>For over 40 years, Australia Medic Alert Foundation has been the Nation&rsquo;s only not-for-profit organisation providing a 24/7 personal medical emergency information and identification service with close to 300,000 members joining since 1971.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert members wear a bracelet or necklace with a genuine MedicAlert emblem custom engraved with their vital medical information, membership number and hotline number.</p>\r\n<p>The 24/7 hotline allows emergency service personnel and healthcare professionals to access important additional medical and other details quickly and efficiently in a time of need.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Heidi Jones announced as new Chief Executive Officer',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2014-11-28','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-08 20:16:36','2016-10-03 00:31:20','2016-10-03 11:01:06'),(20,20,2,0,17,'Getting your kids to do important stuff, like wearing their medical ID',NULL,NULL,'getting-your-kids-to-do-important-stuff-like-wearing-their-medical-id',0,NULL,'<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; style=&quot;float: right;&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/news-and-resources/newsletter/kids2.154306.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;kids2.154306.jpg (42 KB)&quot; width=&quot;290&quot; height=&quot;182&quot; /></strong></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>You know it&rsquo;s important for your kids to wear their MedicAlert medical ID, and chances are they do too, but what&rsquo;s the best way to avoid excuses and ensure they actually do it?</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Doctors, psychologists and a whole list of experts will tell you that the best and most effective way to get a child or teenager to do anything is through routine. Of course there are other means you may need along the way, such as bribes, threats, moral persuasion, parental authority and anger, but when it comes to getting them to wear their medical ID, your first &lsquo;go to&rsquo; should be routine.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Mother of three Rebekah Smith said that for her two girls (aged 9 and 15) who wear a medical ID &ndash; the biggest problem is remembering to have them on when they go to school or their friend&rsquo;s places to play, because sometimes they take it off for sports practice or to wash.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;To combat this, at the breakfast table each morning we initially created a placemat for each child &ndash; the teenager didn&rsquo;t love it of course - with a list of the things that they need to do every morning, one of which is put their bracelet on,&rdquo; said Mrs Smith.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;They both know it&rsquo;s important, we&rsquo;ve educated them about what could happen if they were to suffer an allergic reaction and no one was around who knew about their condition; so it&rsquo;s not about convincing them, it&rsquo;s about making sure they have the ID with them if emergency strikes.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;As you might expect the older one was reluctant to think that she needed reminding every day with a placemat, so we told her she could schedule it in her phone, but if we saw her not wearing her ID, then it was back to the placemat. I think she likes the sense of independence,&rdquo; said Mrs Smith.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Huffington post writer and father of two, Kevin Harnett, says &lsquo;routines are typically neat and clean and easy to manage once you invest the time to get them up and running&rsquo;.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Fellow writer and mother of a 6-year-old with severe food allergies to eggs, milk, peanuts, tree nuts, shellfish and melons, Missy Voronyak said it was easier to get her daughter used to wearing the bracelet while she was young.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&ldquo;</strong>Most of the medical ID jewellery on the market is meant to be worn 24/7 &mdash; including while sleeping and bathing. It took less than a week for my daughter to get used to wearing her bracelet. Now we barely notice it,&rdquo; said Mrs Voronyak in her blog on <a href=&quot;http://marketingmama.com/5-reasons-children-with-food-allergies-should-wear-medical-id-jewelry&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Marketing Mama</a>.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve talked with families who wait to introduce medical ID jewellery until a child starts school and then face a battle of wills with the child. Many children end up wearing them only during the school day and then end up forgetting it.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I like having it as a regular part of our lives, not a <em>special </em>thing we have to remember. In fact, I didn&rsquo;t even think to remove it during our family portraits recently &ndash; and that&rsquo;s okay.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>As for what type of jewellery your child is most likely to put on and keep on, Mrs Voronyak believes the more traditional metal bracelets sit closer to the skin and fit more snugly on the wrist so the wearer usually doesn&rsquo;t notice it is there.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;My hunch is that children are more compliant with wearing a traditional metal bracelet because of this,&rdquo; said Mrs Voronyak.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I often hear two phrases in the food allergy world: 1) My child&rsquo;s been wearing a (metal) medical bracelet since they were diagnosed and never take it off! and 2) My child won&rsquo;t keep their bracelet on, they keep taking it off. The more traditional bracelets usually go on and stay on.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Of course each person and situation is different, so you need to do what works for your family,&rdquo; said Mrs Voronyak.</p>\r\n<p>With a host of fashionable new designs frequently being released Mrs Voronyak says there&rsquo;s no excuse that medical IDs &lsquo;don&lsquo;t look cool&rsquo;, and with an abundance of technology to assist us in remembering just about anything, MedicAlert are encouraging parents to sit down with their children and work out the best way of ensuring everyone is covered if the worst should happen.<br /><br /><br /></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Getting your kids to do important stuff, like wearing their medical ID',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2016-04-01','0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-08 20:18:46','2018-01-31 07:13:08',NULL),(21,34,10,1,6,'Men',NULL,NULL,'men',0,'<p>Whether it&rsquo;s everyday wear or a special occasion, we offer a range of men&rsquo;s medical jewellery to suit all needs. From stainless steel dog tags to braided bracelets and wristband tags for watches and activity trackers, you&rsquo;re bound to find the right fit.</p>\r\n<p> </p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'MedicAlert Men Range - Medical IDs for Men | MedicAlert','Shop our range of mens medical jewellery. From stainless steel dog tags to bracelets and wristband tags, there&#039;s a MedicAlert medical ID to suit you.\r\n',NULL,1,1,0,0,0,'/uploads/collections/men.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-22 14:31:53','2016-10-26 05:11:40',NULL),(22,36,10,1,6,'Women',NULL,NULL,'women',0,'<p>We offer a wide range of stunning women&rsquo;s bracelets and necklaces to suit all styles. From everyday stainless steel bracelets and necklets, to gorgeous 9ct gold bangles and Swarovski charm bracelets, there&rsquo;s a product for all occasions.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'MedicAlert Women Range - Medical IDs for Women | MedicAlert','Browse MedicAlert&reg; collection of medical alert bracelets, necklaces, pendants and other medical ID jewellery for women. Buy a medical ID to suit your style.\r\n',NULL,1,1,0,0,0,'/uploads/collections/women.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-22 18:13:24','2016-10-26 05:09:56',NULL),(23,36,10,1,6,'Category 2',NULL,NULL,'category-2',0,'<p>Category 2 content</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Category 2',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-07-22 18:13:24','2017-07-12 01:47:42','2017-07-12 11:17:43'),(24,94,1,0,0,'Benefits of membership','Only MedicAlert gives you full support in an emergency',NULL,'benefits-of-membership',1,'<p> </p>\r\n<p>When you purchase a genuine MedicAlert product, you&rsquo;re also investing in a vital MedicAlert membership. Together with your ID, this provides you with complete protection in an emergency. By becoming a member, you&rsquo;ll have peace of mind knowing you&rsquo;re taking control of your health.</p>','<h3>Protects in an emergency</h3>\r\n<p>Recommended by the World Health Organisation and World Allergy Organisation, the internationally recognised MedicAlert ID can help protect you in an emergency, no matter where you are in the world.</p>','<h3>Your secure electronic health record</h3>\r\n<p>As a MedicAlert member, your personal and health information is stored in our secure database. These details can be accessed by emergency personnel and healthcare professionals via our 24/7 Emergency Response Service, which is operated by professionally trained staff. When first responders, doctors or pharmacists call this service, they&rsquo;re provided with vital information about a patient&rsquo;s health conditions, ensuring they can receive the fastest and most effective treatment.</p>','For just ==membership_fee== per year, MedicAlert membership gives you access to a range of exclusive benefits','<h3>How MedicAlert membership protects you in an emergency</h3>\r\n<p>Only MedicAlert members wear the genuine MedicAlert ID. This provides first responders with vital information about your conditions and a 24/7 Emergency Response Service number to access your personal details held on your electronic health record, to provide the fastest and most effective treatment. The following diagram shows how your ID helps protect you when seconds count.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Benefits of a MedicAlert membership | MedicAlert','A MedicAlert membership is essential for anyone living with medical conditions, allergies or taking medication. Only MedicAlert gives you full support in an emergency.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/benefits-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:18:03','2018-01-16 23:42:50',NULL),(25,95,1,0,0,'Who needs membership','Who needs membership?',NULL,'who-needs-membership',1,'<p>Please click any of the categories below to see a more comprehensive list of medical conditions, allergies and special needs that we help cover in an emergency.</p>','<p>MedicAlert membership is also ideal for organ donors, travellers, identification assistance, or those who want to store their personal and health records.</p>\r\n<p>Don&#039;t wait until it&#039;s too late. Become a MedicAlert member today.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Who needs a MedicAlert membership',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/who-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:18:42','2016-10-24 05:24:44','2016-10-24 15:54:44'),(26,95,1,0,0,'Who needs membership',NULL,NULL,'who-needs-membership',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Who needs membership',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-02 06:18:42','2016-10-24 05:22:51','2016-10-24 15:52:50'),(27,96,1,0,0,'How to become a member',NULL,NULL,'how-to-become-a-member',1,'<h1>Become a MedicAlert member in just 3 easy steps</h1>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re ready to join the thousands of Australians who are already protected by MedicAlert Foundation, simply follow these 3 easy steps.</p>','<p>Take control of your health today. Become a MedicAlert member before it&rsquo;s too late. <br /><br />We recommend that you verify your health information with your health care provider to ensure that all information to be engraved is accurate. ASCIA (Australasian Society of Clinical Immunology &amp; Allergy) reccomends allergies be confirmed (authenticated) by your doctor.</p>\r\n<p> </p>','<h3>Other ways to join MedicAlert</h3>\r\n<p>If preferred, you can join MedicAlert in one of following ways:</p>','<p>Once you&rsquo;ve signed up, your order will be processed by our Membership Services team within 20 working days. If no further changes need to be made, a membership pack, including your engraved MedicAlert ID and wallet and fridge cards, will be sent to you via Australia Post after this processing time.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'How to become a MedicAlert member | MedicAlert','Become a MedicAlert member in just 3 easy steps and join the thousands of Australians who are already protected by MedicAlert Foundation.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/join-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:28:33','2018-03-06 05:59:19',NULL),(28,97,1,0,0,'Gift certificates','Help protect the ones you care for with a MedicAlert gift certificate',NULL,'gift-certificates',1,'<p>If you know someone who could benefit from a MedicAlert membership, or could use a new piece of jewellery, a MedicAlert gift certificate is the perfect way to show you care. This can go towards their annual membership fee or any MedicAlert product of their choice. Vouchers are available to purchase in any amount you like, or you can choose a pre-selected amount of $32, $50 or $100. Recipients can redeem their gift certificates online or over the phone.</p>\r\n<p>Simply choose the value, insert a few details and select when you&rsquo;d like it to arrive.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'MedicAlert Gift Certificates - Help Protect The Ones You Care | MedicAlert','Help protect the ones you care for with a MedicAlert gift certificate. Vouchers can go towards annual membership fees or MedicAlert products. \r\n',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/gift-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:29:41','2016-10-26 05:52:39',NULL),(29,98,1,0,0,'Update your details','Are you fully protected? Make sure your membership details are up to date',NULL,'update-your-details',1,'<p>So that we can best protect you in an emergency, it&rsquo;s vital that you update and/or confirm the accuracy of the information you&rsquo;ve given us each year. Just a few moments of your time will give you the peace of mind knowing you&rsquo;re protected when seconds count.</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately, if you do not confirm or update your information each year, MedicAlert Foundation may no longer consider you as a member and may withdraw any information you&rsquo;ve previously provided.</p>\r\n<p>Make sure you&rsquo;re protected. Update your details now.</p>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-12 text-center&quot;><a class=&quot;btn btn-red&quot; title=&quot;Update my details&quot; href=&quot;/update-my-profile &quot;>UPDATE MY DETAILS</a></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Update Your MedicAlert Membership Details | MedicAlert','Make sure you&#039;re fully protected in a medical emergency. Update your MedicAlert membership details in just a few easy steps.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/update-details-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:31:42','2016-10-26 05:53:55',NULL),(30,99,1,0,0,'Renew membership',NULL,NULL,'renew-membership',1,'<p><strong>Renew your MedicAlert membership and stay protected in an emergency </strong></p>\r\n<p>To ensure you can stay protected in a medical emergency, it&rsquo;s essential that you renew your MedicAlert membership each year. While you might have your identification jewellery, without a membership, emergency services can&rsquo;t access the vital information we keep on file about your conditions when it&rsquo;s needed most.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Renew your membership in one simple step and feel safe knowing you&rsquo;re protected.</p>\r\n<p> </p>','<div id=&quot;greyblock1&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;container&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-12 text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/homemembers.png&quot; alt=&quot;Members&quot; />\r\n<p class=&quot;bigtxt&quot;>MedicAlert membership is just ==membership_fee== a year</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert membership gives you access to a range of exclusive benefits:</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center benefits&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/benefit1.png&quot; alt=&quot;Protection for 12 months&quot; />\r\n<p>Protection for 12 months</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center benefits&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/benefit2.png&quot; alt=&quot;24/7 emergency service access to your medical information&quot; />\r\n<p>24/7 emergency service access to your medical information</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center benefits&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/benefit3.png&quot; alt=&quot;Exclusive member only offers&quot; />\r\n<p>Exclusive member only offers</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center benefits hidden-xs&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/benefit4.png&quot; alt=&quot;Unlimited wallet and fridge cards listing your details&quot; />\r\n<p>Unlimited wallet and fridge cards listing your details</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center benefits hidden-xs&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/benefit5.png&quot; alt=&quot;Secure online access to your electronic health record &quot; />\r\n<p>Secure online access to your electronic health record</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center benefits hidden-xs&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/benefit6.png&quot; alt=&quot;Support from our Membership Services team&quot; />\r\n<p>Support from our Membership Services team</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-12 text-center&quot;><a class=&quot;btn btn-red&quot; title=&quot;Learn more about MedicAlert membership&quot; href=&quot;/benefits-of-membership&quot;>LEARN MORE</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=&quot;whiteblock2&quot;> </div>','<p><strong>Time to upgrade your jewellery?</strong></p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s important to regularly check that your engraving is legible and the attachments (e.g. jump rings and clasps) are in good condition. If your engraving is difficult to read, or you&rsquo;d simply like a new medical ID style, you can order a new product when you renew your membership.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Replacement attachments can also be purchased by calling Membership Services on <strong>1800 88 22 22</strong>.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ndash; link to Shop page</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Renew membership',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:32:54','2016-10-25 01:43:13','2016-09-27 17:36:33'),(31,100,1,0,0,'Auto-renewal','Take control of your MedicAlert membership with auto-renewals',NULL,'auto-renewal',1,'<p>Take the hassle out of remembering to pay your annual MedicAlert membership with auto-renewals. By setting up Direct Debit payments, you can rest assured knowing you&rsquo;ll always be protected. <br /><br />It&rsquo;s easy to set up automated payments from your nominated credit card, cheque or savings account. Your membership fee will be automatically taken from that account on the due date each year, so you&rsquo;ll never miss a payment. You can unsubscribe at any time by contacting your financial institution directly or calling Membership Services on <a href=&quot;contact-us&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a>.</p>','<p>There are three easy ways to register for auto-renewals:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<div class=&quot;row autorenew&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/1-icon.png&quot; alt=&quot;1-icon.png (3 KB)&quot; width=&quot;99&quot; height=&quot;86&quot; />\r\n<div class=&quot;cost-text&quot;>1. Elect this option when you renew your annual membership</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/2-icon.png&quot; alt=&quot;2-icon.png (3 KB)&quot; width=&quot;104&quot; height=&quot;93&quot; />\r\n<div class=&quot;cost-text&quot;>2. Download our <a title=&quot;direct_debit_form_2016.pdf (450 KB)&quot; href=&quot;/uploads/documents/direct_debit_form_2016.pdf&quot;>Direct Debit form</a> and return it to us via post or email</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/3-icon.png&quot; alt=&quot;3-icon.png (4 KB)&quot; width=&quot;80&quot; height=&quot;80&quot; />\r\n<div class=&quot;cost-text&quot;>3. Contact our Membership Services team on <a href=&quot;contact-us&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Please ensure you have read our <a href=&quot;/terms-and-conditions&quot;>Direct Debit terms and conditions</a> before applying.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Auto-renewal',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/auto-renew-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:33:19','2016-10-24 01:02:41','2016-10-01 14:16:02'),(32,101,1,0,0,'Refer a friend','Refer a friend today',NULL,'refer-a-friend',1,'<p>If someone you know could benefit from a MedicAlert membership, don&rsquo;t wait until it&rsquo;s too late to tell them about it. Simply fill out the form below and we&rsquo;ll get in touch with them with more information. </p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Refer a friend to MedicAlert Foundation in Australia | MedicAlert','Could someone you know benefit from a MedicAlert membership? Refer a friend today by filling out this simple form.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/refer-friend-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:33:49','2016-10-26 05:56:59',NULL),(33,102,1,0,0,'Share your story','Share your story',NULL,'share-your-story',1,'<p>As a MedicAlert member, you&rsquo;re part of a global community of people who have taken a positive step towards protecting their health. From allergy sufferers to frequent travellers with medical conditions, every member has a reason for joining MedicAlert.</p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;d love to hear about what your MedicAlert membership means to you. No matter how big or small your story may be, we welcome you to share it with us. Your very own story could inspire others, and help demonstrate the importance of membership when it matters most.</p>\r\n<p>To share your story, simply fill out the form below, or post your thoughts to:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Share Your Story </strong><br /> MedicAlert Foundation<br /> GPO Box 9963<br /> Adelaide SA 5001</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>If your story is published, you&rsquo;ll also receive a <br /><strong>FREE</strong> Stainless Steel product of your choice.</h3>','<p><strong> Your name and story will not be published without your approval and consent.</strong></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Share your MedicAlert story | MedicAlert','Tell us what your MedicAlert membership means to you. Share your story with our global community here.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/share-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:34:53','2016-10-26 05:57:45',NULL),(34,103,1,0,0,'FAQs','Want to know more about MedicAlert Foundation?<br />View our FAQs',NULL,'faqs',1,'<p>if you have a question about MedicAlert Foundation, chances are you&#039;ll find the answer here. View some of our most frequently asked questions below.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Frequently Asked Questions - Medicalert Foundation Australia | MedicAlert','If you want to know more about MedicAlert Foundation, or have a question about our services, view our FAQs here.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/faq-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:35:21','2016-10-26 06:00:29',NULL),(35,104,1,0,0,'Testimonials','Share your story with the MedicAlert community',NULL,'testimonials',1,'<p>MedicAlert Foundation provides a voice for people all over the world who are committed to taking control of their health. We&rsquo;re proud to play a part in protecting our members every day, no matter what their conditions. View our members&rsquo; testimonies to find out how a MedicAlert membership has made a difference to their lives.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Testimonials',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/testimonial-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:35:43','2016-10-03 22:24:58','2016-10-04 08:55:02'),(36,105,1,0,0,'Refer your patients','One piece of advice could help save your clients&#039; life',NULL,'refer-your-patients',0,'<p>MedicAlert<sup>&reg;</sup> Foundation provides Australia&#039;s most trusted and recognised medical ID. By referring your clients to become a member, you can help to ensure they&#039;re protected in an emergency.</p>','<h3>It&#039;s easy to refer your clients</h3>\r\n<p> </p>','<p>As a not-for-profit organisation, we rely on your support to help us spread the word about our service. By simply telling your clients and colleagues about the importance of MedicAlert Foundation in an emergency, you&#039;re doing your part to help protect all Australians living with medical conditions.</p>\r\n<p>Your clients can become a member by visiting <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au&quot;>medicalert.org.au</a> or calling <a href=&quot;tel://1800 88 2222&quot;>1800 88 2222</a>.</p>','<h3>Protection when seconds count</h3>\r\n<p>Our national Board of Directors volunteer their time to ensure we can provide the best possible service for our members</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert members wear the genuine MedicAlert medical ID. Emergency services and medical personnel are trained to look for our internationally recognised IDs. Each ID provides a 24/7 emergency hotline number which first responders can call to access clients&#039; vital medical files. By having this information at hand, they can make a more accurate diagnosis and provide the fastest and most effective treatment when seconds count.</p>\r\n<p>Order your FREE sample medical ID by emailing <a href=&quot;mailto:kreek@medicalert.org.au&quot;>marketing@medicalert.org.au</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Refer your patients to MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/refer-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:36:08','2016-10-24 05:43:02','2016-10-24 16:13:02'),(37,106,1,0,0,'Emergency personnel','When seconds count, count on MedicAlert',NULL,'emergency-personnel',1,'<p>MedicAlert is more than an ID. Our exclusive 24/7 Emergency Response Service can give you a more detailed picture of a patient&rsquo;s condition, special needs, health history, medications and allergies.</p>\r\n<p>Together, our IDs and 24/7 Emergency Response Service help you make more informed decisions about a patient&rsquo;s treatment, which could mean the difference between life and death when seconds count.</p>','<h3>Watch our training video</h3>\r\n<p>To ensure you&rsquo;re fully up to date with MedicAlert&rsquo;s life saving service, we encourage you to watch our short video.</p>\r\n<div class=&quot;videoWrapper&quot;>\r\n<p><iframe src=&quot;//www.youtube.com/embed/4TfpGy6Iz4g?rel=0&quot; width=&quot;560&quot; height=&quot;314&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;allowfullscreen&quot;></iframe></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>For more information, you can download a free training kit, and also subscribe to receive industry relevant updates when changes and improvements are made to the MedicAlert product and service offering.</p>\r\n<p><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/emergency-kit.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><a class=&quot;btn-red btn&quot; href=&quot;/uploads/documents/medicalert_foundation_first_responders_training_kit.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>DOWNLOAD TRAINING KIT</a></p>','<p>MedicAlert IDs come in a range of different colours, shapes and styles which are updated every year. We recommend checking our products regularly to familiarise yourself with the different ID types.</p>\r\n<p class=&quot;text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/benefits-frontback.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;benefits-frontback.jpg (43 KB)&quot; width=&quot;598&quot; height=&quot;274&quot; /></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,10,99,'Information for emergency personnel | MedicAlert','It&#039;s important for emergency personnel to ensure they&#039;re fully equipped with knowledge about MedicAlert Foundation and our medical IDs. Learn more here.\r\n',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/emergency-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:36:32','2018-02-07 02:51:17',NULL),(38,106,1,0,0,'Emergency personnel',NULL,NULL,'emergency-personnel',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Emergency personnel',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-02 06:36:32','2016-09-16 06:11:00','2016-08-02 13:10:00'),(39,107,1,0,0,'Member partners','MedicAlert&rsquo;s member partners',NULL,'member-partners',1,'<p>At MedicAlert we&#039;re passionate about doing all we can to help Australians stay protected in an emergency. That&#039;s why we&#039;re proud to partner with a range of organisations across the country to ensure our members receive additional benefits with their MedicAlert membership.</p>\r\n<p>These dynamic partnerships allow us to provide more support, better value, discounted rates and other special offers, along with vital education about the importance of MedicAlert membership.</p>','<p>If your business is interested in becoming a member partner, we&#039;d love to hear from you.</p>\r\n<p><a title=&quot;Click to contact us&quot; href=&quot;/contact-us&quot;>Contact us</a> today to get started.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'MedicAlert&rsquo;s member partners - we partner with a range of organisations across the country',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/corp-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:37:15','2016-10-24 02:15:09','2016-10-24 12:45:09'),(40,108,1,0,0,'Help','MedicAlert is always here to help',NULL,'help',1,'<p>As a not-for-profit organisation, we value your feedback about our service and products. If you&#039;d like to provide your feedback, or have any questions or concerns about MedicAlert Foundation, simply fill out the form below and we&#039;ll get back to you soon.</p>','<p><strong>Our commitment to customer service</strong></p>\r\n<p>At MedicAlert Foundation we pride ourselves on our exceptional customer service. If you have any queries about our service or response time when submitting your query, please read our <a title=&quot;Communication Service Guarantee&quot; href=&quot;/terms-and-conditions#service-communication&quot;>Communication Service Guarantee</a>.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Have a question or need help from MedicAlert Foundation | MedicAlert','Got a question about MedicAlert Foundation? Our Membership Services team is always here to help. View our popular help topics or contact us here.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/feedback-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:37:38','2016-10-26 06:06:54',NULL),(41,109,1,0,0,'Careers',NULL,NULL,'careers',1,'<p>Joining us means you become part of the internationally recognised MedicAlert community and whatever the role, we all work towards our organisations vision, purpose and values to serve the Australian public - saving lives and providing protection in an emergency.</p>','<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1&quot;>\r\n<h3>Why work with us?</h3>\r\n<h5> </h5>\r\n<p>At Australia MedicAlert Foundation we are a small, open and energetic team. We are a people focussed, supportive and committed to promoting a workplace culture that encourages staff to grow, learn and achieve their goals. We provide on-going personal and professional development to allow our team to reach their aspirations, expand their knowledge and skills, and achieve and deliver against our business requirements.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Working with us means you will work in a safe, professional, dynamic and enjoyable work environment. We celebrate our employees achievements and milestones. We help one another to achieve and have fun along the way. We expect our employees to be committed to improving their own skills, being positive and enthusiastic brand ambassadors, service experts, and to delivering exceptional quality customer service to fellow team members and our Members.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1&quot;>\r\n<h3>Our Employee Benefits</h3>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2&quot;>\r\n<ul style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<li>Discounts on MedicAlert Membership and products for immediate family members</li>\r\n<li>Staff Incentive Programs</li>\r\n<li>Salary packaging</li>\r\n<li>Free parking</li>\r\n<li>Corporate attire provided</li>\r\n<li>Annual immunisation program &ndash; flu vaccinations for immediate family members</li>\r\n<li>Smoke free environment</li>\r\n<li>Employee Assistance Program</li>\r\n<li>Safe and comfortable work environment</li>\r\n<li>Career and personal development</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1&quot;>\r\n<h3>When joining us</h3>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>If we have a vacancy listed on our website or on the Seek website, job applications need to be addressed to our email address <span style=&quot;color: #ff0000;&quot;><a style=&quot;color: #ff0000;&quot; href=&quot;mailto:apply@medicalert.org.au&quot;>apply@medicalert.org.au</a></span> indicating the position you are applying for in the subject line.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>All applications should include:</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2&quot;>\r\n<ul style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<li>A cover letter which clearly indicates the position you are applying for and give a brief summary of your motivations for applying, your relevant skills and experience</li>\r\n<li>A statement demonstrating how you meet each of the selection criteria in the position description</li>\r\n<li>A copy of your resume in Word format outlining your work experience, educational background, professional development</li>\r\n<li>Names and contact details of three (3) professional referees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1&quot;>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>All employees must be an Australian Citizen, have permanent residency status or an appropriate working visa to apply for a position with Australian MedicAlert Foundation. All employment offers are subject to employees having a satisfactory national Police Clearance.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','<h3>Recruitment Privacy Statement</h3>\r\n<p>Statement of commitment</p>\r\n<p>Australia MedicAlert Foundation is committed to protecting an individual&#039;s right to privacy and to full compliance with its obligations under the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) as amended by the Privacy Amendment (Private Sector) Act 2000 (Cth) (&quot;Act&quot;). In particular, Australia MedicAlert Foundation will comply with the National Privacy Principles contained in the Act. This Privacy/Collection Statement explains some of these Principles and how they may apply to you, for more information <a title=&quot;download the Recruitment Privacy Statement&quot; href=&quot;/uploads/documents/Recruitment-Privacy-Statement-September-2016.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>download the Recruitment Privacy Statement</a>.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Careers - Join the MedicAlert Team in Australia | MedicAlert','Joining us means you become part of the internationally recognised MedicAlert community.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/career-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:38:22','2016-10-26 06:01:59',NULL),(42,111,1,0,0,'Accessibility','Your ease of accessibility is MedicAlert Foundation&#039;s priority',NULL,'accessibility',1,'<p>MedicAlert Foundation is committed to help thousands of people across Australia who may experience accessibility challenges. We have a range of policies and services in place to help cater to the needs of people with accessibility challenges, as detailed below.</p>','<p>Our website adheres to the global <a title=&quot;Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)&quot; href=&quot;https://www.w3.org/WAI/intro/wcag.php &quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)</a> to ensure people with disabilities and other accessibility challenges can perceive, understand, navigate and interact with all pages.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>If you&#039;re having any difficulties accessing our website, or would like to learn more about our accessibility services, please contact us.</p>\r\n<p> </p>','<h3 class=&quot;p1&quot;><span class=&quot;s1&quot;>Interpreting Service<br /><br /></span></h3>\r\n<p class=&quot;p1&quot;><span class=&quot;s1&quot;>As part of our goal to provide responsive personal medical identification and information to all Australian&rsquo;s we provide a free interpreting service for all members who call the member service hotline.</span></p>\r\n<p class=&quot;p2&quot;> </p>\r\n<p class=&quot;p1&quot;><span class=&quot;s1&quot;>To access this service simply call the member services team on <a title=&quot;Call us now&quot; href=&quot;tel:1800 88 22 22&quot;>1800 88 22 22</a> and advise them of what language you require interpreting services for (have a friend help you if you need) and we&rsquo;ll arrange a time for an interpreter to call you back to discuss your needs.</span></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Accessibility | MedicAlert','MedicAlert Foundation caters to the needs of people with accessibility challenges. Learn more about our policies and services here.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/access-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:39:35','2016-10-26 06:07:41',NULL),(43,112,1,0,0,'Donate','Your donations can make a difference',NULL,'donate',1,'<p>Our mission at MedicAlert&reg; Foundation is to help protect the thousands of Australians living with medical conditions. But to do this, we need your support.</p>\r\n<p>As a not-for-profit organisation, we rely on your generous donations to provide our vital service. With your help, we can continue to educate healthcare professionals about the importance of MedicAlert Foundation, and keep membership fees affordable for years to come.</p>\r\n<p>All donations $2.00 and over are tax deductible.</p>',NULL,'<h3>Ways to donate to MedicAlert Foundation</h3>\r\n<p>You can donate to MedicAlert Foundation by either:</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Donate',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/donate-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:40:56','2016-09-30 06:18:05','2016-09-30 15:48:02'),(44,114,1,0,0,'Cost',NULL,NULL,'cost',1,'<p>Your medical identification jewellery is backed by vital MedicAlert membership. It tells emergency services workers that you are protected by MedicAlert, and provides them with vital information about your conditions when seconds count. You become a member of the Foundation at the time of your first purchase of a medical bracelet or necklace.</p>','<h3>MedicAlert membership is just ==membership_fee== per year</h3>\r\n<p>For less than the cost of a tank of petrol, or a few days worth of takeaway coffees, your membership will provide you with real peace of mind knowing you&rsquo;re protected in an emergency. By renewing your MedicAlert membership each year, you can continue to enjoy the benefits of being a member, and rest assured knowing you&rsquo;re protected in an emergency.</p>','<h3>Payment help is available</h3>\r\n<p>Depending on your health fund and cover level, you may be eligible to receive rebates for the full or part cost of your MedicAlert membership and/or medical ID. The following funds currently provide rebates for MedicAlert members:</p>\r\n<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 helpimg text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/cost-hbf.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;HBS&quot; /></div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 helpimg text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/cost-cbhs.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;CBHS&quot; /></div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 helpimg text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/cost-aca.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;ACA Health&quot; /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>To see what you&#039;re covered for, please contact your health fund provider.</p>','<p>Bupa members receive this exclusive offer:</p>\r\n<p class=&quot;visible-xs&quot;><a title=&quot;Bupa&quot; href=&quot;/bupa&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive visible-xs&quot; src=&quot;/images/mob-bupa.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Bupa offer&quot; /></a></p>\r\n<p class=&quot;hidden-xs&quot;><a title=&quot;Bupa&quot; href=&quot;/bupa&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive hidden-xs&quot; src=&quot;/images/cost-bupa.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Bupa offer&quot; /></a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'How Much Does MedicAlert Membership Cost - View Our Prices | MedicAlert','MedicAlert membership is a small price to pay for complete peace of mind. Find out more about the cost of MedicAlert membership and join today.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/cost-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:44:26','2016-10-26 05:48:15',NULL),(45,160,2,0,17,'MedicAlert Foundation and Heart Foundation join in fundraising partnership',NULL,NULL,'t-foundation-and-heart-foundation-join-in-fundraising-partnership',0,'Australia&rsquo;s MedicAlert Foundation has partnered with the Heart Foundation to raise funds to fight cardiovascular disease, one of the most common causes of death in Australia, killing one Australian','<div id=&quot;description&quot; class=&quot;news-description&quot;>\r\n<p>Australia&rsquo;s MedicAlert Foundation has partnered with the Heart Foundation to raise funds to fight cardiovascular disease, one of the most common causes of death in Australia, killing one Australian every 12 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert already plays a valuable role in supporting many thousands of Australians living with a heart condition and this new partnership has now been expanded via a new fundraising campaign.</p>\r\n<p>The campaign, which officially begins launched at the start of November, runs until the end of the year and will see $5 donated to the Heart Foundation from each MedicAlert product sold with a special promotional code.</p>\r\n<p>The campaign aims to raise thousands of dollars for Heart Foundation, the leading organisation in Australia raising money for education and research into the prevention of cardiovascular disease.</p>\r\n<p>Many people living with heart disease, or recovering from heart surgery or heart attack, are on medications including anticoagulants. They choose to become a member of the MedicAlert Foundation and wear a MedicAlert bracelet or necklace to give them peace of mind in a medical emergency.</p>\r\n<p>If an emergency arises, first responders and first aid providers should know that the patient has a heart condition and is on anticoagulant medication.</p>\r\n<p>Adelaide grandfather, Robert Tunbridge, was in his early 50s in 2009 when he was diagnosed with cardiomyopathy, enlargement of the heart muscle. Specialists advised him his only option was to consider a heart and liver transplant. Complicating matters, he has a rare form of amyloidosis, a rare genetic condition that results in protein build up in organs and tissues.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;My wife and I decided to go for it as there was no other option,&rsquo;&rsquo; Mr Tunbridge said. &ldquo;I had my surgery in 2014 and to my knowledge I think I may be the only surviving transplant patient in Australia with amyloidosis.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;To my knowledge my transplant was one of the first of its kind in Australia using the &lsquo;heart in a box technology&rsquo;, where rather than being placed on ice until it can be transplanted, the donor heart is placed in a machine connected to its own blood supply until the time of surgery.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;One of the recommendations provided by my transplant team was to join MedicAlert, so that if required medical staff can quickly asses any pre-existing conditions and so they knew how to treat me accordingly if I were to collapse. Thankfully I haven&rsquo;t had to use my MedicAlert bracelet yet, but my family and I definitely feel safe knowing that I have this is a time of need.&rsquo;&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation Chief Executive Officer Heidi Jones said she is delighted MedicAlert is supporting the important work of the Heart Foundation.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Cardiovascular diseases (CVD) is one of the biggest killers of Australians and many thousands live with CVD,&rdquo; said Ms Jones. &ldquo;Supporting the Heart Foundation provides an opportunity to extend the support we provide to those living with or recovering CVD and helping raise valuable research funds.&rsquo;&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;It also provides an opportunity to raise awareness of the value to MedicAlert to patients living with cardiovascular disease. Both organisations will be actively marketing the fundraising campaign through their respective networks.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>The Heart Foundation has welcomed the fund raising partnership with the MedicAlert Foundation. It says the campaign will help generate important funds towards research projects.</p>\r\n<p>The fundraising campaign runs until December 31, 2015 with purchasers of MedicAlert products needing to quote Promotional Code HEART15 for funds to go directly to the Heart Foundation.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About MedicAlert Foundation </strong></p>\r\n<p>For over 40 years, MedicAlert Foundation has been the Nation&rsquo;s only not-for-profit organisation providing a 24/7 personal medical emergency information and identification service with close to 300,000 members joining since 1971. MedicAlert members wear a bracelet or necklace with a genuine MedicAlert emblem custom engraved with their vital medical information, membership number and MedicAlert hotline number. The 24/7 hotline allows emergency service personnel and healthcare professionals to access important additional medical and other details quickly and efficiently in a time of need.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About Heart Foundation</strong></p>\r\n<p>Our purpose is to reduce premature death and suffering from heart, stroke and blood vessel disease in Australia. For more than fifty years, the Heart Foundation has been dedicated to saving lives by making a difference to the heart health of all Australians. Donations from the community help us to fund vital research, develop guidelines for health professionals, support patient care and help Australians to live healthier lifestyles.</p>\r\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'MedicAlert Foundation and Heart Foundation join in fundraising partnership',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-1.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2015-11-06','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-12 12:31:04','2016-10-03 00:16:45','2016-10-03 10:46:31'),(46,161,2,0,17,'Tunstall and MedicAlert partnership connecting care service for clients',NULL,NULL,'tunstall-and-medicalert-partnership-connecting-care-service-for-clients',0,'Tunstall Healthcare and the MedicAlert Foundation are proud to announce an exciting new partnership which will seek to benefit some of Australia&#039;s most vulnerable residents around the country.\r\n','<p>Tunstall Healthcare and the MedicAlert Foundation are proud to announce an exciting new partnership which will seek to benefit some of Australia&#039;s most vulnerable residents around the country.</p>\r\n<p>From July 1, 2015, Tunstall Healthcare and the MedicAlert Foundation will embark on a new partnership to provide more comprehensive services to their respective clients and members.</p>\r\n<p>For over 40 years, the MedicAlert Foundation has been Australia&#039;s only not-for-profit organisation to provide a 24/7 personal medical emergency information and identification service.</p>\r\n<p>Operating globally for over 57 years, Tunstall Healthcare supports people to live independently with a range of assistive technology solutions that enable clients to have access to help when they need it most.</p>\r\n<p>&quot;Tunstall and MedicAlert share common values and philosophies on providing a high quality of service to our customers,&quot; said Tunstall&#039;s Managing Director Lyn Davies.</p>\r\n<p>&quot;Our new alliance aims to reach more people around Australia to gain access to a wider range of services and support to assist them to remain independent and safe, both in and out of their homes.&quot;</p>\r\n<p>Collectively the two organisations provide assistance to more than 200,000 Australians with varying healthcare needs.</p>\r\n<p>&quot;At MedicAlert, our core purpose is to provide responsive personal medical identification and information for all Australians, and Tunstall Healthcare aligns with this vision,&quot; said MedicAlert&#039;s Chief Executive Officer Heidi Jones.</p>\r\n<p>&quot;This partnership marks the start of a range of innovations, services and technology we are introducing to ensure that we continue to meet the needs of our current and new members,&quot; she said.</p>\r\n<p>This partnership is an exciting step forward for Tunstall and MedicAlert in providing connected healthcare services for their clients.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About Medic Alert Foundation</strong></p>\r\n<p>For over 40 years, Australia Medic Alert Foundation has been the Nation&rsquo;s only not-for-profit organisation providing a 24/7 personal medical emergency information and identification service, with close to 300,000 members joining since 1971.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert members wear a bracelet or necklace with a genuine MedicAlert emblem custom engraved with their vital medical information, membership number and hotline number.</p>\r\n<p>The 24/7 hotline allows emergency service personnel and healthcare professionals to access important additional medical and other details quickly and efficiently in a time of need.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Tunstall and MedicAlert partnership connecting care service for clients',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-4.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2015-07-01','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-12 12:37:07','2016-10-03 00:21:39','2016-10-03 10:51:25'),(47,162,2,0,17,'MedicAlert Foundation and National Breast Cancer Foundation join in fundraising partnership',NULL,NULL,'medicalert-foundation-and-national-breast-cancer-foundation-join-in-fundraising-partnership',0,'Australia&rsquo;s MedicAlert Foundation has partnered with the National Breast Cancer Foundation (NBCF) to raise funds to fight one of the most commonly diagnosed cancers among Australian women.','<div id=&quot;description&quot; class=&quot;news-description&quot;>\r\n<p>Australia&rsquo;s MedicAlert Foundation has partnered with the National Breast Cancer Foundation (NBCF) to raise funds to fight one of the most commonly diagnosed cancers among Australian women.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert already plays a valuable role in supporting many thousands of Australian women living with, or recovering from, breast cancer and this new partnership has now been expanded via a new fundraising campaign.</p>\r\n<p>The campaign, which is officially launched mid-October, runs until the end of the year and will see $5 donated to the NBCF from each MedicAlert product sold with a special promotional code.</p>\r\n<p>The campaign aims to raise thousands of dollars for NBCF, the leading community-funded organisation in Australia raising money for research into the prevention and cure of breast cancer.</p>\r\n<p>Many women living with, or recovering from breast cancer, choose to become a member of the MedicAlert Foundation and wear a MedicAlert bracelet or necklace to give them piece of mind in a medical emergency.</p>\r\n<p>If an emergency arises, injections and Intravenous therapy (IV) in the arms of women living with, or recovering from breast cancer should be avoided. This is because after surgery women can develop lymphedema, a sometimes painful swelling in the arm, which is more susceptible to infection.</p>\r\n<p>Simple procedures or activities such as drawing blood, leaning a book on the arm, being vaccinated, or measuring blood pressure can lead to a severe infection.</p>\r\n<p>Townsville grandmother and breast cancer survivor Sally Clayton, 76, said she would not be without her MedicAlert medical ID.</p>\r\n<p>Sixteen years ago Mrs Clayton was diagnosed with breast cancer and successfully treated, which included the removal of lymph nodes.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Over the years I&rsquo;ve had a bracelet and necklace and now I&rsquo;ve moved to a stretchy bands and I never take it off. I like to travel as much as I can and it&rsquo;s a real peace of mind for me and my family to know that in case there&rsquo;s an emergency, they need to be careful of certain procedures.&rsquo;&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation Chief Executive Officer Heidi Jones said she is delighted MedicAlert is supporting the important work of the NBCF.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Breast cancer is the most commonly diagnosed cancer among women in Australia with one in eight women developing breast cancer in their lifetime,&rdquo; said Ms Jones.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Supporting the Foundation provides an opportunity to extend the support we provide to women living with or recovering from breast cancer by raising awareness and funds.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;It also provides an opportunity to raise awareness of the value to MedicAlert to women living with or recovering from breast cancer.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Both organisations will be actively marketing the fundraising campaign through their respective networks.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>The National Breast Cancer Foundation has welcomed the fund raising partnership with the MedicAlert Foundation. It says the campaign will help generate important funds towards research project. Research is the most effective way to end breast cancer, one of the biggest killers of Australian women and impacting many thousands of families.</p>\r\n<p>The fundraising campaign runs until December 31, 2015 with purchasers of MedicAlert products needing to quote Promotional Code NBCF15 for funds to go directly to the National Breast Cancer Foundation.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About MedicAlert Foundation</strong></p>\r\n<p>For over 40 years, MedicAlert Foundation has been the Nation&rsquo;s only not-for-profit organisation providing a 24/7 personal medical emergency information and identification service with close to 300,000 members joining since 1971.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert members wear a bracelet or necklace with a genuine MedicAlert emblem custom engraved with their vital medical information, membership number and MedicAlert hotline number.</p>\r\n<p>The 24/7 hotline allows emergency service personnel and healthcare professionals to access important additional medical and other details quickly and efficiently in a time of need.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About National Breast Cancer Foundation</strong></p>\r\n<p>The National Breast Cancer Foundation is the leading community-funded organisation in Australia raising money for research into the prevention and cure of breast cancer.</p>\r\n<p>They work with the public who both give and raise funds and the research community to whom they grant funds to change the health future.</p>\r\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'MedicAlert Foundation and National Breast Cancer Foundation join in fundraising partnership',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-1.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2014-10-14','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-12 14:09:42','2016-10-03 00:19:28','2016-10-03 10:49:14'),(48,163,10,1,6,'Kids',NULL,NULL,'kids',0,'<p>Designed specially for kids, our children&rsquo;s collection offers a large variety of fashionable and practical medical identification jewellery. From vibrant sports bands to gold-filled bracelets, there&rsquo;s a unique product for every girl and boy.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'MedicAlert Kids Range - Medical IDs for Children | MedicAlert','Designed specially for kids, our children&#039;s collection offers a wide variety of medical identification jewellery for every girl and boy. Shop the range. ',NULL,1,1,0,0,0,'/uploads/collections/children.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-16 15:17:48','2016-10-26 05:12:57',NULL),(49,164,10,1,6,'New',NULL,NULL,'new',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,'MedicAlert New Range of  Medical IDs - New Collection | MedicAlert','Browse our new range of medical identification jewellery styles. Our products are updated regularly so be sure to check back for new additions. ',NULL,1,1,0,0,0,'/uploads/collections/new.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-16 15:37:27','2016-10-26 05:15:23',NULL),(50,165,10,1,6,'Everyday',NULL,NULL,'everyday',0,'<p>Our classic everyday collection is perfect for daily wear. With a range of practical, yet stylish jewellery types to choose from, including stainless steel, sterling silver and wristband tags, there&rsquo;s something to suit everyone.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,5,'MedicAlert Everyday Collection - Medical IDs for Daily Use | MedicAlert','Perfect for daily wear, our everyday medical identification jewellery collection offers a range of practical and stylish ways to stay protected.',NULL,1,1,0,0,0,'/uploads/collections/everyday.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-16 15:38:39','2016-10-26 05:16:51',NULL),(51,166,4,0,104,'Amanda Tionisio',NULL,NULL,'amanda-tionisio',0,'Rockingham, WA, member since 2012','I feel protected knowing that my family&#039;s medical information is available in the case of an emergency, particularly if something should happen to any of us and we are far from home.','<p>There are few people that may ever claim to understand MedicAlert Foundation member, Amanda Tionisio&rsquo;s, extremely rare condition, but many of you will know the anxiety she feels living with a life-threatening disease.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I was diagnosed with HAE (Hereditary Angioedema) at the age of 5 when my Father received his diagnosis. For many years prior, the condition was thought of and treated as an allergic reaction,&rdquo; Amanda says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I have lived nearly my entire life with HAE and it is all I have ever known.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Amanda says it was her immunologist who suggested she contact MedicAlert, as it&rsquo;s particularly important when living with a chronic rare disease that medical professionals and others around you are away of your condition in the case of an emergency.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;With a rare disease such as HAE there is an increased risk of fainting and there is also the risk of oedema in the airways &ndash; these are times when it would be difficult to convey to others about the condition and having the bracelet alerts them to the condition,&rdquo; Amanda says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I am also anaphylactic to Fresh Frozen Plasma so my specialist advised me that in the case of an accident where I wasn&rsquo;t able to respond &ndash; having that information on my bracelet could be the difference between life and death.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>With four young children to look after, and two of her girls also having HAE, Amanda says MedicAlert bracelets have taken on a newfound importance in her family.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;My two daughters with HAE are also MedicAlert members,&rdquo; Amanda says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;It is very frightening as a parent of a child with a chronic and potentially life-threatening disease, to send them out of your care. It requires a lot of trust in those around them and having their bracelets on provides a sense of relief that their condition can be identified.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I feel protected knowing that my family&#039;s medical information is available in the case of an emergency, particularly if something should happen to any of us and we are far from home or if I am alone with my 4 young children.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Amanda&rsquo;s passion to help her girls, and others affected by the condition, has seen her become the Secretary of HAE Australasia, where she points out their focus is in their name.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;H is about &lsquo;hope&rsquo;, A is about &lsquo;Advocacy, and E is about &lsquo;Education&rsquo;, because together we know we can beat this,&rdquo; Amanda says.</p>\r\n<p>For more information about HAE please visit <a href=&quot;http://www.haeaustralasia.org.au/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>www.haeaustralasia.org.au/</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Amanda Tionisio',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/testimonial-1.png',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-19 09:57:36','2016-10-01 03:51:06','2016-10-01 13:20:54'),(52,167,4,0,104,'Peter Richards',NULL,NULL,'peter-richards',0,'Glandore, SA, member since 2009','MedicAlert seemed like an obvious choice to me, if I was unable to speak for myself in an emergency, doctors would still know that I had electrodes and battery powered neuro stimulators implanted in my head and chest','<p>Meet MedicAlert Foundation member Peter Richards, a humble man and avid traveller, who thought his time abroad might be at an end when he was diagnosed with Parkinson&rsquo;s disease 13 years ago.</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;</em>After almost seven years of gradual decline, and despite everybody&rsquo;s best efforts to alleviate my Parkinson&rsquo;s symptoms, I was in a tough spot, finding it difficult to walk for long periods and suffering significant left hand tremors.&rdquo; Peter says.</p>\r\n<p>What happened next would come as a welcome shock to both Peter and his wife Kathy, as the pair headed to Brisbane to discuss Peter&rsquo;s suitability for Deep Brain Stimulation (DBS) surgery.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;The revolutionary treatment involves surgeons placing electrodes deep into the affected parts of a Parkinson&rsquo;s sufferer&rsquo;s brain,&rdquo; Peter says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;These electrodes are connected by wire leads to battery powered neuro stimulators implanted in the patient&rsquo;s chest. Electrical impulses are sent to the electrodes to help alleviate certain physical symptoms of Parkinson&rsquo;s, including slowness of movement and tremors&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p>On 1 April 2009 Peter underwent DBS surgery. Seven weeks later, he and his wife Kathy embarked on a cruise ship to Asia.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Having DBS was clearly the best decision Kathy and I ever made,&rdquo; he says.</p>\r\n<p>While the surgery had improved his physical capabilities, Peter says his confidence and peace of mind still wavered, as he feared what might happen if caught in an emergency, without someone to explain his condition and various implants.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;MedicAlert seemed like an obvious choice to me, if I was unable to speak for myself in an emergency, doctors would still know that I had electrodes and battery powered neuro stimulators implanted in my head and chest,&rdquo; Peter says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;In the wrong situation this could pose significant health risks, so it&rsquo;s great to have that peace of mind, and it&rsquo;s allowed us to travel to Asia with confidence, not once or twice, but five times since I had the surgery.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Peter explains that it wasn&rsquo;t only he who benefitted from his MedicAlert Foundation membership, it was his wife too.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Kathy works part-time, so it allows both her and I to feel more relaxed at home, or out and about, and most importantly allows us to maintain our independence.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;All in all it&rsquo;s given me the confidence to be part of the real world, which is priceless.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Grateful for the assistance he received over many years, Peter is now a very active member of Parkinson&rsquo;s SA and the Parkinson&rsquo;s SA Deep Brain Stimulation Group. The 65-year-old says that he has definitely found his calling in helping others, and outside of a few more overseas trips, Peter says that is how he plans to spend his days.</p>\r\n<p>To watch the miracle of Deep Brain Stimulation surgery <a href=&quot;http://www.abc.net.au/7.30/content/2014/s4084426.htm&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>click here</a></p>\r\n<p>For more information on Parkinson&rsquo;s SA <a href=&quot;http://www.parkinsonssa.org.au/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>click here</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Peter Richards',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/testimonial-2.png',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-19 10:01:06','2016-10-01 03:39:39','2016-10-01 13:09:27'),(53,168,4,0,104,'Thomas Bunning',NULL,NULL,'brenda-nirenstein',0,'Adelaide, SA, member since ','As someone who deeply understands the importance of being able to communicate clearly, it&rsquo;s great to know that even if I was caught in an emergency overseas, my medical details would be made available to the people treating me.','<p>MedicAlert Foundation member Tom Bunning was walking a familiar stretch of road when disaster struck. In the early hours of Sunday 3 September 2006 Tom was hit by a passing car, leaving the then 19-year-old unconscious and fighting for his life.</p>\r\n<p>With a punctured lung and severe swelling of the brain, amongst other injuries, Tom was left in an induced coma and on life-support.</p>\r\n<p>After a week and just as things seemed on the up, Tom suffered another set back, with massive and unrelieved pressure on the brain causing further damage and leaving doctors with little hope.</p>\r\n<p>To save his life surgeons were forced to perform a bifrontal craniectomy &ndash; removing a large flap of skull to reduce the pressure on his brain. While the procedure was successful, Tom was given slim to no chance of survival, as doctors warned of what his life might be like even if he did wake up.</p>\r\n<p>After 3 weeks in a coma, he started to breathe on his own and his brain began to settle. Over the coming weeks and months, Tom&rsquo;s family were given the shocking news that a third of his brain was dead. But still he endured, and as he woke up to realise he couldn&rsquo;t walk, talk, read, write, understand what people said, remember or even taste, it was evident that Tom&rsquo;s life would never be the same again.</p>\r\n<p>Nine years on and Tom&rsquo;s will to live life to the fullest has seen him fight to regain much of what he lost, including re-enrolling in university, travelling the world and becoming the Co-Chair of &lsquo;Talkback&rsquo; which is the peak body for people living with aphasia in South Australia.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Aphasia is a loss of language skills caused by stroke or other brain injury and continues to be one of the greatest challenges in my life,&rdquo; Tom says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;In South Australia there are about 10,000 people living with aphasia, and yet it remains a very misunderstood and unknown disorder, largely because those with it struggle to communicate.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>As someone with a number of complex and potentially life-threatening conditions, Tom says a MedicAlert membership was a simple choice that gave both he and his mum peace of mind.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I didn&rsquo;t want to have to stop doing the things I loved, like travel, study and attending social outings, but I also knew that I would be in danger if an emergency struck and the people around me weren&rsquo;t aware of my medical history,&rdquo; he says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;As someone who deeply understands the importance of being able to communicate clearly, it&rsquo;s great to know that even if I was caught in an emergency overseas, my medical details would be made available to the people treating me.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Tom says he is looking forward to an upcoming trip to Europe, and feels that extra layer of confidence knowing that the MedicAlert emblem is recognised worldwide.</p>\r\n<p>To find out more about the Talkback Association for Aphasia head to <a href=&quot;http://www.aphasia.asn.au/&quot;>http://www.aphasia.asn.au/</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Thomas Bunning',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/testimonial-3.png',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-19 10:02:45','2016-10-01 03:58:27','2016-10-01 13:28:15'),(54,170,4,0,104,'Robert Tunbridge',NULL,NULL,'emily-ahrens',0,'Craigmore, SA, member since','If I were to collapse or need assistance the paramedics can tailor their response to my needs accordingly and these details are on my alert bracelet. Thankfully I haven&rsquo;t had to use my MedicAlert bracelet yet, but I definitely feel safe knowing that I have this in a time of need','<p>In 2008 MedicAlert Foundation member Robert Tunbridge was hiking up a mountain at Whistler in Canada when he experienced a familiar problem - shortness of breath. For many years doctors had treated his symptoms as asthma, because his general aerobic capacity was well above average for his age, but as Robert recalls this was all about to change.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;When I told my doctor about my mountain mishap they decided to take me for a &lsquo;stress echo&rsquo;, which highlighted a problem with my heart&rsquo;s ability to recover,&rdquo; Robert says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Specialists soon diagnosed me with a rare form of cardio myopathy related to a genetic problem called Transthyretin Amyloidosis. They suggested I get my affairs into order as there was no cure except transplant, and of the three (heart and liver) transplants they had attempted with my condition none had survived.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>With few options worth considering, Robert and his wife jumped on a plane to Sydney to find out whether he was an eligible candidate for a transplant.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;After 10 days of testing I was put on the transplant list, and the long wait began,&rdquo; he says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I was put on the list in July 2012 and in February 2013 I got a phone call from one of the transplant coordinators saying that they had a heart for me.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;My wife and I were on a plane within two hours and that day I went under the knife for the heart transplant surgery.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Despite the operation not quite going go to plan and his recovery being extremely slow, Robert remains one of the few surviving heart transplant patients in Australia with Amyloidosis.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;While doctors would normally aim to transplant both the heart and liver for Amyloidosis patients, they feared the risks of attempting this were far too great, and focussed on getting my new heart working correctly,&rdquo; Robert says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Despite a number of near death experiences and &lsquo;Australian firsts&rsquo; being required just to keep me alive, I was discharged nine weeks later with a new lease on life thanks to an extraordinarily selfless individual, whose heart I will literally never forget.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Robert says one of the first recommendations provided by his transplant team was to join MedicAlert Foundation, so that his unique condition would be made available to treating medical staff in an emergency.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;If I were to collapse or need assistance the paramedics can tailor their response to my needs accordingly and these details are on my alert bracelet. Thankfully I haven&rsquo;t had to use my MedicAlert bracelet yet, but I definitely feel safe knowing that I have this in a time of need,&rdquo; he says.</p>\r\n<p>While Robert continues to deal with a number of obstacles, he remains optimistic about life and is working to assist doctors in finding a cure for the defective amyloid gene.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I have already been the guinea pig with some of the procedures and drugs I&rsquo;ve taken to date, so if I can help others benefit from my journey then that would be a great outcome.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>To share your story via our newsletter email your interest to <a href=&quot;mailto:sharemystory@medicalert.org.au&quot;>sharemystory@medicalert.org.au</a>.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Robert Tunbridge',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/testimonial-4.png',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-22 13:03:35','2016-10-01 03:34:02','2016-10-01 13:03:50'),(55,171,4,0,104,'Denise Mascaro',NULL,NULL,'denise-mascaro',0,'Dubbo, NSW, member since 1990','Emergency workers and health staff see my MedicAlert medical ID around my neck and they take notice of it &ndash; I can&rsquo;t tell you how many times it has saved my life','<p>Most of us have encountered an idling bus or truck and inhaled a lungful of unwanted diesel fumes and were left feeling sightly queasy. For MedicAlert member Denise Mascaro, the outcome is far worse &ndash; as she discovered when she nearly died a short time after breathing in fumes from a bus parked on the forecourt of the motel she owned at the time.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I have severe anaphylaxis and through pure accident I discovered that diesel fumes are probably the most deadly thing to me, and it is only because of the quick-thinking medical staff at the local hospital that I am here today,&rdquo; Denise says.</p>\r\n<p>It wasn&rsquo;t the first time that the New South Wales woman has had a near-fatal episode &ndash; in fact she has been through the experience twice &ndash; and been revived successfully on each occasion.</p>\r\n<p>Denise wasn&rsquo;t born with any of her life-threatening issues. As a child she had asthma and eczema. A bout of whooping cough that turned into pneumonia as a youngster saw her treated with antibiotics which set off a chain of events that turned her life upside down.</p>\r\n<p>It was after lung surgery in 1979 that she developed severe health and allergy issues, with the suspected cause being a reaction to the drugs she had received.</p>\r\n<p>The 61-year old now suffers from recurrent anaphylaxis, asthma, bronchiectasis, migraines and she also has type 2 diabetes. She has undergone allergy testing to try to pinpoint the triggers.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I had no reaction to any of the placebos and had differing grades of reactions to a range of other materials. One thing I didn&rsquo;t react to at the time was MSG (monosodium glutamate), which was a surprise to everyone involved,&rdquo; she says.</p>\r\n<p>That surprise turned to horror later that night when Denise suffered a delayed and very severe reaction that would give her a second near-fatal experience.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I carry my MedicAlert card with me at all times and when I was rushed to hospital they saw it and went straight into resuscitation mode, which again saved my life.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Exactly what triggers an anaphylaxis reads like a who&rsquo;s who of daily dangers and includes regularly prescribed antibiotics and a number of other drugs, latex, artificial colourings and preservatives, and of course, diesel fumes, to name a few.</p>\r\n<p>While Denise jokes that she lives a hermit lifestyle these days, the serious reality is that when it comes to going outside her home, it&rsquo;s often just too much of a risk to take.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I can&rsquo;t go to the movies, I avoid people wearing strong perfume, I don&rsquo;t eat food prepared by someone else, and soap and garden aisles in the supermarkets are no-go zones for me,&rdquo; Denise says.</p>\r\n<p>With the severity of reaction dictated by her exposure to a certain trigger, it was the danger of not being able to tell people her condition in an emergency that sparked Denise to research for a trusted way to alert health authorities.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;MedicAlert membership was the best solution for me and I know that if I become unconscious then someone coming to my aid can make a correct assessment and give me the life-saving adrenalin that I need,&rdquo; she says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I have one daughter who is a nurse and another who is a radiographer, so I am in good hands when they are around, and my MedicAlert emblem helps me when they are not.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Emergency workers and health staff see my MedicAlert emblem around my neck and they take notice of it &ndash; I can&rsquo;t tell you how many times it has saved my life.&rdquo;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Denise Mascaro',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/testimonial-5.png',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-22 13:05:33','2016-10-01 03:37:19','2016-10-01 13:07:06'),(56,172,4,0,104,'Darrin Burgmann',NULL,NULL,'darrinburgmann',0,'Nowra, NSW 2016','&ldquo;Chances are I could be found in just about any state - unconscious due to low blood pressure or suffering an attack of some variety - so at least if a member of the public or a paramedic can look at my wrist and see what is wrong, then they&rsquo;ll know what to do, or at least who to call &ndash; my Mum,&rdquo; said Darrin.','<p>Walking into his home in Nowra New South Wales, you would have no idea that MedicAlert member Darrin Burgmann even has a medical condition, and yet, this former nurse of nine years has one of the rarest and most debilitating conditions on the planet.<br /><br />Six years ago, while he was still working as a nurse, the now 41-year-old began noticing he was forgetting things and said certain tasks seemed to be becoming more difficult.<br /><br />&ldquo;I really had no idea what was going on, and despite a growing range of bizarre symptoms and an even bigger list of tests I was undertaking, no one had any answers, other than to say &lsquo;you&rsquo;re losing your mind&rsquo; or &lsquo;you must be making this up&rsquo;,&rdquo; said Darrin.<br /><br />&ldquo;While I knew that wasn&rsquo;t true, many of my behaviours - suddenly dropping things, seeing objects, almost blacking out or having my limbs fling out randomly - seemed to suggest something wasn&rsquo;t right.&rdquo;<br /><br />After four years of tests and devastating speculation about his mental state, Darrin was diagnosed with Multiple System Atrophy (MSA) or Shy-Drager Syndrome (SDS) which is a rare degenerative condition resulting from deterioration of certain nerve cells in the brain and spinal cord.<br /><br />&ldquo;When I was finally diagnosed in June 2015, I was both relieved and devastated. Relieved to know that I wasn&rsquo;t mad and that all these trips to hospital were in fact justified, but also devastated, because I had a chronic incurable disease with a short life-span,&rdquo; said Darrin.<br /><br />&ldquo;I&rsquo;d already had my stomach and kidneys shutdown and had endured issues with my heart, bladder and pancreas &ndash; most of which saw me rushed to hospital in the back of an ambulance.&rdquo;<br /><br />But, while he was (and still is) facing a completely unpredictable set of symptoms that could present at any time, Darrin said he wanted to try and continue living as normal a life as possible.<br /><br />&ldquo;I didn&rsquo;t want my life to be over, so I began looking into measures that would allow me to retain some quality of life and most importantly the independence we all enjoy,&rdquo; said Darrin.<br /><br />&ldquo;I&rsquo;d often heard patients talking about the freedom and security they felt from using a MedicAlert bracelet, because it had information about their condition, allergies and gave their emergency contact details, which for me is so important, because my Mum and sister are really the two who know most about my illness.&rdquo;<br /><br />Darrin said that with diabetes, an allergy to certain medications and peanuts, as well as a host of issues relating to his MSA, he&rsquo;d be silly not to have this documented, so that emergency responders can treat him correctly.<br /><br />&ldquo;Chances are I could be found in just about any state - unconscious due to low blood pressure or suffering an attack of some variety - so at least if a member of the public or a paramedic can look at my wrist and see what is wrong, then they&rsquo;ll know what to do, or at least who to call &ndash; my Mum,&rdquo; said Darrin.<br /><br />First discovered in 1960, MSA impacts around one in 10,000 people (or around 2300 Australians) and is most known for attacking the autonomic or involuntary nervous system (which controls blood pressure, heart rate, and bladder function) and the motor system (which controls balance and muscle movement). This often means people with MSA will often present with a variety of disorders and complications, many of which can be similar to Parkinson&rsquo;s disease.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Darrin Burgmann',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-22 13:09:26','2016-10-01 03:30:47','2016-10-01 13:00:35'),(57,173,4,0,104,'Skye-Anne Ellard',NULL,NULL,'skye-anne-ellard',0,'Seaford Rise, SA, member since 2009','Never having had morphine before I was looking forward to the near-instant pain relief that had been promised to me, but what I got was certainly unexpected and nowhere near that outcome','<div id=&quot;&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;container&quot;>\r\n<p>As a result of being born prematurely, Skye-Anne Ellard suffered from recurring kidney problems from a young age - and over the years that followed she became very familiar with the hospital system.</p>\r\n<p>As it turns out those experiences must have left their mark, because the now 23-year old Adelaide careworker has turned her attention to carving a career in the health sector, and is currently studying nursing at Flinders University.</p>\r\n<p>It wasn&rsquo;t until her early teens, however, that she stumbled across the fact that she has a severe &ndash; and potentially fatal &ndash; anaphylaxis to morphine. It was when she was admitted to hospital as a 16-year old with a severe kidney infection and given morphine to better manage the crippling pain that the drama began.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Never having had morphine before I was looking forward to the near-instant pain relief that had been promised to me, but what I got was certainly unexpected and nowhere near that outcome,&rdquo; Skye says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;As soon as the needle had been pushed into my IV I could feel the morphine moving into my vein and my body suddenly felt like it was on fire, with a horrific rash instantly spreading,&rdquo; she says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;My throat started to close up, I couldn&#039;t breathe, and the last thing I remembered before passing out was an alarm beeping, people running from all directions towards my room, and my mum being pushed out of the way.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>The emergency response was justified, with Skye going into respiratory arrest and having to be intubated and given shots of adrenaline to get her heart back to beating in a normal rhythm.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;When I woke up a few hours later the doctor told me it was the quickest and worst reaction to morphine that he had ever seen - so for my own piece of mind I became a Medic Alert member and invested in a bracelet,&rdquo; she says.</p>\r\n<p>After already surviving one near-miss, the decision to become a Medic Alert member was one that would save her life several years later.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I had been out at a music festival at Glenelg and was walking with some friends when we were jumped and bashed in the middle of a busy street,&rdquo; Skye says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;After being knocked to the ground, repeatedly punched in the head and kicked to the back of my skull and ribs I was barely conscious when an ambulance arrived.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;The paramedics put me in a spinal collar and strapped me to a board, and even though I could see the paramedic inserting an IV line to give me morphine, I was in so much agony that I couldn&#039;t talk or move &ndash; and that&rsquo;s when panic hit me.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Skye managed to draw on her remaining strength to lift up her arm and the paramedic spotted her Medic Alert bracelet on her wrist and no morphine was given.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;While I was left to recover from serious injuries from the attack, I have no doubt that my bracelet saved my life that night &ndash; and I wear it every hour of every day, because something can happen in an instant and it could be my only chance of survival.&rdquo;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Skye-Anne Ellard',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-22 13:56:36','2016-10-01 03:58:16','2016-10-01 13:28:04'),(58,219,1,0,0,'Update my profile','Update my profile',NULL,'update-my-profile',0,'<p>If you continue and update your record, you will be locked out of your member profile until a Membership Services representative has reviewed and updated your profile. Please make sure you have made changes on all relevant tabs before continuing. This is so that our quality control team can review your updates. You will receive an email once your profile has been confirmed.</p>','<p>Your updates are currently pending. You can still <a href=&quot;/products&quot;>continue to shop</a>.</p>\r\n<p>You are unable to make any more changes to your &#039;Personal&#039; details until the changes you made have been reviewed and updated by our Membership Services team.</p>','<p>Your updates are currently pending. You can still continue making more changes.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Update my profile | MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'2016-09-16 15:36:18','2017-04-11 00:45:03',NULL),(59,220,5,0,17,'MedicAlert Foundation First Responder Training ',NULL,NULL,'medicalert-foundation-first-responder-training-',0,'MedicAlert Foundation First Responder Training','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4TfpGy6Iz4g',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'MedicAlert Foundation First Responder Training ',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/videos/6-september-video.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1,'2016-09-16 16:20:27','2018-01-31 23:51:47',NULL),(60,221,1,0,0,'Thank you for signing up',NULL,NULL,'thank-you-for-signing-up',0,'<p>You have been successfully signed up to our email newsletter.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Thank you for signing up to our newsletter | MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1,'2016-09-19 18:04:32','2016-10-26 06:45:27',NULL),(61,222,1,0,0,'Quick renew','Renew your MedicAlert membership in one easy step',NULL,'quick-renew',0,'<p>Simply enter your credit card information below to renew your annual membership.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>If you want to re-order a product when you renew your membership, you can view your past purchases and re-order or review an ID. </p>\r\n<p><a class=&quot;btn btn-red&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 10px;&quot; href=&quot;/my-purchases&quot;>My purchases</a></p>','<p>Your MedicAlert membership has not expired yet.</p>','<p> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>Why renew?</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>A MedicAlert&reg; ID can help first responders quickly identify your pre-existing health conditions in an emergency, but a MedicAlert membership is more than just an ID.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>As a lapsed member, your secure health record may be out of date. It&rsquo;s also important to check that the engraving on your existing ID is legible and accurate.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>MedicAlert 24/7 service provides emergency responders, health professionals and general practitioners with access to your past and present health information, allowing them to accurately manage your ongoing care and provide you with peace of mind.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>As a member, you&rsquo;re also entitled to unlimited membership cards that contain your health information and a range of member only benefits and offers.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Please note: If you choose not to renew your membership within 3 months from the lapsed date, MedicAlert reserve the right to remove your records and personal information from our database. This means that your ID will no longer be linked to your electronic health record and supported by the 24/7 emergency response service.</strong></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>If you want to re-order a product when you renew your membership, you can view your past purchases and re-order or review an ID. </p>\r\n<p><a class=&quot;btn btn-red&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 10px;&quot; href=&quot;/my-purchases&quot;>My purchases</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Quick Renew - Renew Your Membership in One Step | MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'2016-09-21 14:52:10','2018-03-06 05:46:50',NULL),(62,239,1,0,0,'My wish list',NULL,NULL,'my-wish-list',1,'<p>Add the item/s to your cart now to complete your purchase.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,2,1,NULL,99,'My wish list | MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'2016-09-25 16:28:32','2016-10-26 06:40:32',NULL),(63,114,1,0,0,'Cost',NULL,NULL,'cost',1,'<p>Your medical identification jewellery is backed by vital MedicAlert membership. It tells emergency services workers that you are protected by MedicAlert, and provides them with vital information about your conditions when seconds count. You become a member of the Foundation at the time of your first purchase of a medical bracelet or necklace.</p>','<h3>MedicAlert membership is just ==membership_fee== per year</h3>\r\n<p>For less than the