ers Area on the website.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Application</strong> means an application for Membership.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Business Hours</strong> means 9am to 5pm Monday to Friday (CST).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Delivery Address</strong> means the address specified by you during the customer registration process or listed in an Order for the delivery of products that we will supply to you under these Terms and Conditions.</li>\r\n<li><strong>GST</strong> has the meaning it has in the <em>A New Tax System (Goods and Services Tax) Act 1999</em> (Cth).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Life Member</strong> means a member who joined the Foundation before 1 January 1998.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Member Medical Information</strong> means all health information (as defined in the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em>(Cth)) held by the Foundation about you.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Member Personal Information</strong> means all personal information (as defined in the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth)) held by the Foundation about you.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Member </strong>means a person with Membership of the Foundation.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Membership </strong>means your membership of the Foundation, as either an Annual Member or Life Member.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Product</strong> means each good or service that is advertised as being available for supply by the Foundation from time to time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Version 5.3 | Date: 25 February 2016</p>\r\n</div>','<p>GIFT CERTIFICATE TERMS AND CONDITIONS - NEEDS TITLE</p>\r\n<h1>Acceptance of terms and conditions</h1>\r\n<p>By purchasing, redeeming or attempting to redeem a Gift Certificate, you accept and become bound by the terms and conditions below as varied from time to time. </p>\r\n<h1>Purchasing Gift Certificates</h1>\r\n<p>You may purchase Gift Certificates by completing all mandatory fields.</p>\r\n<p>We will send Gift Certificates electronically to the Recipient&rsquo;s Email Address immediately upon purchase, or at 9:00am Australian Eastern Standard Time on the date you select at the time of purchase. </p>\r\n<p>We will email to Your Email Address confirmation of your purchase and confirmation that the Gift Certificate has been sent to the Recipient.  These confirmations will be sent at the time of purchase and sending of the Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<p>Notwithstanding the above, we will not be responsible for any delay in sending a Gift Certificates or any delay in sending confirmation of purchase or sending of a Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<p>Please correctly complete all mandatory fields on purchase of a Gift Certificate as we will not be responsible for any lost or incorrect Gift Certificates due to incorrect or incomplete information being provided.</p>\r\n<h1>Pricing and payment</h1>\r\n<p>All prices for Gift Certificates are in Australian dollars and all payments must be made in Australian dollars.  We are not responsible for any losses associated with currency exchange or exchange rate fluctuations.</p>\r\n<p>Gift Certificates may only be purchased using an acceptable debit or credit card.  Debit and credit card details provided at the time of purchase are stored until the purchase has been processed.</p>\r\n<h1>How and when you can redeem a Gift Certificate</h1>\r\n<p>You may redeem a Gift Certificate by the purchase of goods or services from us through our website, over the phone or at our National Office.</p>\r\n<p>You will be required to provide the unique identification number printed on the Gift Certificate at the point of redemption.</p>\r\n<p>A Gift Certificate may only be redeemed by the purchase of goods and services up to the value specified on the Gift Certificate.  If you wish to make a purchase that exceeds that value, you must pay the excess using another method of payment.</p>\r\n<p>A Gift Certificate may only be redeemed in one transaction.  A Gift Certificate will not be debited, reissued or replaced with a new Gift Certificate with a lower value as a consequence of purchases that are below the value specified on the Gift Certificate.  </p>\r\n<p>Once your Gift Certificate is redeemed, it should be destroyed.</p>\r\n<h1>Reversal of redemption</h1>\r\n<p>The redemption of Gift Certificates may not be cancelled or reversed except with our approval which we may give or withhold at our discretion.  This does not affect your rights under the Australian Consumer Law or under our returns policy in respect of goods or services purchased on redemption of a Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<h1>No exchange</h1>\r\n<p>Gift Certificates cannot be exchanged or redeemed for cash.</p>\r\n<h1>Expiry of Gift Certificates</h1>\r\n<p>Gift Certificates will expire on the first anniversary of their date of issue if they are not redeemed in accordance with these terms and conditions.</p>\r\n<h1>Lost or stolen Gift Certificates</h1>\r\n<p>Gift Cards should be treated like cash.  Lost or stolen Gift Certificates will not be replaced or refunded.</p>\r\n<h1>Your responsibilities</h1>\r\n<p>You are responsible for the use and safety of your Gift Certificate.  We are not responsible for any transactions using your Gift Certificate except to the extent that there has been fraud or negligence by us or by any of our employees.</p>\r\n<h1>Disclaimer</h1>\r\n<p>To the extent permitted by law, we exclude all responsibility for any harm to any person or property or for any loss of profits or other indirect or consequential loss relating to the purchase, redemption or attempted redemption of Gift Certificates, including any delay in sending Gift Certificates.</p>\r\n<h1>Privacy</h1>\r\n<p>We collect personal information to provide and market our products and services.  That information may be disclosed to our contractors who assist us with these activities and to our affiliate in the United States of America, MedicAlert Foundation United States, Inc.  Our <span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;>Privacy Policy (need to anchor to privacy policy)</span> contains information about how an individual may access or correct information we hold about the individual, how complaints about a breach of privacy can be made to us and how such complaints will be dealt with.  If you do not consent to us using your personal information to market products and services, please email <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au.</a> <strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<h1>Contact us</h1>\r\n<p>Please do not hesitate to email <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a> about any queries, comments or requests for information you may have regarding Gift Certificates or these terms and conditions.</p>','<div id=&quot;service-communication&quot;>COMMUNICATION SERVICE GUARANTEE - ADD TITLE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>The Australia Medic Alert Foundation (AMAF) is committed to providing high quality services, and adopts the following service standards, guided by our core values of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Accountability</li>\r\n<li>Commitment</li>\r\n<li>Community</li>\r\n<li>Equity and Diversity</li>\r\n<li>Integrity</li>\r\n<li>WH&amp;S</li>\r\n<li>Innovation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>When you contact us</h1>\r\n<h2>Telephone enquiries</h2>\r\n<p>If you call us we will answer your calls promptly and courteously and aim to answer your queries on the spot.</p>\r\n<p>We recognise that you may have queries that are unique to your own specific</p>\r\n<p>circumstances or are complex. In these instances we may need to arrange a call back so that we can research the query sufficiently to ensure a specific and thorough response is given.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, if your query is not straight forward, please email us. We aim to provide you with a response within 3 business days for queries sent to <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a></p>\r\n<h2>Correspondence (letter or email)</h2>\r\n<p>We will acknowledge your correspondence within 24 hours of receipt (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply). We aim to give you a full response to general correspondence within 3 business days of receiving all of the required information. In some cases, we may request further information from you to ensure that we understand your reason for contact fully and to give you a full response.</p>\r\n<p>For more complex correspondence, the exact timing and content of our response will depend on each case and the request.</p>\r\n<h2>Social Media Channels</h2>\r\n<p>We will acknowledge your correspondence within 4 - 6 hours of receipt during</p>\r\n<p>business hours (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply). We aim to give you a full response to general correspondence within 3 business days of receiving all of the required information. In some cases, we may request further information from you to ensure that we understand your reason for contact fully and to give you a full response.</p>\r\n<p>For more complex correspondence, the exact timing and content of our response will depend on each case and the request.</p>\r\n<h2>AMAF membership application forms</h2>\r\n<p>When you lodge a form to become a member or update your details we aim to process the request within 3 business days of receipt of all of the required information.</p>\r\n<h1>When you provide us with feedback</h1>\r\n<h2>General</h2>\r\n<p>We take your feedback seriously. We will listen and work with you to reach a resolution where we can.</p>\r\n<p>If you provide feedback, we will act immediately where there is a serious risk to public trust and confidence and/or they relate to AMAF&rsquo;s compliance requirements.</p>\r\n<p>We aim to provide a substantive response to your feedback within 3 business days.</p>\r\n<h2>Product</h2>\r\n<p>All AMAF products offered to our members are supported by <u>Product Warranty Statement</u>.</p>\r\n<p>If you provide feedback about a product we will work with you to reach a resolution where we can within the warranty guidelines.</p>\r\n<p>We aim to address any product queries or concerns on the spot, but where the issue is unique or complex we may need to arrange a call back so that we can research the query sufficiently to ensure a specific and thorough response is given. In all cases, we aim to address the issue within 3 business days.</p>\r\n<h1>When you request information we hold</h1>\r\n<h2>General information requests</h2>\r\n<p>We aim to acknowledge all requests for access to information within 24 hours receipt (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply).</p>\r\n<p>We aim to provide a response to requests not falling under the Freedom of Information Act and Privacy Act within 14 business days.</p>\r\n<h2>Freedom of Information Act requests</h2>\r\n<p>We aim to respond to requests for information falling under the Freedom of Information Act within 30 calendar days (plus statutory extensions). Where third party consultation is required; we aim to provide you with a full response within 60 calendar days.</p>\r\n<h2>Privacy Act requests</h2>\r\n<p>If you raise an issue with us that falls under the Privacy Act, we aim to provide a response within 30 calendar days.</p>\r\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Terms and Conditions',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-04 15:37:14','2016-10-24 02:07:51','2016-10-24 12:37:51'),(108,10,1,0,0,'Terms and Conditions',NULL,NULL,'terms-and-conditions',1,'<div>\r\n<h3>TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF MEMBERSHIP</h3>\r\n<p><em>1. Introduction<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>1.1 By applying to become a Member you agree to be bound by these Conditions as varied from time to time.  Please read them carefully.</p>\r\n<p>1.2 We reserve the right to amend these Conditions at any time.</p>\r\n<p><em>2. Benefits of Membership<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>2.1 Upon becoming a Member, we will provide the following benefits to you:</p>\r\n<p>2.1.1 provision of a Medic Alert Identification Number;</p>\r\n<p>2.1.2 creation and maintenance of an electronic record of all your Health Information;</p>\r\n<p>2.1.3 secure web based access to your Health Information using any user name or password provided to you or generated in connection with your Membership;</p>\r\n<p>2.1.4 the right to purchase from us Personalised Medic Alert Products for your own personal use;</p>\r\n<p>2.1.5 through the 24/7 Medic Alert Emergency Response Service, disclosure of your Health Information to any professional emergency responders and Health Practitioners requesting such information in circumstances where they have quoted your Medic Alert Identification Number or other personal information which identifies you; and</p>\r\n<p>2.1.6 access to our newsletter and other Member publications.</p>\r\n<p>2.2 The above benefits will only be made available to you for so long as your Membership Fees are fully paid up.</p>\r\n<p><em>3. Applying for Membership<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>3.1 You may only apply for Membership:</p>\r\n<p>3.1.1 on your own behalf; or</p>\r\n<p>3.1.2 on behalf of any minor or adult person who is not capable of applying for Membership for him or herself and for whom you are acting as a Responsible Person.</p>\r\n<p>3.2 An application for Membership may be for annual or Membership for any other period we may permit.</p>\r\n<p>3.3 You may only apply for Membership by providing to us a completed Membership Application Form online through the Website or by post or other means of delivery acceptable to us.</p>\r\n<p>3.4 An application for Membership must be accompanied by payment of the relevant Membership Fee Application Fee (if any).</p>\r\n<p><em>4. Membership Fees<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>4.1 Membership Fees are inclusive of GST.</p>\r\n<p>4.2 Continuation of your annual and other periodic Membership is subject to payment of your annual or other periodic Membership Fee;</p>\r\n<p>4.3 You must pay your Membership Fees by the due date for payment.</p>\r\n<p>4.4 We will take reasonable steps to notify you of your Membership Fee falling due before the due date for payment.</p>\r\n<p><em>5. Your Information<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>5.1 We may collect your Personal Information (which includes Health Information) from you or from your Responsible Person, Health Practitioner or other agent nominated by you in connection with your Membership.</p>\r\n<p>5.2 We may collect your Health Information from any professional emergency responders and Health Practitioners attending you in the event of a medical emergency where such responders or practitioners have quoted your Medic Alert Identification Number or other personal information which identifies you.</p>\r\n<p>5.3 Your Personal Information must be accurate and complete.</p>\r\n<p>5.4 We may assist you with providing your Health Information to us however we will not be responsible for the provision of such information.</p>\r\n<p>5.5 If you have any doubts or concerns about the Health Information to be provided to us, we recommend that you consult your Health Practitioner who may assist you.</p>\r\n<p>5.6 We will not be responsible for any errors or omissions in your Personal Information.</p>\r\n<p>5.7 We may give you notice requiring you to update or confirm your Personal Information from time to time and you must comply with such notices.</p>\r\n<p>5.8 You must promptly advise us if your Personal Information changes.  You may do this by accessing your Personal Information on the Members Only Pages on the Website using any user name or password provided to you or generated in connection with your Membership.  Alternatively, you can advise us of these changes over the telephone, by email or by any other means acceptable to us.</p>\r\n<p>5.9 You are responsible for the safekeeping of any user name or password provided to you or generated in connection with your Membership.  We will not be responsible for any unauthorized use of such user name or passwords including in relation to unauthorized changes to your Health Information.</p>\r\n<p>5.10 We may disclose your Personal Information to any professional emergency responders or Health Practitioners attending you in the event of a medical emergency where such responders or practitioners have requested such information and have quoted your Medic Alert Identification Number or other personal information which identifies you.</p>\r\n<p>5.11 We will take reasonable steps to verify that any person representing themselves to us as:</p>\r\n<p>5.11.1 a professional emergency responder or Health Practitioner attending you in the event of a medical emergency; or</p>\r\n<p>5.11.2 your Responsible Person, Health Practitioner or other agent nominated by you in connection with your Membership, is such a person.</p>\r\n<p>5.12 We may disclose or otherwise deal with your Personal Information as permitted under our Privacy Policy and as permitted under the Privacy Act.</p>\r\n<p>5.13 You consent to our collection, holding, disclosure and other dealings with your Personal Information as permitted in these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>5.14 We will take reasonable steps to protect your Personal Information from misuse and loss and from unauthorised access, modification or disclosure.  We will store your Personal Information in access controlled premises, and electronic information on secure servers.  We will require all persons authorised to access such information directly from our servers to use logins and passwords to access such information.</p>\r\n<p>5.15 We require all persons to whom we disclose your Personal Information or whom may have access to your Personal Information in accordance with these Conditions to keep such information private and to protect such information from misuse and loss and from unauthorised access, modification or disclosure.</p>\r\n<p>5.16 Unless we are prevented to do so by the law, we will de-identify or securely destroy your Personal Information when no longer reasonably required by us in connection with your Membership.</p>\r\n<p>5.17 Notwithstanding the above security measures, we cannot give any absolute guarantee that your Personal Information will be available at all times and not subject to any misuse or loss, including misuse or loss from unauthorised access, modification or disclosure.  We will notify you as soon as we reasonably can if we become aware of any unauthorised access to or modification or disclosure of your Personal Information.</p>\r\n<p><em>6. Payments<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>6.1 You must pay your Membership Fees by payment method options offered by us at the time such payments are due.</p>\r\n<p>6.2 Any credit and debit card details provided in respect of any payment under these Conditions are stored until the payment process has been finalised. </p>\r\n<p>6.3 We reserve the right to charge a reasonable administration fee for issuing duplicate invoices, statements or other documents requested by you.</p>\r\n<p><em>7. Termination<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>7.1 We may terminate your Membership Benefits or your Membership without notice if:</p>\r\n<p>7.1.1 your Membership Fee is outstanding;</p>\r\n<p>7.1.2 you commit any breach of these Conditions;</p>\r\n<p>7.1.3 you abuse any Membership Benefit;</p>\r\n<p>7.1.4 you provide any misleading information or make any misrepresentations to us;</p>\r\n<p>7.1.5 you are otherwise dishonest or fraudulent in your dealings with us.</p>\r\n<p>7.2 We will not be responsible for any Liabilities or other consequence arising out of termination of your Membership Benefits or you Membership.</p>\r\n<p>7.3 We may only reinstate your Membership Benefits or Membership at our discretion and on any conditions we consider fit.</p>\r\n<p><em>8. Our Liability<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>8.1 Except to the extent permitted by the Australian Consumer Law, this clause does not limit our liability in respect of any Consumer Guarantees.</p>\r\n<p>8.2 Except where otherwise required by law (including the Australian Consumer Law):</p>\r\n<p>8.2.1 all guarantees, conditions, warranties or other terms which may be implied by law or otherwise in connection with these Conditions or your Membership Benefits and Membership are excluded;</p>\r\n<p>8.2.2 we are not liable in tort for any loss or damage suffered by you or by any other person;</p>\r\n<p>8.2.3 we do not accept responsibility for any Liabilities which you may incur in connection with these Conditions or your Membership Benefits and Membership and you release us from any Claim relating to such Liabilities;</p>\r\n<p>8.2.4 in no circumstances will we be responsible for any loss of profits or interruption to business or other indirect economic or other consequential loss suffered by you or any third party in connection with these Conditions or your Membership Benefits and Membership<em>;</em></p>\r\n<p>8.2.5 you indemnify us against all Liabilities which we may incur and release us from any Claim in connection with these Conditions or your Membership Benefits and Membership.</p>\r\n<em>9. Privacy<br /></em>\r\n<p>9.1 We are committed to protecting your privacy.  We collect Personal Information to provide and market our products and services and may disclose that information to our authorised staff, agents, contractors or service providers contractors with whom we have a contractual arrangement, in the course of them undertaking their legitimate duties in providing a given product or service.  We may also provide Personal Information to MedicAlert Foundation United States, Inc (based in the United States of America) and to other overseas recipients in accordance with our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot;>Privacy Policy</a>.</p>\r\n<p>9.2 If you do not provide us with any Personal Information we may request from you, we may not be able to provide you with our products and services or otherwise assist you.</p>\r\n<p>9.3 Our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot;>Privacy Policy</a> contains information about how you may access or correct Personal Information we hold about you, how you can complain about a breach of privacy and how we will deal with such complaints.</p>\r\n<p><em>10. Your Breach<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>You indemnify us against all Liabilities which we may incur in respect of your breach of these Conditions.</p>\r\n<em>11. Contact Us<br /></em>\r\n<p>Please email to us any queries, comments or requests for information you may have regarding these Conditions at enquiry@medicalert.org.au.</p>\r\n<p><em>12. Notices<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>12.1 We may give notices to you by email, post, text messages or by notices published on our Website.  You may give notices to us by email to [insert].</p>\r\n12.2 We will not be responsible for any delay in or failure to give you any notice referred to in these Conditions.<br />\r\n<p><em>13. General<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>13.1 Unless otherwise provided, we may in our discretion give (conditionally or unconditionally) or withhold any approval or consent under these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>13.2 You must not assign or otherwise deal with these Conditions or any right or obligation under these Conditions without our written consent.</p>\r\n<p>13.3 These Conditions cover the entire agreement and understanding between you and us with respect to your Membership and Membership Benefits and supersede any prior agreement or understanding.</p>\r\n<p>13.4 A waiver of a provision of or right under these Conditions by us must be in writing signed by us and is effective only to the extent set out in the written waiver.</p>\r\n<p>13.5 The failure, delay, relaxation or indulgence in exercising a power or right under these Conditions is not a waiver of that power or right.</p>\r\n<p>13.6 An exercise of a power or right under these Conditions does not preclude a further exercise of it or the exercise of another right or power.</p>\r\n<p>13.7 The validity and interpretation of these Conditions are governed by the laws of South Australia.  Any dispute in connection with these Conditions is s