 Soon after, Greg says he quit smoking, adopted a healthier lifestyle and joined MedicAlert on the advice of a long-time family friend.<br /> <br /> &ldquo;I always wear my stainless steel MedicAlert emblem around my neck, only taking it off when I go swimming in case I lose it,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;While my diabetes is quite stable, it gives me great peace of mind to know that it could be a lifesaver if I was in an accident.&rdquo;<br /> <br /> Greg&rsquo;s 87-year-old mother-in-law is also a MedicAlert member and he says they both renew their membership at the same time each year.<br /> <br /> &ldquo;MedicAlert is part of my wellbeing plan, together with regular check-ups with my specialist, looking after my health and taking time out to enjoy gardening or relaxing with our sons and friends,&rdquo; he says.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Greg Sutton',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-01 14:37:44','2016-10-01 05:09:47','2016-10-01 14:39:35'),(115,583,4,0,104,'Greg Sutton',NULL,NULL,'greg-sutton',0,'Onkaparinga Hills, SA, member since 2006','MedicAlert is part of my well-being plan, together with regular check-ups with my specialist, looking after my health and taking time out to enjoy gardening or relaxing with our sons and friends','<p>Finance broker, Greg Sutton, leads a very busy life that revolves around his business, family and friends, and love of sport.<br /> <br /> Proud father of four adult sons, including twins, Greg says MedicAlert helps him to &rsquo;live well&rsquo; with his diabetes.<br /> <br /> &ldquo;During my mid-thirties my wife, Judy, and others noticed that I seemed tired, irritable and just not myself&rdquo;, Greg says. <br /> <br /> &ldquo;A trip to the doctor revealed that I had type 2 diabetes, which unfortunately runs in my family. I think a combination of eating on the run between our sons&rsquo; sporting commitments, long working hours and a love of socialising with friends probably contributed to developing the condition&rdquo;.<br /> <br /> Soon after, Greg says he quit smoking, adopted a healthier lifestyle and joined MedicAlert on the advice of a long-time family friend.<br /> <br /> &ldquo;I always wear my stainless steel MedicAlert emblem around my neck, only taking it off when I go swimming in case I lose it,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;While my diabetes is quite stable, it gives me great peace of mind to know that it could be a lifesaver if I was in an accident.&rdquo;<br /> <br /> Greg&rsquo;s 87-year-old mother-in-law is also a MedicAlert member and he says they both renew their membership at the same time each year.<br /> <br /> &ldquo;MedicAlert is part of my wellbeing plan, together with regular check-ups with my specialist, looking after my health and taking time out to enjoy gardening or relaxing with our sons and friends,&rdquo; he says.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Greg Sutton',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/testimonials/greg_sutton.png',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-01 14:37:44','2016-10-10 00:07:10',NULL),(116,584,4,0,104,'Rebeka B',NULL,NULL,'rebeka-b',0,'Amaroo, ACT, member since 2010','We joined MedicAlert Foundation in December 2010 and Millie has worn her &lsquo;special bracelet&rsquo; every day since','<p>Busy mother of two, Rebeka, finds MedicAlert &lsquo;priceless&rsquo; in helping to manage her youngest daughter&rsquo;s multiple allergies.<br /> <br /> Millie was just three months&rsquo; old, when she first suffered baffling outbreaks of itchy, red, swollen spots on her body. The problem became steadily worse, resulting in many visits to her GP and local hospital. Finally, a paediatrician diagnosed mastocytosis &ndash; an abnormally high amount of mast cells in her body. Mast cells contain many natural chemicals including histamine. Heat, rubbing, certain foods and drugs can cause the mast cells to release these chemicals.<br /> <br /> Rebeka says she was initially shocked to learn of her daughter&rsquo;s condition and that she was also allergic to several common foods, including fish and nuts, and to penicillin.<br /> <br /> &lsquo;Even someone touching her after they&rsquo;d eaten a trigger food, would set off a nasty skin reaction,&rsquo; she says.<br /> <br /> &lsquo;We had to be so careful at playgroup, parties, in public places and at home to make sure Millie didn&rsquo;t pick up &lsquo;forbidden&rsquo; foods which caused sudden swelling, rashes and wheezing.<br /> <br /> &lsquo;We joined MedicAlert Foundation in December 2010 and Millie has worn her &lsquo;special bracelet&rsquo; every day since.&rsquo;<br /> <br /> Rebeka says she has real peace of mind knowing that paramedics or doctors can quickly get accurate information about Millie&rsquo;s condition and allergies, particularly as she gets older.<br /> <br /> &lsquo;Another advantage is that other parents have become my extra &lsquo;eyes&rsquo;. People often ask me why Millie wears her emblem, and are much more careful than before about giving her food or touching her after they&rsquo;ve eaten,&rsquo; she says.<br /> <br /> &lsquo;I feel so much more at ease knowing that Millie&rsquo;s MedicAlert bracelet is always there to protect her health.&rsquo;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Rebeka B',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-01 14:40:27','2016-10-01 05:11:51','2016-10-01 14:41:39'),(117,584,4,0,104,'Rebeka B',NULL,NULL,'rebeka-b',0,'Amaroo, ACT, member since 2010','We joined MedicAlert Foundation in December 2010 and Millie has worn her &lsquo;special bracelet&rsquo; every day since','<p>Busy mother of two, Rebeka, finds MedicAlert &lsquo;priceless&rsquo; in helping to manage her youngest daughter&rsquo;s multiple allergies.<br /> <br /> Millie was just three months&rsquo; old, when she first suffered baffling outbreaks of itchy, red, swollen spots on her body. The problem became steadily worse, resulting in many visits to her GP and loc