to also be a frustrated explorer and has wandered away from the family home on a couple of occasions.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;He isn&rsquo;t at the stage where he can tell you his name, home phone number or where he lives, so I looked around for a suitable identification option and it was clear that MedicAlert membership was the perfect solution,&rdquo; says Amanda.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Kane wears a bracelet 24/7 that has our contact details on it in case he goes missing again, and it clearly flags that he has a hearing condition.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>It was an investment that has already paid for itself, with the youngster recently wandering away from the family&rsquo;s nine acre property near Parkerville in Western Australia.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Previously, he hasn&rsquo;t gone too far, but the most recent incident saw him missing for more than ten minutes &ndash; which seems like a lifetime when you are a panicked mum,&rdquo; says Amanda.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;A lady passer-by came across Kane and used the contact details on the rear of his MedicAlert emblem to call and let us know he had been found safe and well, just as we were about to call the police to mount a search for him.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Every parent in a similar situation should invest in a MedicAlert membership for their children because it can save their life.&rdquo;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Amanda and Kane Searle',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-01 14:47:27','2016-10-01 05:18:22','2016-10-01 14:48:10'),(125,588,4,0,104,'Amanda and Kane Searle',NULL,NULL,'amanda-and-kane-searle',0,'Parkerville, WA, member since 2013','Kane wears a bracelet 24/7 that has our contact details on it in case he goes missing again, and it clearly flags that he has a hearing condition.','<p>With six children, Amanda Searle certainly knows a thing or two when it comes to raising little ones, so when her 18-month old son Kane wasn&rsquo;t developing in line with her experience, she knew something wasn&rsquo;t right.</p>\r\n<p>A trip to a hearing specialist confirmed that her instincts were right, with Kane diagnosed with Sensorineural hearing loss (SNHL) caused from an abnormality in the central auditory system.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Kane now has hearing aids, but because his condition went undetected for quite a while he has a fair amount of catching up to do to get him to the stage in his development where he needs to be,&rdquo; Amanda says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;He has always been a clever little boy, but what triggered my concern was that his speech hadn&rsquo;t progressed and he wasn&rsquo;t talking properly, so a hearing test done under sedation finally identified his condition.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Now that he has started to wear his hearing aid he is moving forward in leaps and bounds, which is great to see,&rdquo; she says.</p>\r\n<p>Adding to Amanda&rsquo;s challenges was the fact that Kane seems to also be a frustrated explorer and has wandered away from the family home on a couple of occasions.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;He isn&rsquo;t at the stage where he can tell you his name, home phone number or where he lives, so I looked around for a suitable identification option and it was clear that MedicAlert membership was the perfect solution,&rdquo; says Amanda.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Kane wears a bracelet 24/7 that has our contact details on it in case he goes missing again, and it clearly flags that he has a hearing condition.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>It was an investment that has already paid for itself, with the youngster recently wandering away from the family&rsquo;s nine acre property near Parkerville in Western Australia.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Previously, he hasn&rsquo;t gone too far, but the most recent incident saw him missing for more than ten minutes &ndash; which seems like a lifetime when you are a panicked mum,&rdquo; says Amanda.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;A lady passer-by came across Kane and used the contact details on the rear of his MedicAlert emblem to call and let us know he had been found safe and well, just as we were about to call the police to mount a search for him.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Every parent in a similar situation should invest in a MedicAlert membership for their children because it can save their life.&rdquo;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Amanda and Kane Searle',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/testimonials/amanda_and_kane_searle.png',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-01 14:47:27','2016-10-09 23:43:39',NULL),(126,589,4,0,104,'Kathy and Bonnie McAlinden',NULL,NULL,'kathy-and-bonnie-mcalinden',0,'Brisbane, QLD, member since 2006','I strongly recommend investing in a MedicAlert bracelet to all parents who have children with allergies &ndash; the financial outlay is minimal, and the peace of mind it offers is priceless.','<p>All parents want to provide the very best for their children, and when Kathy&rsquo;s baby girl Bonnie was diagnosed with life-threatening allergies, she knew that one of the best things she could give her daughter was a MedicAlert membership to help keep her safe.</p>\r\n<p>&quot;Her allergy was so sensitive that just being touched by someone, sitting on a chair, or coming in contact with even the smallest of dairy traces was enough to trigger a reaction and leave her with red hives,&rdquo; Kathy says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;We found through testing, that she also had allergies to egg and nuts, so when she was about 18 months old we decided to invest in a stainless steel MedicAlert bracelet and since then she has worn it every day regardless of what she has been doing.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Kathy says the distinctive emblem is easily spotted by others, and people often ask her now nine year old daughter about the reason she wears it.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I have seen Bonnie&rsquo;s gymnastic coaches look at her wrist, turn over the MedicAlert emblem and read it. It comforts me to know that they&rsquo;re now aware she has allergies and carries an Epi-pen in case she has a severe reaction,&rdquo; Kathy says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve also seen new teachers&#039; aides or relief teachers naturally go to check her bracelet and because her school doesn&rsquo;t allow children to wear jewellery, they quickly understand that it serves a much more important purpose beyond fashion,&rdquo; she says.</p>\r\n<p>Whether it is gymnastics, cheerleading, choir, or swimming lessons, the active Queensland youngster understands that wearing her MedicAlert bracelet is an important accessory. Kathy says she doesn&rsquo;t have to worry as much about the constant threat of an unexpected reaction.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;As Bonnie has grown, she has become increasingly exposed to different children and carers, and we have found that children in particular, are easy to educate about Bonnie&rsquo;s allergies, whereas adults have proven slightly harder to explain that a bad reaction could be life-threatening,&rdquo; Kathy says.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;It really was an easy decision to provide her with a MedicAlert bracelet because people are aware of what the emblem means and look for it. We did try other lesser-known options and they didn&rsquo;t last long and tended to blend in as more a fashion accessory. Whilst we have bought Bonnie a second MedicAlert bracelet as a back-up, it is still sitting untouched because her first bracelet is in perfect condition.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&quot;I strongly recommend investing in a MedicAlert bracelet to all parents who have children with allergies &ndash; the financial outlay is minimal, and the peace of mind it offers is priceless.&rdquo;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Kathy and Bonnie McAlinden',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-01 14:48:46','2016-10-01 05:19:38','2016-10-01 14:49:26'),(127,589,4,0,104,'Kathy and Bonnie McAlinden',NULL,NULL,'kathy-and-bonnie-mcalinden',0,'Brisbane, QLD, member since 2006','I strongly recommend investing in a MedicAlert bracelet to all parents who have children with aller