will throw at us every day, and that uncertainty means that becoming a MedicAlert member might one day save my life during a situation where I might have no control and cannot talk for myself,&rdquo; she said.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I know of incidents where people with von Willebrand disorder have tragically died because emergency crews didn&rsquo;t know about their condition until it was too late, and I want to make sure that doesn&rsquo;t happen to me or my family,&rdquo; said Fiona.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Fiona Smith',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/testimonials/fiona_smith.png',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-01 14:50:08','2016-10-10 00:06:50',NULL),(130,591,4,0,104,'Janet Sperou',NULL,NULL,'janet-sperou',0,'Golden Grove, SA, member since 1971','My husband and I are out most weekends and for me, MedicAlert membership is one of the cheapest forms of &lsquo;life insurance&rsquo; you can buy.','<p>&lsquo;My husband and I are out most weekends and for me, MedicAlert membership is one of the cheapest forms of &lsquo;life insurance&rsquo; you can buy&rsquo;, says Janet.</p>\r\n<p>Janet was just five years old when her Mum explained that her new Medic Alert bracelet would help her if she &lsquo;got sick&rsquo;. Janet had been diagnosed with aortic stenosis &ndash; an abnormal narrowing of the aortic valve, which restricts the flow of blood into the body&rsquo;s main artery. <br /> <br /> Janet recalls her parents being concerned that if she collapsed she may be too ill or distressed to properly explain her condition to ambulance officers.<br /> <br /> &lsquo;Luckily, I was one of MedicAlert Foundation&rsquo;s first members as my father worked for St John, who with Rotary, introduced the Foundation into Australia that year,&rsquo; she says. <br /> <br /> Surgeons replaced Janet&rsquo;s faulty heart valve with an artificial one when she was eight, which is why she always wears her emblem and keeps her Foundation membership current. <br /> <br /> &lsquo;While my prosthetic valve is working perfectly, it could fail or become infected. Taking warfarin to prevent blood clots could also cause serious problems if I have an accident or need emergency surgery&rsquo;, she explains.<br /> <br /> A St John volunteer through her teens and into her twenties, Janet remembers being trained to look for a Medic Alert emblem.<br /> <br /> &lsquo;I also told my two sons when they were young to mention my bracelet to ambulance officers if I collapsed.<br /> <br /> &lsquo;Luckily I never did, but I know that wearing a MedicAlert emblem helps to take the guesswork out in an emergency as it quickly &lsquo;tells&rsquo; paramedics the information they need to give the best possible treatment.&rsquo;<br /> <br /> A busy management professional and grandmother of five, Janet still finds time to volunteer, now helping to crew SA&rsquo;s iconic River Murray paddle steamers.<br /> <br /> &lsquo;It&rsquo;s easy to put things off, but if you have a health problem and are considering joining Medic Alert, do it today &ndash; it could be a decision that helps to save your life tomorrow.&rsquo;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Janet Sperou',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-01 14:51:20','2016-10-01 05:22:12','2016-10-01 14:52:00'),(131,591,4,0,104,'Janet Sperou',NULL,NULL,'janet-sperou',0,'Golden Grove, SA, member since 1971','My husband and I are out most weekends and for me, MedicAlert membership is one of the cheapest forms of &lsquo;life insurance&rsquo; you can buy.','<p>&lsquo;My husband and I are out most weekends and for me, MedicAlert membership is one of the cheapest forms of &lsquo;life insurance&rsquo; you can buy&rsquo;, says Janet.</p>\r\n<p>Janet was just five years old when her Mum explained that her new Medic Alert bracelet would help her if she &lsquo;got sick&rsquo;. Janet had been diagnosed with aortic stenosis &ndash; an abnormal narrowing of the aortic valve, which