n to any asthma action plan. A MedicAlert ID carries the internationally recognised MedicAlert emblem and is engraved with your personal medical information, membership number and a 24/7 hotline number for emergency service to call for more information. Should a medical emergency arise, emergency services and healthcare professionals can easily recognise that you&rsquo;re an asthma sufferer and respond accordingly. <br /><br />1 May 2012 is <a href=&quot;http://www.nationalasthma.org.au/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>World Asthma Day</a>, a day dedicated to improving asthma awareness and taking control of the disease. So if you are living with asthma, or know of someone who is, this month is the perfect time to consider how best to manage a condition that should not be allowed to hold you back.<br /><small><small><br /></small></small></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>[1] National Asthma Council Australia 2006, <em>Asthma Management Handbook 2006</em>. National Asthma Council Australia, Melbourne, Australia.</li>\r\n<li>[2] National Asthma Council Australia 2012, date accessed: 23 April 2012 <a href=&quot;http://www.nationalasthma.org.au/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>www.nationalasthma.org.au</a>.</li>\r\n<li>[3] Australian Centre for Asthma Monitoring 2011, <em>Asthma in Australia 2011</em>. Australian Institute of Health and Welfare, Canberra, Australia.</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'MedicAlert Foundation: helping people living with asthma take control',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2012-05-01','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-03 12:08:08','2016-10-10 05:23:53',NULL),(186,617,2,0,17,'Plan for a safe break',NULL,NULL,'plan-for-a-safe-break',0,'April is here already! All those New Year&rsquo;s celebrations feel like forever ago and the first hectic months of the year have well and truly taken their toll on personal energy reserves.','<p>April is here already! All those New Year&rsquo;s celebrations feel like forever ago and the first hectic months of the year have well and truly taken their toll on personal energy reserves. For many, April is the month in which we set aside a little time to enjoy an already well-earned break.<br /><br />Many of us jump at the chance to go on a trip, some prefer to devote their days to massages and retail therapy, while others believe there&rsquo;s nothing like a good dose of fishing to relax the soul.<br /><br />Whatever your plans are you need to consider the best ways to keep yourself, and your loved ones, safe over the break. Planning ahead will mean you get to enjoy yourself that much more.<br /><br />April is a particularly busy time for the Grey Nomads &ndash; the growing legion of 50+ travellers who begin to head north to escape the winter chills. Year after year, they take off to explore new destinations or head back to old favourites, enjoying all our wonderful, open country has to offer.<br /><br />It&rsquo;s also a great time for mums, dads and kids to reconnect without the busyness of everyday life getting in the way. After all the excitement of an Easter egg hunt, this time is usually packed full of fun day trips and new activities, or sometimes even a little escape to the family holiday home. <br /><br />If you&rsquo;re a grandparent, you no doubt relish the school holidays as a time to catch up with the grandkids without having to make an appointment. You&rsquo;ll take the children out, play games, cook; pretty much spoil them rotten. It can be tiring but you&rsquo;ll have it no other way.<br /><br />No matter what your upcoming plans are, being a MedicAlert member offers you complete peace of mind to get out and make the most of your free time. Your MedicAlert ID carries the internationally recognised MedicAlert emblem and is engraved with your personal medical information, membership number and a 24/7 hotline number. Should a medical emergency arise, emergency services and healthcare professionals can quickly and easily access your vital personal information, ensuring that you are treated effectively and efficiently. <br /><br /><em>MedicAlert membership: don&rsquo;t go without it.</em></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Plan for a safe break',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2012-04-01','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-03 12:13:04','2016-10-03 01:45:04','2016-10-03 12:14:51'),(187,617,2,0,17,'Plan for a safe break',NULL,NULL,'plan-for-a-safe-break',0,'April is here already! All those New Year&rsquo;s celebrations feel like forever ago and the first hectic months of the year have well and truly taken their toll on personal energy reserves.','<p>April is here already! All those New Year&rsquo;s celebrations feel like forever ago and the first hectic months of the year have well and truly taken their toll on personal energy reserves. For many, April is the month in which we set aside a little time to enjoy an already well-earned break.<br /><br />Many of us jump at the chance to go on a trip, some prefer to devote their days to massages and retail therapy, while others believe there&rsquo;s nothing like a good dose of fishing to relax the soul.<br /><br />Whatever your plans are you need to consider the best ways to keep yourself, and your loved ones, safe over the break. Planning ahead will mean you get to enjoy yourself that much more.<br /><br />April is a particularly busy time for the Grey Nomads &ndash; the growing legion of 50+ travellers who begin to head north to escape the winter chills. Year after year, they take off to explore new destinations or head back to old favourites, enjoying all our wonderful, open country has to offer.<br /><br />It&rsquo;s also a great time for mums, dads and kids to reconnect without the busyness of everyday life getting in the way. After all the excitement of an Easter egg hunt, this time is usually packed full of fun day trips and new activities, or sometimes even a little escape to the family holiday home. <br /><br />If you&rsquo;re a grandparent, you no doubt relish the school holidays as a time to catch up with the grandkids without having to make an appointment. You&rsquo;ll take the children out, play games, cook; pretty much spoil them rotten. It can be tiring but you&rsquo;ll have it no other way.<br /><br />No matter what your upcoming plans are, being a MedicAlert member offers you complete peace of mind to get out and make the most of your free time. Your MedicAlert ID carries the internationally recognised MedicAlert emblem and is engraved with your personal medical information, membership number and a 24/7 hotline number. Should a medical emergency arise, emergency services and healthcare professionals can quickly and easily access your vital personal information, ensuring that you are treated effectively and efficiently. <br /><br /><em>MedicAlert membership: don&rsquo;t go without it.</em></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Plan for a safe break',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2012-04-01','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-03 12:13:04','2016-10-10 05:23:01',NULL),(188,618,2,0,17,'MedicAlert Foundation is turning purple for Epilepsy Awareness Month!',NULL,NULL,'medicalert-foundation-is-turning-purple-for-epilepsy-awareness-month',0,'Nearly 400 people living with epilepsy took steps to improve their lives by becoming MedicAlert Foundation members in 2011.','<p>Nearly 400 people living with epilepsy took steps to improve their lives by becoming MedicAlert Foundation members in 2011.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation Chief Executive Officer, Sandra Turner, said that almost thirty percent of those new members were school-aged children 18 years and under.</p>\r\n<p>This month the Foundation wants to improve the lives of even more people living with epilepsy by showing their support for Epilepsy Awareness Month.</p>\r\n<p>Epilepsy is a neurological condition which affects the nervous system, resulting in recurring convulsive or non-convulsive seizures that can occur without warning.</p>\r\n<p>By wearing a MedicAlert emblem around the neck or on the wrist, members living with epilepsy have the best chance of having their medical condition identified quickly and accurately, often meaning more appropriate medical treatment sooner.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;As a MedicAlert Foundation member, people living with epilepsy can have comfort in knowing the MedicAlert emblem has been in Australia for over forty years and it is well-recognised and respected by emergency and healthcare personnel across the country,&rdquo; said Ms Turner.</p>\r\n<p>March is National Epilepsy Awareness Month and includes a variety of events, community activities and media campaigns to raise awareness and improve understanding of epilepsy, culminating in Purple Day on March 26<sup>th</sup>.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Purple Day is the chance for schools, businesses and community groups to show their support for epilepsy awareness by running purple themed events or wearing purple,&rdquo; said Graeme Shears, Chief Executive Officer of the Epilepsy Foundation of Victoria.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s also an opportunity for people to tell their stories, and help to raise awareness and reduce the stigma that still exists.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Medic Alert Foundation is showing their support on the day with their team wearing purple on March 26th.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'MedicAlert Foundation is turning purple for Epilepsy Awareness Month!',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2012-03-26','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-03 12:15:28','2016-10-10 06:43:12',NULL),(189,619,2,0,17,'Australians urged to ask and know their loved ones&#039; donation wishes',NULL,NULL,'australians-urged-to-ask-and-know-their-loved-ones-donation-wishes',0,'One organ or tissue donor can save or enhance the lives of ten or more people, and with this week being Donate Life Week, MedicAlert Foundation is supporting the campaign by encouraging all potential','<div id=&quot;description&quot; class=&quot;news-description&quot;>\r\n<p>One organ or tissue donor can save or enhance the lives of ten or more people, and with this week being Donate Life Week, MedicAlert Foundation is supporting the campaign by encouraging all potential donors to make their donation wishes known to their family.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation Chief Executive Officer, Sandra Turner, says close to 17 percent of the Foundation&rsquo;s current members have indicated their desire to be an organ donor, and some members join specifically to wear their emblem as an immediate alert of their wishes.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;A significant number of our members choose to be organ donors and many have their wishes recorded on their body-worn medical ID emblem for easy recognition, as well as storing the information on our database,&rdquo; said Ms Turner.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Wearing an engraved MedicAlert emblem provides an immediate and effective way to inform emergency services personnel of a member&rsquo;s donation decision.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;What is most important however is that once you have made a donation decision that you discuss it with your family and register with the Australian Organ Donor Registry,&rdquo; she said.</p>\r\n<p>Dr Jonathan Gillis, National Medical Director of the Organ and Tissue Authority says many Australians are prepared to be organ and tissue donors however the family consent rate is less than 60%.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;In 2011, 1001 Australians and their families benefited from the legacy of 337 of their fellow Australians who last year became organ donors,&rdquo; said Dr Gillis.</p>\r\n<p>He reaffirms the importance of people advising their loved ones of their desire to donate because in Australia the family will always be asked to confirm the donation wishes of the deceased before donation or transplantation can proceed.</p>\r\n<p>By talking to their families, registering with the Australian Organ Donor Registry and wearing an engraved MedicAlert emblem outlining their wishes, Australians can help save more lives.</p>\r\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Australians urged to ask and know their loved ones&#039; donation wishes',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2012-02-22','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-03 12:17:23','2016-10-10 05:17:49',NULL),(190,620,2,0,17,'MedicAlert Foundation supports Donate Life Week 19-26 February',NULL,NULL,'medicalert-foundation-supports-donate-life-week-19-26-february',0,'Did you know that one organ and tissue donor can save or enhance the lives of 10 or more people? You can make a difference; make your donation wishes known now.','<p>Did you know that one organ and tissue donor can save or enhance the lives of 10 or more people? You can make a difference; make your donation wishes known now&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>You know the importance of wearing a MedicAlert emblem to let emergency staff know your medical condition(s). But did you know that MedicAlert Foundation can also advise of your wishes regarding organ and tissue donation at the most critical time? <br /> <br /> Whether you choose to communicate your donation wishes via your bracelet, necklace or just on your membership card, MedicAlert provides an immediate and effective way to inform emergency services personnel of your decision to save and improve lives. But first, you must register your donation decision on the <a href=&quot;http://www.medicareaustralia.gov.au/public/services/aodr/index.jsp&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Australian Organ Donor Register</a> and, most importantly, you must discuss your donation decision with your family. <br /> <br /> &ldquo;In 2011, 1001 Australians and their families benefited from the legacy of 337 of their fellow Australians who last year became organ donors,&rdquo; said Dr Jonathan Gillis, National Medical Director of the Organ and Tissue Authority. However, the Authority emphasises that many more people could have been helped if the families of willing donors knew of their loved ones&rsquo; desire to donate. <br /> <br /> You see, in Australia the family is always asked to confirm the donation wishes of the deceased before donation or transplantation can proceed. While many Australians are prepared to be organ and tissue donors, the family consent rate is less than 60%. <br /> <br /> DonateLife Week, held this year between 19&ndash;26 February, is part of the Australian Government&rsquo;s national awareness campaign to increase family discussion about donation wishes. Since the reform began just over two years ago, Australia has achieved the highest ever number of donors and transplant recipients. <br /> <br /> During DonateLife Week, all Australians will be encouraged to ask and know their loved ones&rsquo; donation wishes . Sure, it&rsquo;s a difficult topic to bring up, but it&rsquo;s important that you do so. <br /> <br /> For some great suggestions on how to start a conversation about organ and tissue donation or to find out more about becoming a donor yourself, visit <a href=&quot;http://www.donatelife.gov.au%20&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>donatelife.gov.au.</a><br /> <br /> This month MedicAlert Foundation is encouraging you to communicate your wishes with your family first and then with us. It&rsquo;s the best way you can make a difference.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'MedicAlert Foundation supports Donate Life Week 19-26 February',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2012-02-07','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-03 12:18:53','2016-10-10 05:24:21',NULL),(191,621,2,0,17,'New fun options for young children and teenagers',NULL,NULL,'new-fun-options-for-young-children-and-teenagers',0,'Just in time for the start of another busy year, we&rsquo;ve expanded our range of sports bands designed specially to suit the needs of younger MedicAlert members.','<div id=&quot;description&quot; class=&quot;news-description&quot;>\r\n<h4>Just in time for the start of another busy year, we&rsquo;ve expanded our range of sports bands designed specially to suit the needs of younger MedicAlert members.</h4>\r\n<p>Practical and fun, four new designs - cars, green and pink flowers and music - join our already popular owls and fun mix options. <br /> <br /> Featuring a durable, non-allergenic stainless steel emblem, these comfortable, washable nylon bands are easily adjusted with a Velcro closure. <br /> <br /> Sports bands are ideal for children with metal allergies and are made tough to withstand the rigours of playing sport or just the rough and tumble of everyday play. <br /> <br /> They are available with a small, standard or large emblem &ndash; all proudly Australian-made using 304 grade stainless steel. <br /> <br /> As with all of our high quality products, laser engraving of each emblem is free and customised to meet the wearer&rsquo;s individual needs. <br /> <br /> This range is priced at an affordable $55 for new members and $40 for existing members. <br /> <br /> More information about the full range of sports bands, or to order, <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au/Products/Bracelets/Stainless_Steel1&quot;>click here</a>. <INSERT NEW LINK TO SHOP></p>\r\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'New fun options for young children and teenagers',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2012-01-12','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-03 12:30:13','2016-10-10 05:23:11',NULL),(192,622,2,0,17,'If your 2012 new year&#039;s resolution is to live life to the full, don&#039;t risk it without a MedicAlert emblem',NULL,NULL,'if-your-2012-new-years-resolution-is-to-live-life-to-the-full-dont-risk-it-without-a-medicalert-emblem',0,'Just because you may have an underlying medical condition, it&rsquo;s no reason to hold back on experiencing new adventures in life.','<p>Just because you may have an underlying <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au/Membership/Who_needs_MedicAlert__membership&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>medical condition</a>, it&rsquo;s no reason to hold back on experiencing new adventures in life.</p>\r\n<p>Why not push the boundaries of what you thought was possible?</p>\r\n<p>With a <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/News/News_and_Media_Releases/Membership/How_to_Join&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>MedicAlert membership</a> you can have more confidence to tackle any of life&rsquo;s adventures with the assurance that if something unforeseen happens, your medical ID can alert emergency staff of your medical condition(s) in the event that you cannot effectively communicate yourself. Your medical ID is personally engraved with your membership number, key medical information and 24/7 emergency hotline number for emergency services and healthcare professionals to access.</p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/News/News_and_Media_Releases/Membership/How_to_Join&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Membership</a> is suitable for any <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/News/News_and_Media_Releases/Membership/Who_needs_MedicAlert__membership&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>medical condition</a> including diabetes, asthma, allergies, heart problems, epilepsy, transplants, special medication needs or simply for emergency identification.</p>\r\n<p>So don&rsquo;t just talk about maybe one day doing all those exciting things you&rsquo;ve always wanted to.</p>\r\n<p>In 2012 the world is yours and you should feel free to do what makes you happy.</p>\r\n<p>Adventure beckons and with a <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/News/News_and_Media_Releases/Products&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>MedicAlert emblem</a> you can feel safe in the knowledge that you have our support.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is your new year&#039;s resolution?</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;http://www.facebook.com/AustraliaMedicAlertFoundation&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Post your comments on Facebook</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;http://medicalertaus.blogspot.com/2012/01/if-your-2012-new-years-resolution-is-to.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Post your comments on our Blog</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'if your 2012 new year&#039;s resolution is to live life to the full, don&#039;t risk it without a MedicAlert emblem',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2012-01-11','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-03 13:01:11','2016-10-10 05:19:51',NULL),(193,624,2,0,17,'Add some sparkle to your day with our new crystal bracelet collection',NULL,NULL,'add-some-sparkle-to-your-day-with-our-new-crystal-bracelet-collection',0,'Our handcrafted crystal bracelet collection made with SWAROVSKI ELEMENTS, is the latest stylish addition to our versatile range of medical ID jewellery.','<div id=&quot;description&quot; class=&quot;news-description&quot;>\r\n<h4>Our handcrafted crystal bracelet collection made with SWAROVSKI ELEMENTS, is the latest stylish addition to our versatile range of medical ID jewellery.</h4>\r\n<p>Our handcrafted crystal bracelet collection made with SWAROVSKI ELEMENTS, is the latest stylish addition to our versatile range of medical ID jewellery. <br /> <br /> The bracelets come in three sparkling sterling silver options; blush, spectrum blue and midnight. Each features Cartier-style clasps, making it simple for members to quickly change the look of their MedicAlert ID to suit any outfit or occasion. <br /> <br /> They are available in various lengths, with a small, standard or large sterling silver emblem &ndash; all of which are proudly Australian-made. <br /> <br /> As with all of our high quality products, laser engraving of each emblem is free and customised to the wearer&rsq