nd healthcare professionals to ensure they routinely check for medical identification and understand how it supports life-saving treatment when seconds can make all the difference.</p>\r\n<p>As part of its 40th anniversary celebrations the Foundation has launched a new website (www.medicalert.org.au) and is hosting a small celebration for invited guests in Adelaide on the evening of Monday 22 August.</p>\r\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Australian medical icon fit at 40',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2011-08-19','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-03 13:20:37','2016-10-10 05:17:23',NULL),(197,626,2,0,17,'MedicAlert puts parents in charge of their children&rsquo;s health over the holidays',NULL,NULL,'medicalert-puts-parents-in-charge-of-their-childrenandrsquos-health-over-the-holidays',0,'School holidays can be an anxious time for the parents of children with life-threatening or ongoing health conditions, particularly when the child is away from familiar home or school environments and','<div id=&quot;description&quot; class=&quot;news-description&quot;>\r\n<p>School holidays can be an anxious time for the parents of children with life-threatening or ongoing health conditions, particularly when the child is away from familiar home or school environments and support.</p>\r\n<p>Australia Medic Alert Foundation chief executive officer, Ms Sandra Turner, says that parents can ensure their children get the right help in an emergency, by &lsquo;speaking for them&rsquo; through with a MedicAlert emblem.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;A MedicAlert emblem worn on the wrist or around the neck can ensure emergency and medical personnel always have the right information about a child&rsquo;s underlying medical conditions available quickly and can help to provide the most effective treatment.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Statistics show that up to five per cent of children in Australia have a food allergy - most often to peanuts - by school age, one in nine school-aged children has asthma and about one in 700 children has diabetes.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;In 2010, almost 20 per cent of the Foundation&rsquo;s new members were children aged 18 years or less &ndash; a trend also seen in the first half of 2011.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;The MedicAlert emblem gives parents the chance to &lsquo;speak up&rsquo; for their child&rsquo;s specific health needs even when they are not with them,&rdquo; said Ms Turner.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;The personally engraved emblem identifies the child has a specific health condition and using the MedicAlert emblem as a &lsquo;break glass&rsquo; device, emergency personnel can access extra medical and personal information over the phone, so the best treatment can be implemented quickly,&rdquo; said Ms Turner.</p>\r\n<p>The genuine MedicAlert emblem is widely recognised and trusted by emergency healthcare professionals and paramedics are trained to look on the wrist and around the neck for medical identification.</p>\r\n<p>Leading national health awareness and support organisations like Anaphylaxis Australia also recommend that children and adults at risk of anaphylaxis &ndash; the most severe form of allergic reaction &ndash; wear a MedicAlert emblem.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Time and time again our member parents report real benefits in using MedicAlert&rsquo;s 24/7 service to protect their small children,&rdquo; said Ms Turner.</p>\r\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'MedicAlert puts parents in charge of their children&rsquo;s health over the holidays',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2011-07-01','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-03 13:23:19','2016-10-03 02:55:06','2016-10-03 13:24:52'),(198,626,2,0,17,'MedicAlert puts parents in charge of their children&rsquo;s health over the holidays',NULL,NULL,'medicalert-puts-parents-in-charge-of-their-childrenandrsquos-health-over-the-holidays',0,'School holidays can be an anxious time for the parents of children 