y purchase of Products affected by such error.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.4 We will provide you with a tax invoice with the total price for the Products, including credits applied and any other fees at or prior to delivery of the Products.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.5 On placement of an Order, you must select your payment method from the payment options offered by us at the time of Order.  Unless we otherwise agree, payment must be made by the selected payment method.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.6 Any credit and debit card details provided in connection with an Order are stored until the Order process has been finalised. </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.7 We reserve the right to charge a reasonable administration fee for issuing duplicate invoices, statements or other documents requested by you.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>7. Cancellations</em>\r\n<p>7.1 Subject to clause 5.2, you may not cancel a Contract at any time except with our consent.</p>\r\n<p>7.2 In the event that you cancel a Contract otherwise than under clause 5.2, you must indemnify us against all Liabilities we incur in respect of such cancellation including in respect of Consequential Loss.</p>\r\n<p>7.3 In the event you cancel a Contract under clause 5.2, we will refund to you any sums paid in respect of the Products.  We will not have any other liability in respect of such cancellation.</p>\r\n<p>7.4 We may cancel any Contract any time before Products are delivered by giving notice to you.  On giving such notice, we will refund to you any sums paid in respect of the Products.  We will not have any other liability in respect of such cancellation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>8. Personalised Medic Alert Products</em></p>\r\n<p>8.1 You may not re-supply any Personalised Medic Alert Products purchased otherwise than to any person for whom you have Ordered or purchased the Products acting as Responsible Person.</p>\r\n<p>8.2 We will not be responsible for any Personalised Medic Alert Products resupplied otherwise than as permitted under these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>8.3 We will not make any changes to any Personalised Medic Alert Products resupplied otherwise than as permitted under these Conditions.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>9. Credits and Refunds</em></p>\r\n<p>9.1 You can make a Claim for a refund or credit for Products delivered to you if:</p>\r\n<p>9.1.1 the Products do not correspond to the Order;</p>\r\n<p>9.1.2 the Products invoiced are not the Products delivered; or</p>\r\n<p>9.1.3 the Products are defective under the terms of any warranty against manufacturing defects in material or workmanship we may provide in respect of the Product at the time of placement of your Order.</p>\r\n<p>9.2 Email <a href=&quot;emailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a> to lodge your Claim.  We will assess your Claim and if accepted, we will provide you with a credit or refund at our discretion.  We may need to inspect the Products to assess your Claim so you are required to keep the Products until we notify you that they may be discarded.</p>\r\n<p>9.3 Credit accepted for the value of any Products under this clause will be applied to your next Order as long as the Order is for a value of at least the amount of credit accepted.  This credit will lapse after 12 months.</p>\r\n<p><em>10. Australian Consumer Law</em></p>\r\n<p>10.1 Our Products come with guarantees that cannot be excluded under the Australian Consumer Law.  You are entitled to a replacement or refund for a major failure and compensation for any other reasonably foreseeable loss or damage.  You are also entitled to have the Products repaired or replaced if the Products fail to be of acceptable quality and the failure does not amount to a major failure.</p>\r\n<p>10.2 Where the Contract under which you purchase the Products is a Consumer Contract (ie where you are a Consumer):</p>\r\n<p>10.2.1 the Products are supplied subject to the Consumer Guarantees; and</p>\r\n<p>10.2.2 you may only exercise any right or remedy for breach of a Consumer Guarantee strictly in accordance with your rights and responsibilities under the Australian Consumer Law.</p>\r\n<p><em>11. Our Liability</em></p>\r\n<p>11.1 Except to the extent permitted by the Australian Consumer Law, this clause does not limit our liability in respect of any Consumer Guarantees.</p>\r\n<p>11.2 None of the Implied Terms apply to any Contract except to the extent that they cannot be lawfully excluded.</p>\r\n<p>11.3 We are not liable in tort for any loss or damage suffered by you or by any other person.</p>\r\n<p>11.4 In no circumstances whatsoever shall we be liable to you or to any other person arising from the Products following delivery being:</p>\r\n<p>11.4.1 stored, handled, used or consumed contrary to any directions or recommendations made by us or the manufacturer of the Products from time to time;</p>\r\n<p>11.4.2 altered, modified, co-mingled or combined with any other products or ingredients otherwise than in accordance with any directions or recommendations made by us or the manufacturer of the Products from time to time;</p>\r\n<p>11.4.3 otherwise subject to inappropriate storage or handling, contamination, misuse, neglect, negligence or damage; or</p>\r\n<p>11.4.4 used or consumed after any defect in the Products becomes reasonably apparent.</p>\r\n<p>11.5 In no circumstance whatsoever shall we be liable to you or to any third party for any Consequential Loss arising out of the late delivery of Products or any failure to perform or observe our obligations under any Contract or Implied Terms and you will keep us fully indemnified against all Liabilities arising from any Claim made against us by a third party for Consequential Loss.</p>\r\n<p><em>12. Privacy</em></p>\r\n<p>12.1 We are committed to protecting your privacy.  We collect Personal Information to provide and market our products and services and may disclose that information to our authorised staff, agents, contractors or service providers contractors with whom we have a contractual arrangement, in the course of them undertaking their legitimate duties in providing a given product or service.  We may also provide Personal Information to MedicAlert Foundation United States, Inc (based in the United States of America) and to other overseas recipients in accordance with our Privacy Policy.</p>\r\n<p>12.2 If you do not provide us with any Personal Information we may request from you, we may not be able to provide you with our products and services or otherwise assist you.</p>\r\n<p>12.3 Our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot;>Privacy Policy</a> contains information about how you may access or correct information we hold about you, how you can complain about a breach of privacy and how we will deal with such complaints.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>13. Your Breach</em></p>\r\n<p>13.1 You indemnify us against all Liabilities which we may incur in respect of your breach of these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>13.2 Any breach or threatened breach of these Conditions entitles us to apply for and obtain injunctive relief in any court of competent jurisdiction in addition to all other available remedies.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>14. Contact Us</em></p>\r\n<p>Please email to us any queries, comments or requests for information you may have regarding these Conditions at <a href=&quot;emailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>15. Notices</em></p>\r\n<p>15.1 We may give notices to you by email, post or by notices published on our Website.  You may give notices to us by email to <a href=&quot;emailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enqui