ender;</p>\r\n<p>13.4 a reference to a party includes its employees, officers, contractors, executors, administrators, successors and permitted agents and assigns;</p>\r\n<p>13.5 a reference to a person includes a partnership, corporation, association, government body and any other entity;</p>\r\n<p>13.6 a reference to legislation includes any amendment to it, any legislation substituted for it, and any subordinate legislation made under it;</p>\r\n<p>13.7 a provision is not to be construed against us only because we prepared it;</p>\r\n<p>13.8 an unenforceable provision or part of a provision may be severed, and the remainder of these Conditions continues in force, unless this would materially change the intended effect of these Conditions;</p>\r\n<p>13.9 the meaning of general words is not limited by specific examples introduced by &lsquo;including&rsquo;, &lsquo;for example&rsquo; or similar expressions.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Version 6.0 | Date: 31 October 2016</p>\r\n</div>','<div id=&quot;gift-certificates&quot; class=&quot;text-left&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;h1&quot; style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>GIFT CERTIFICATE TERMS AND CONDITIONS</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;h1&quot; style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Acceptance of terms and conditions</div>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>By purchasing, redeeming or attempting to redeem a Gift Certificate, you accept and become bound by the terms and conditions below as varied from time to time.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Purchasing Gift Certificates</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>You may purchase Gift Certificates by completing all mandatory fields.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>We will send Gift Certificates electronically to the Recipient&rsquo;s Email Address immediately upon purchase, or at 9:00am Australian Eastern Standard Time on the date you select at the time of purchase.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>We will email to Your Email Address confirmation of your purchase and confirmation that the Gift Certificate has been sent to the Recipient. These confirmations will be sent at the time of purchase and sending of the Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Notwithstanding the above, we will not be responsible for any delay in sending a Gift Certificates or any delay in sending confirmation of purchase or sending of a Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Please correctly complete all mandatory fields on purchase of a Gift Certificate as we will not be responsible for any lost or incorrect Gift Certificates due to incorrect or incomplete information being provided.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Pricing and payment</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>All prices for Gift Certificates are in Australian dollars and all payments must be made in Australian dollars. We are not responsible for any losses associated with currency exchange or exchange rate fluctuations.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Gift Certificates may only be purchased using an acceptable debit or credit card. Debit and credit card details provided at the time of purchase are stored until the purchase has been processed.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>How and when you can redeem a Gift Certificate</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>You may redeem a Gift Certificate by the purchase of goods or services from us through our website, over the phone or at our National Office.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>You will be required to provide the unique identification number printed on the Gift Certificate at the point of redemption.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>A Gift Certificate may only be redeemed by the purchase of goods and services up to the value specified on the Gift Certificate. If you wish to make a purchase that exceeds that value, you must pay the excess using another method of payment.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>A Gift Certificate may only be redeemed in one transaction. A Gift Certificate will not be debited, reissued or replaced with a new Gift Certificate with a lower value as a consequence of purchases that are below the value specified on the Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Once your Gift Certificate is redeemed, it should be destroyed.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Reversal of redemption</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>The redemption of Gift Certificates may not be cancelled or reversed except with our approval which we may give or withhold at our discretion. This does not affect your rights under the Australian Consumer Law or under our returns policy in respect of goods or services purchased on redemption of a Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>No exchange</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Gift Certificates cannot be exchanged or redeemed for cash.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Expiry of Gift Certificates</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Gift Certificates will expire on the first anniversary of their date of issue if they are not redeemed in accordance with these terms and conditions.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Lost or stolen Gift Certificates</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Gift Cards should be treated like cash. Lost or stolen Gift Certificates will not be replaced or refunded.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Your responsibilities</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>You are responsible for the use and safety of your Gift Certificate. We are not responsible for any transactions using your Gift Certificate except to the extent that there has been fraud or negligence by us or by any of our employees.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Disclaimer</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>To the extent permitted by law, we exclude all responsibility for any harm to any person or property or for any loss of profits or other indirect or consequential loss relating to the purchase, redemption or attempted redemption of Gift Certificates, including any delay in sending Gift Certificates.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Privacy</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>We collect personal information to provide and market our products and services. That information may be disclosed to our contractors who assist us with these activities and to our affiliate in the United States of America, MedicAlert Foundation United States, Inc. Our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot;>privacy policy</a> contains information about how an individual may access or correct information we hold about the individual, how complaints about a breach of privacy can be made to us and how such complaints will be dealt with. If you do not consent to us using your personal information to market products and services, please email <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au.</a> <strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Contact us</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Please do not hesitate to email <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a> about any queries, comments or requests for information you may have regarding Gift Certificates or these terms and conditions.</p>\r\n</div>','<div id=&quot;service-communication&quot; class=&quot;text-left&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;h1&quot;>COMMUNICATION SERVICE GUARANTEE</div>\r\n<p>The Australia Medic Alert Foundation (AMAF) is committed to providing high quality services, and adopts the following service standards, guided by our core values of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Accountability</li>\r\n<li>Commitment</li>\r\n<li>Community</li>\r\n<li>Equity and Diversity</li>\r\n<li>Integrity</li>\r\n<li>WH&amp;S</li>\r\n<li>Innovation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>When you contact us</h1>\r\n<h2>Telephone enquiries</h2>\r\n<p>If you call us we will answer your calls promptly and courteously and aim to answer your queries on the spot.</p>\r\n<p>We recognise that you may have queries that are unique to your own specific</p>\r\n<p>circumstances or are complex. In these instances we may need to arrange a call back so that we can research the query sufficiently to ensure a specific and thorough response is given.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, if your query is not straight forward, please email us. We aim to provide you with a response within 3 business days for queries sent to <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a></p>\r\n<h2>Correspondence (letter or email)</h2>\r\n<p>We will acknowledge your correspondence within 24 hours of receipt (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply). We aim to give you a full response to general correspondence within 3 business days of receiving all of the required information. In some cases, we may request further information from you to ensure that we understand your reason for contact fully and to give you a full response.</p>\r\n<p>For more complex correspondence, the exact timing and content of our response will depend on each case and the request.</p>\r\n<h2>Social Media Channels</h2>\r\n<p>We will acknowledge your correspondence within 4 - 6 hours of receipt during</p>\r\n<p>business hours (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply). We aim to give you a full response to general correspondence within 3 business days of receiving all of the required information. In some cases, we may request further information from you to ensure that we understand your reason for contact fully and to give you a full response.</p>\r\n<p>For more complex correspondence, the exact timing and content of our response will depend on each case and the request.</p>\r\n<h2>AMAF membership application forms</h2>\r\n<p>When you lodge a form to become a member or update your details we aim to process the request within 3 business days of receipt of all of the required information.</p>\r\n<h1>When you provide us with feedback</h1>\r\n<h2>General</h2>\r\n<p>We take your feedback seriously. We will listen and work with you to reach a resolution where we can.</p>\r\n<p>If you provide feedback, we will act immediately where there is a serious risk to public trust and confidence and/or they relate to AMAF&rsquo;s compliance requirements.</p>\r\n<p>We aim to provide a substantive response to your feedback within 3 business days.</p>\r\n<h2>Product</h2>\r\n<p id=&quot;product_warranty&quot;>All AMAF products offered to our members are supported by <a href=&quot;/uploads/documents/product_warranty_statement_v1.1_a4_jan14_copy1.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Product Warranty Statement</a>.</p>\r\n<p>If you provide feedback about a product we will work with you to reach a resolution where we can within the warranty guidelines.</p>\r\n<p>We aim to address any product queries or concerns on the spot, but where the issue is unique or complex we may need to arrange a call back so that we can research the query sufficiently to ensure a specific and thorough response is given. In all cases, we aim to address the issue within 3 business days.</p>\r\n<h1>When you request information we hold</h1>\r\n<h2>General information requests</h2>\r\n<p>We aim to acknowledge all requests for access to information within 24 hours receipt (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply).</p>\r\n<p>We aim to provide a response to requests not falling under the Freedom of Information Act and Privacy Act within 14 business days.</p>\r\n<h2>Freedom of Information Act requests</h2>\r\n<p>We aim to respond to requests for information falling under the Freedom of Information Act within 30 calendar days (plus statutory extensions). Where third party consultation is required; we aim to provide you with a full response within 60 calendar days.</p>\r\n<h2>Privacy Act requests</h2>\r\n<p>If you raise an issue with us that falls under the Privacy Act, we aim to provide a response within 30 calendar days.</p>\r\n</div>','<h1>DIRECT DEBIT REQUEST (DDR)</h1>\r\n<h2>Australia Medic Alert Foundation (455996)</h2>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>By agreeing to the Terms and Conditions of Auto Renewal via Direct Debit you authorise Australia Medic Alert Foundation (455996) to arrange, through its own financial institution,</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>a debit to your nominated account any amount Australia Medic Alert Foundation (455996), has deemed payable by you. This debit or charge will be made through the Bulk Electronic Clearing System (BECS) from your account held at the financial institution you have nominated and will be subject to the terms and conditions of the Customer Direct Debit Request (DDR) Service Agreement.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Or</p>\r\n<ol start=&quot;2&quot;>\r\n<li>to arrange for funds to be debited from your nominated credit card according to the schedule specified below and Customer Direct Debit Request (DDR) Service Agreement.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Schedule</p>\r\n<p><strong>Date of First Payment:</strong> Payment will coincide with your current Annual Renewal schedule.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Frequency:</strong>                         Once per year</p>\r\n<p><strong>Payment Amount:</strong>           ==membership_fee==.00 (incl. GST) for each debit</p>\r\n<p><strong>Number of Payments:</strong>   Continue until further notice</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>If the scheduled date is not a banking day, the debit will take place on the next banking day.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>Customer Direct Debit Request (DDR) Service Agreement</strong></p>\r\n<p> This is your Direct Debt Service Agreement with Australia Medic Alert Foundation (455996) 31 140 801 427. It explains what your obligations are when undertaking Direct Debt arrangement with us. It also details what your obligations are to us as your Direct Debt provider.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Please keep this agreement for future reference. It forms part of the terms and conditions of your Direct Debit Request (DDR) and should be read in conjunction with your DDR authorisation.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h4>How to Contact Us</h4>\r\n<p><strong>Enquiries </strong></p>\r\n<p>You can contact us directly or alternatively contact your financial institution. These should be made at least 7 working days prior to the next scheduled drawing date. You may contact us as follows:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Phone:                 1800 88 22 22</p>\r\n<p>Email:    <a href=&quot;mailto:ddenquiries@medicalert.org.au&quot;>ddenquiries@medicalert.org.au</a></p>\r\n<p>Mail:      GPO Box 99 63</p>\r\n<p>               ADELAIDE SA 5001</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>All communication addressed to us should include your Membership Number.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h4>Definitions</h4>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Account</em></strong>               means the account held at your financial institution from which we are authorised to arrange for funds to be debited.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Agreement</em></strong><strong>         </strong>means this Direct Debit Request Service Agreement between you and us.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Banking day</em></strong><em>      </em>means a day other than a Saturday or Sunday or a public holiday listed throughout Australia.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Debit day</em></strong><em>            </em>means the day that payment by you to us is due.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Debit payment</em></strong> means a particular transaction where a debit is made.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Direct debit request</em></strong> means the Direct Debit Request between us and you.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Us</em></strong> and <strong><em>we</em></strong>           means Australia Medic Alert Foundation (455996) you have authorised by requesting a Direct Debit Request.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>You</em></strong>                        means the member who signed or authorised by other means the Direct Debit Request.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Your financial institution</em></strong> means the financial institution nominated by you on the DDR at which the account is maintained.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h4>Debiting your account</h4>\r\n<p>By signing a <em>Direct Debit Request</em> or by providing <em>us</em> with a valid instruction, <em>you</em> have authorised <em>us</em> to arrange for funds to be debited from your <em>account</em>. <em>You</em> should refer to the <em>Direct Debit Request</em> and this <em>agreement</em> for the terms of the arrangement between <em>us</em> and <em>you</em>.</p>\r\n<p><em> </em></p>\r\n<p><em>We</em> will only arrange for funds to be debited from <em>your account</em> as authorised in the <em>Direct Debit Request</em>.</p>\r\n<p>OR</p>\r\n<p>We will only arrange for funds to be debited from <em>your account</em> if we have sent to the address nominated by you in the <em>Direct Debit Request</em>, a billing advice which specifies the amount payable by you to us and when it is due.</p>\r\n<p>If the <em>debit day</em> falls on a day that is not a <em>banking day</em>, we may direct your <em>financial institution</em> to debit your <em>account</em> on the following <em>banking day</em>. If you are unsure about which day your <em>account</em> has or will be debited <em>you</em> should ask your <em>financial institution</em>.</p>\r\n<p>Amendments by <em>us</em></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>We may vary any details of this arrangement or a Direct Debit Request at any time by giving<em> you</em> at least <strong>thirty (30) days</strong> written notice.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Amendments by <em>you</em></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><em>You</em> may change, stop or defer a <em>debit payment</em>, or terminate this agreement by providing<em> us</em> with at least 7 days notification by writing to:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>GPO Box 9963</p>\r\n<p>ADELAIDE SA 5001</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>OR</p>\r\n<p>By telephoning <em>us</em> on 1800 88 22 22 during business hours;</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>OR</p>\r\n<p>Arranging it through <em>your financial institution</em>, which is required to act promptly on your instructions.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h4>Your obligations</h4>\r\n<p>It is <em>your</em> responsibility to ensure that there are sufficient clear funds available in <em>your</em> <em>account</em> to allow a <em>debit payment</em> to be made in accordance with the <em>Direct Debit Request</em>.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>If there are insufficient clear funds in your account to meet a <em>debit payment</em>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>you</em> may be charged a fee and/or interest by your <em>financial institution</em>;</li>\r\n<li><em>you</em> may also incur fees or charges imposed or incurred by <em>us</em>; and</li>\r\n<li><em>you</em> must arrange for the <em>debit payment</em> to be made by another method or arrange for sufficient clear funds to be in <em>your</em> <em>account</em> by an agreed time so that <em>we</em> can process the <em>debit payment</em>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><em>You</em> should check <em>your account</em> statement to verify that the amounts debited from <em>your account</em> are correct.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h4>Dispute</h4>\r\n<p>If you believe that there has been an error in debiting your account, you should notify <em>us</em> directly on 1800 88 22 22 and confirm that notice in writing with <em>us</em> as soon as possible so that <em>we</em> can resolve your query more quickly. Alternatively <em>you</em> can take it up with <em>your financial institution</em>.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>If <em>we</em> conclude as a result of our investigations that <em>your account</em> has been incorrectly debited we will respond to <em>your</em> query by arranging for <em>your financial institution</em> to adjust <em>your account</em> (including interest and charges) accordingly. <em>We</em> will also notify <em>you</em> in writing of the amount by which <em>your account </em>has been adjusted.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>If <em>we</em> conclude as a result of our investigations that <em>your account</em> has not been incorrectly debited <em>we</em> will respond to<em> your</em> query by providing <em>you</em> with reasons and any evidence for this finding in writing.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h4>Accounts</h4>\r\n<p><em>You</em> should check:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>with <em>your financial institution</em> whether direct debiting is available from <em>your account</em> as direct debiting is not available on all accounts offered by financial institutions.</li>\r\n<li><em>your account</em> details which <em>you</em> have provided to <em>us</em> are correct by checking them against a recent account statement; and</li>\r\n<li>with <em>your financial institution</em> before completing the <em>Direct Debit Request</em> if <em>you</em> have any queries about how to complete the <em>Direct Debit Request</em>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h4>Confidentiality</h4>\r\n<p><em>We</em> will keep any information (including <em>your account</em> details) in your <em>Direct Debit Request</em> confidential. <em>We</em> will make reasonable efforts to keep any such information that we have about <em>you</em> secure and to ensure that any of<em> our</em> employees or agents who have access to information about <em>you</em> do not make any unauthorised use, modification, reproduction or disclosure of that information.</p>\r\n<p><em>We</em> will only disclose information that we have about <em>you</em>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>to the extent specifically required by law; or</li>\r\n<li>for the purposes of this agreement (including disclosing information in connection with any query or claim).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Notice</p>\r\n<p>If <em>you</em> wish to notify <em>us</em> in writing about anything relating to this <em>agreement</em>, <em>you</em> should write to</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Australia Medic Alert Foundation</p>\r\n<p>Finance Department</p>\r\n<p>GPO Box 9963</p>\r\n<p>ADELAIDE SA 5001</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><em>We</em> will notify <em>you</em> by sending a notice in the ordinary post to the address <em>you</em> have given <em>us</em> in the <em>Direct Debit Request</em>.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Any notice will be deemed to have been received on the third <em>banking day</em> after posting.</p>\r\n<p> </p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Terms and Conditions',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-04 15:37:14','2016-10-25 01:46:42','2016-10-24 12:35:59'),(262,10,1,0,0,'Terms and Conditions',NULL,NULL,'terms-and-conditions',1,'<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF MEMBERSHIP</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>1. Introduction<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>1.1 By applying to become a Member you agree to be bound by these Conditions as varied from time to time. Please read them carefully.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>1.2 We reserve the right to amend these Conditions at any time.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>2. Benefits of Membership<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>2.1 Upon becoming a Member, we will provide the following benefits to you:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>2.1.1 provision of a Medic Alert Identification Number;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>2.1.2 creation and maintenance of an electronic record of all your Health Information;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>2.1.3 secure web based access to your Health Information using any user name or password provided to you or generated in connection with your Membership;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>2.1.4 the right to purchase from us Personalised Medic Alert Products for your own personal use;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>2.1.5 through the 24/7 Medic Alert Emergency Response Service, disclosure of your Health Information to any professional emergency responders and Health Practitioners requesting such information in circumstances where they have quoted your Medic Alert Identification Number or other personal information which identifies you; and</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>2.1.6 access to our newsletter and other Member publications.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>2.2 The above benefits will only be made available to you for so long as your Membership Fees are fully paid up.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>3. Applying for Membership<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.1 You may only apply for Membership:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>3.1.1 on your own behalf; or</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>3.1.2 on behalf of any minor or adult person who is not capable of applying for Membership for him or herself and for whom you are acting as a Responsible Person.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.2 An application for Membership may be for annual or Membership for any other period we may permit.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.3 You may only apply for Membership by providing to us a completed Membership Application Form online through the Website or by post or other means of delivery acceptable to us.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.4 An application for Membership must be accompanied by payment of the relevant Membership Fee Application Fee (if any).</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>4. Membership Fees<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>4.1 Membership Fees are inclusive of GST.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>4.2 Continuation of your annual and other periodic Membership is subject to payment of your annual or other periodic Membership Fee;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>4.3 You must pay your Membership Fees by the due date for payment.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>4.4 We will take reasonable steps to notify you of your Membership Fee falling due before the due date for payment.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>5. Your Information<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.1 We may collect your Personal Information (which includes Health Information) from you or from your Responsible Person, Health Practitioner or other agent nominated by you in connection with your Membership.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.2 We may collect your Health Information from any professional emergency responders and Health Practitioners attending you in the event of a medical emergency where such responders or practitioners have quoted your Medic Alert Identification Number or other personal information which identifies you.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.3 Your Personal Information must be accurate and complete.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.4 We may assist you with providing your Health Information to us however we will not be responsible for the provision of such information.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.5 If you have any doubts or concerns about the Health Information to be provided to us, we recommend that you consult your Health Practitioner who may assist you.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.6 We will not be responsible for any errors or omissions in your Personal Information.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.7 We may give you notice requiring you to update or confirm your Personal Information from time to time and you must comply with such notices.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.8 You must promptly advise us if your Personal Information changes. You may do this by accessing your Personal Information on the Members Only Pages on the Website using any user name or password provided to you or generated in connection with your Membership. Alternatively, you can advise us of these changes over the telephone, by email or by any other means acceptable to us.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.9 You are responsible for the safekeeping of any user name or password provided to you or generated in connection with your Membership. We will not be responsible for any unauthorized use of such user name or passwords including in relation to unauthorized changes to your Health Information.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.10 We may disclose your Personal Information to any professional emergency responders or Health Practitioners attending you in the event of a medical emergency where such responders or practitioners have requested such information and have quoted your Medic Alert Identification Number or other personal information which identifies you.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.11 We will take reasonable steps to verify that any person representing themselves to us as:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>5.11.1 a professional emergency responder or Health Practitioner attending you in the event of a medical emergency; or</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>5.11.2 your Responsible Person, Health Practitioner or other agent nominated by you in connection with your Membership, is such a person.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.12 We may disclose or otherwise deal with your Personal Information as permitted under our Privacy Policy and as permitted under the Privacy Act.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.13 You consent to our collection, holding, disclosure and other dealings with your Personal Information as permitted in these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.14 We will take reasonable steps to protect your Personal Information from misuse and loss and from unauthorised access, modification or disclosure. We will store your Personal Information in access controlled premises, and electronic information on secure servers. We will require all persons authorised to access such information directly from our servers to use logins and passwords to access such information.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.15 We require all persons to whom we disclose your Personal Information or whom may have access to your Personal Information in accordance with these Conditions to keep such information private and to protect such information from misuse and loss and from unauthorised access, modification or disclosure.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.16 Unless we are prevented to do so by the law, we will de-identify or securely destroy your Personal Information when no longer reasonably required by us in connection with your Membership.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.17 Notwithstanding the above security measures, we cannot give any absolute guarantee that your Personal Information will be available at all times and not subject to any misuse or loss, including misuse or loss from unauthorised access, modification or disclosure. We will notify you as soon as we reasonably can if we become aware of any unauthorised access to or modification or disclosure of your Personal Information.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>6. Payments<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.1 You must pay your Membership Fees by payment method options offered by us at the time such payments are due.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.2 Any credit and debit card details provided in respect of any payment under these Conditions are stored until the payment process has been finalised.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.3 We reserve the right to charge a reasonable administration fee for issuing duplicate invoices, statements or other documents requested by you.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>7. Termination<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>7.1 We may terminate your Membership Benefits or your Membership without notice if:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>7.1.1 your Membership Fee is outstanding;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>7.1.2 you commit any breach of these Conditions;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>7.1.3 you abuse any Membership Benefit;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>7.1.4 you provide any misleading information or make any misrepresentations to us;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>7.1.5 you are otherwise dishonest or fraudulent in your dealings with us.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>7.2 We will not be responsible for any Liabilities or other consequence arising out of termination of your Membership Benefits or you Membership.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>7.3 We may only reinstate your Membership Benefits or Membership at our discretion and on any conditions we consider fit.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>8. Our Liability<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>8.1 Except to the extent permitted by the Australian Consumer Law, this clause does not limit our liability in respect of any Consumer Guarantees.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>8.2 Except where otherwise required by law (including the Australian Consumer Law):</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>8.2.1 all guarantees, conditions, warranties or other terms which may be implied by law or otherwise in connection with these Conditions or your Membership Benefits and Membership are excluded;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>8.2.2 we are not liable in tort for any loss or damage suffered by you or by any other person;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>8.2.3 we do not accept responsibility for any Liabilities which you may incur in connection with these Conditions or your Membership Benefits and Membership and you release us from any Claim relating to such Liabilities;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>8.2.4 in no circumstances will we be responsible for any loss of profits or interruption to business or other indirect economic or other consequential loss suffered by you or any third party in connection with these Conditions or your Membership Benefits and Membership<em>;</em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>8.2.5 you indemnify us against all Liabilities which we may incur and release us from any Claim in connection with these Conditions or your Membership Benefits and Membership.</p>\r\n<em>9. Privacy<br /></em>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>9.1 We are committed to protecting your privacy. We collect Personal Information to provide and market our products and services and may disclose that information to our authorised staff, agents, contractors or service providers contractors with whom we have a contractual arrangement, in the course of them undertaking their legitimate duties in providing a given product or service. We may also provide Personal Information to MedicAlert Foundation United States, Inc (based in the United States of America) and to other overseas recipients in accordance with our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot;>Privacy Policy</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>9.2 If you do not provide us with any Personal Information we may request from you, we may not be able to provide you with our products and services or otherwise assist you.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>9.3 Our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot;>Privacy Policy</a> contains information about how you may access or correct Personal Information we hold about you, how you can complain about a breach of privacy and how we will deal with such complaints.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>10. Your Breach<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>You indemnify us against all Liabilities which we may incur in respect of your breach of these Conditions.</p>\r\n<em>11. Contact Us<br /></em>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Please email to us any queries, comments or requests for information you may have regarding these Conditions at <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>12. Notices<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>12.1 We may give notices to you by email, post, text messages or by notices published on our Website. You may give notices to us by email to <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a>.</p>\r\n12.2 We will not be responsible for any delay in or failure to give you any notice referred to in these Conditions.<br />\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>13. General<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>13.1 Unless otherwise provided, we may in our discretion give (conditionally or unconditionally) or withhold any approval or consent under these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>13.2 You must not assign or otherwise deal with these Conditions or any right or obligation under these Conditions without our written consent.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>13.3 These Conditions cover the entire agreement and understanding between you and us with respect to your Membership and Membership Benefits and supersede any prior agreement or understanding.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>13.4 A waiver of a provision of or right under these Conditions by us must be in writing signed by us and is effective only to the extent set out in the written waiver.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>13.5 The failure, delay, relaxation or indulgence in exercising a power or right under these Conditions is not a waiver of that power or right.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>13.6 An exercise of a power or right under these Conditions does not preclude a further exercise of it or the exercise of another right or power.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>13.7 The validity and interpretation of these Conditions are governed by the laws of South Australia. Any dispute in connection with these Conditions is subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of South Australia.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>14. Definitions<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>In these Conditions unless the context otherwise requires:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.1 <strong>Australian Consumer Law</strong> means the law as set out in Schedule 2 of the <em>Competition and Consumer Act 2010</em> (Cth).</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.2 <strong>Claim</strong> means any claim, demand, action or cause of action, whether in contract, tort, equity or under statute, and any loss, cost, expense or Liability arising from or in connection with such claim, demand, action or cause of action.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.3 <strong>Conditions </strong>means these terms and conditions as amended from time to time.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.4 <strong>Consumer Guarantees </strong>means the consumer guarantees under the Australian Consumer Law.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.5 <strong>GST </strong>means the goods and services tax imposed under <em>A New Tax System (Goods And Services Tax) Act 1999</em> (Cth).</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.6 <strong>Health Information </strong>has the meaning set out in the Privacy Act. It includes Personal Information about an individual&rsquo;s health, including disability or injury.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.7 <strong>Health Practitioner</strong> means a health practitioner registered with the Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency and any other person authorised to provide professional personal care to an individual.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.8 <strong>Liabilities </strong>means liabilities, losses, damages, actions, causes of action, arbitrations, claims, orders, judgments, outgoings, costs (including legal costs calculated on a solicitor and own client basis) and expenses, whether present or future, actual or contingent.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.9 <strong>24/7 Medic Alert Emergency Response Service </strong>means our emergency response service operated 24 hours a day, seven days a week for the purposes of providing Health Information to professional emergency responders and Health Practitioners as permitted under these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.10 <strong>Medic Alert Identification Number </strong>means a unique Medic Alert Identification Number provided to you upon becoming a Member in accordance with these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.11 <strong>Member</strong> means any person who applies to become a Member as permitted under these Conditions and <strong>Membership</strong> has a corresponding meaning.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.12 <strong>Member Benefit </strong>means benefits of Membership as provided in these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.13 <strong>Membership Application Form</strong> means an application for Membership in a form we approve from time to time.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.14 <strong>Membership Fee </strong>means a fee for an annual or other periodic Membership as determined by us from time to time.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.15 <strong>Personal Information </strong>has the meaning set out in the Privacy Act. It includes information that can be used to identify an individual.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.16 <strong>Personalised Medic Alert Products </strong>means any product available for purchase from us and which includes or which has affixed to the product your Medic Alert Identification Number or Health Information.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.17 <strong>Privacy Act</strong> means the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth).</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.18 <strong>Responsible Person</strong> has the meaning set out in the Privacy Act. It includes in respect of an individual, a guardian of that individual, close relatives of that individual who are over the age of 18 and any person nominated by that individual to be contacted in case of emergency.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.19 <strong>Website</strong> means the website at <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au/&quot;>www.medicalert.org.au</a> and includes all information tools and other material posted or accessible from that website.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.20 <strong>We</strong>, <strong>our</strong> and <strong>us</strong> refers to Australia Medic Alert Foundation, Level 1, 210 Greenhill Road Eastwood SA 5063.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.21 <strong>You</strong>, <strong>yours</strong> and <strong>yourself</strong> refers to any person applying for Membership as permitted in these Conditions and includes a person on behalf of whom you may be applying for Membership as permitted under these Conditions and a person making a payment under these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.22 <strong>your Health Information</strong> means all Health Information relating to you which is provided to us by you or by any other person as permitted under these Conditions and includes Health Information provided in connection with your Membership.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>14.23 <strong>your Personal Information </strong>all Personal Information relating to you which is provided to us by you or by any other person as permitted under these Conditions and includes your Health Information.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>15. Interpretation<br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>In these Conditions unless the context otherwise requires:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>15.1 headings do not affect interpretation;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>15.2 singular includes plural and plural includes singular;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>15.3 words of one gender include any gender;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>15.4 a reference to a party includes its employees, officers, contractors, executors, administrators, successors, agents and permitted agents and assigns;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>15.5 a reference to a person includes a partnership, corporation, association, government body and any other entity;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>15.6 a reference to legislation includes any amendment to it, any legislation substituted for it, and any subordinate legislation made under it;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>15.7 a provision is not to be construed against us only because we prepared it;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>15.8 an unenforceable provision or part of a provision may be severed, and the remainder of these Conditions continues in force, unless this would materially change the intended effect of these Conditions;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>15.9 the meaning of general words is not limited by specific examples introduced by &lsquo;including&rsquo;, &lsquo;for example&rsquo; or similar expressions.</p>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF SALE</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>1. Introduction</em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>1.1 These Conditions apply each time you place an Order or purchase Products. By placing an Order or purchasing Products, you agree to these Conditions, and on our acceptance of that Order or purchase of Products, a contract incorporating these Conditions is created. Please read them carefully.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>1.2 These Conditions prevail over all inconsistencies in any Order unless we otherwise agree.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>1.3 We reserve the right to amend these Conditions at any time.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>2. Membership Application and Information</em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>2.1 Any information provided by you in connection with your application for Membership must be accurate and complete.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>2.2 You must advise us if any information you have provided to us changes.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>2.3 You are responsible for the safekeeping of any user name or password provided to you or generated by you for the purposes of your Membership or placing any Order. We will not be responsible for any unauthorised use of such user name or passwords including in relation to unauthorised purchases.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>3. Your Order</em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.1 You may only place an Order:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>3.1.1 on your own behalf: or</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>3.1.2 on behalf of any minor or adult person who is not capable of placing an Order for him or herself and for whom you are acting as a Responsible Person.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.2 Orders for Personalised Medic Alert Products may only be placed by or on behalf of a Member in accordance with our Terms and Conditions of Membership.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.3 Orders for delivery to addresses that are not within our delivery area may not be accepted or may be subject to an additional charge. We will let you know if your Delivery Address is not within our delivery area, or ceases to be within our delivery area.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.4 Any Orders placed with us must be completed online through the Website, using our hard copy Order form or by any other means acceptable to us from time to time.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.5 You must provide all information requested in relation to your Order otherwise, the Order may not be accepted.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.6 You must ensure that all information you provide in respect of your Order is accurate and complete.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.7 We may assist you with completing your Order however we will not be responsible for the information you provide in respect of your Order.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.8 If you have any doubts or concerns about the information to be provided in respect of your Order, we strongly recommend that you consult your Health Practitioner who may assist you.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>3.9 We will not be responsible for any Products supplied in connection with your Order which are unsuitable due to any errors or omissions in information provided in respect of your Order. You may not return or exchange such Products or Claim a refund or credit for such Products.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>4. Substitute Products</em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Unless you have indicated in the Order that you will not accept substitute Products, we reserve the right to deliver substitute Products if the Products in the Order are out of stock at the time of processing the Order.</p>\r\n<em>5. Delivery</em>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.1 Delivery times advised to you are estimates only and we are not liable for late delivery or non delivery.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.2 You may cancel an Order if we are unable to deliver the Products within three months of any delivery times advised.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.3 Except where clause 5.2 applies:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>5.3.1 we are not liable for any loss, damage or delay arising from late or non-delivery of the Products;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>5.3.2 late delivery or non-delivery does not vary these Conditions or relieve you from your obligations to accept the Products and to pay for the Products.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.4 Delivery of the Products will be taken to have occurred when posted or otherwise delivered to the Delivery Address.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.5 Any person at the Delivery Address who receives the Products is taken to be authorised to receive the Products.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>5.6 Ownership in the Products passes on delivery and the Products shall be at your risk after delivery.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>6. Prices and Payment</em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.1 Unless otherwise stated, all prices published by us are inclusive of GST but do not include delivery charges.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.2 Products and delivery charges in respect of your Order will be charged at the prices and charges published by us at the time of submitting the Order and appearing in our confirmation of the Order unless:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>6.2.1 you modify the Order, in which case, the Products will be charged at the higher of the prices published by us at the time of submitting the Order and the prices published by us at the time of modification of the Order;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>6.2.2 the Products are out of stock and you have indicated in the Order that you will not accept substitute Products, in which case, there will be no charge for the Products;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 35px;&quot;>6.2.3 the Products are out of stock and you have indicated in the Order that you will accept substitute Products, in which case, the Products will be charged at the lower of the price for the original Products published by us at the time of submitting the Order and the price of the substitute Products published by us at the time of processing the Order.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.3 We reserve the right to rectify any pricing errors published due to human error, computer malfunction or any other reason. We will notify you of any error in pricing and you may elect not to proceed with any purchase of Products affected by such error.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.4 We will provide you with a tax invoice with the total price for the Products, including credits applied and any other fees at or prior to delivery of the Products.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.5 On placement of an Order, you must select your payment method from the payment options offered by us at the time of Order. Unless we otherwise agree, payment must be made by the selected payment method.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.6 Any credit and debit card details provided in connection with an Order are stored until the Order process has been finalised.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>6.7 We reserve the right to charge a reasonable administration fee for issuing duplicate invoices, statements or other documents requested by you.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>7. Cancellations</em>\r\n<p>7.1 Subject to clause 5.2, you may not cancel a Contract at any time except with our consent.</p>\r\n<p>7.2 In the event that you cancel a Contract otherwise than under clause 5.2, you must indemnify us against all Liabilities we incur in respect of such cancellation including in respect of Consequential Loss.</p>\r\n<p>7.3 In the event you cancel a Contract under clause 5.2, we will refund to you any sums paid in respect of the Products. We will not have any other liability in respect of such cancellation.</p>\r\n<p>7.4 We may cancel any Contract any time before Products are delivered by giving notice to you. On giving such notice, we will refund to you any sums paid in respect of the Products. We will not have any other liability in respect of such cancellation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>8. Personalised Medic Alert Products</em></p>\r\n<p>8.1 You may not re-supply any Personalised Medic Alert Products purchased otherwise than to any person for whom you have Ordered or purchased the Products acting as Responsible Person.</p>\r\n<p>8.2 We will not be responsible for any Personalised Medic Alert Products resupplied otherwise than as permitted under these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>8.3 We will not make any changes to any Personalised Medic Alert Products resupplied otherwise than as permitted under these Conditions.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>9. Credits and Refunds</em></p>\r\n<p>9.1 You can make a Claim for a refund or credit for Products delivered to you if:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>9.1.1 the Products do not correspond to the Order;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>9.1.2 the Products invoiced are not the Products delivered; or</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>9.1.3 the Products are defective under the terms of any warranty against manufacturing defects in material or workmanship we may provide in respect of the Product at 