st manufacturing defects in material or workmanship we may provide in respect of the Product at the time of placement of your Order.</p>\r\n<p>9.2 Email <a href=&quot;emailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a> to lodge your Claim. We will assess your Claim and if accepted, we will provide you with a credit or refund at our discretion. We may need to inspect the Products to assess your Claim so you are required to keep the Products until we notify you that they may be discarded.</p>\r\n<p>9.3 Credit accepted for the value of any Products under this clause will be applied to your next Order as long as the Order is for a value of at least the amount of credit accepted. This credit will lapse after 12 months.</p>\r\n<p><em>10. Australian Consumer Law</em></p>\r\n<p>10.1 Our Products come with guarantees that cannot be excluded under the Australian Consumer Law. You are entitled to a replacement or refund for a major failure and compensation for any other reasonably foreseeable loss or damage. You are also entitled to have the Products repaired or replaced if the Products fail to be of acceptable quality and the failure does not amount to a major failure.</p>\r\n<p>10.2 Where the Contract under which you purchase the Products is a Consumer Contract (ie where you are a Consumer):</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>10.2.1 the Products are supplied subject to the Consumer Guarantees; and</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>10.2.2 you may only exercise any right or remedy for breach of a Consumer Guarantee strictly in accordance with your rights and responsibilities under the Australian Consumer Law.</p>\r\n<p><em>11. Our Liability</em></p>\r\n<p>11.1 Except to the extent permitted by the Australian Consumer Law, this clause does not limit our liability in respect of any Consumer Guarantees.</p>\r\n<p>11.2 None of the Implied Terms apply to any Contract except to the extent that they cannot be lawfully excluded.</p>\r\n<p>11.3 We are not liable in tort for any loss or damage suffered by you or by any other person.</p>\r\n<p>11.4 In no circumstances whatsoever shall we be liable to you or to any other person arising from the Products following delivery being:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>11.4.1 stored, handled, used or consumed contrary to any directions or recommendations made by us or the manufacturer of the Products from time to time;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>11.4.2 altered, modified, co-mingled or combined with any other products or ingredients otherwise than in accordance with any directions or recommendations made by us or the manufacturer of the Products from time to time;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>11.4.3 otherwise subject to inappropriate storage or handling, contamination, misuse, neglect, negligence or damage; or</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>11.4.4 used or consumed after any defect in the Products becomes reasonably apparent.</p>\r\n<p>11.5 In no circumstance whatsoever shall we be liable to you or to any third party for any Consequential Loss arising out of the late delivery of Products or any failure to perform or observe our obligations under any Contract or Implied Terms and you will keep us fully indemnified against all Liabilities arising from any Claim made against us by a third party for Consequential Loss.</p>\r\n<p><em>12. Privacy</em></p>\r\n<p>12.1 We are committed to protecting your privacy. We collect Personal Information to provide and market our products and services and may disclose that information to our authorised staff, agents, contractors or service providers contractors with whom we have a contractual arrangement, in the course of them undertaking their legitimate duties in providing a given product or service. We may also provide Personal Information to MedicAlert Foundation United States, Inc (based in the United States of America) and to other overseas recipients in accordance with our Privacy Policy.</p>\r\n<p>12.2 If you do not provide us with any Personal Information we may request from you, we may not be able to provide you with our products and services or otherwise assist you.</p>\r\n<p>12.3 Our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot;>Privacy Policy</a> contains information about how you may access or correct information we hold about you, how you can complain about a breach of privacy and how we will deal with such complaints.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>13. Your Breach</em></p>\r\n<p>13.1 You indemnify us against all Liabilities which we may incur in respect of your breach of these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>13.2 Any breach or threatened breach of these Conditions entitles us to apply for and obtain injunctive relief in any court of competent jurisdiction in addition to all other available remedies.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>14. Contact Us</em></p>\r\n<p>Please email to us any queries, comments or requests for information you may have regarding these Conditions at <a href=&quot;emailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>15. Notices</em></p>\r\n<p>15.1 We may give notices to you by email, post or by notices published on our Website. You may give notices to us by email to <a href=&quot;emailto: enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a>.</p>\r\n<p>15.2 We will not be responsible for any delay in or failure to give you any notice referred to in these Conditions.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>16. General</em></p>\r\n<p>16.1 Unless otherwise provided, we may in our discretion give (conditionally or unconditionally) or withhold any approval or consent under a Contract.</p>\r\n<p>16.2 You must not assign or otherwise deal with a Contract or any right or obligation under it without our written consent.</p>\r\n<p>16.3 A Contract covers the entire agreement and understanding between you and us with respect to the subject matter of the Contract and supersede any prior agreement or understanding.</p>\r\n<p>16.4 A waiver of a provision of or right under a Contract by us must be in writing signed by us and is effective only to the extent set out in the written waiver.</p>\r\n<p>16.5 The failure, delay, relaxation or indulgence by a party in exercising a power or right under a Contract is not a waiver of that power or right.</p>\r\n<p>16.6 An exercise of a power or right under a Contract does not preclude a further exercise of it or the exercise of another right or power.</p>\r\n<p>16.7 Each indemnity, obligation of confidence and other term capable of taking effect after the expiration or termination of a Contract, remains in force after the expiration or termination of the Contract.</p>\r\n<p>16.8 The validity and interpretation of these Conditions are governed by the laws of South Australia. Any dispute in connection with these Conditions is subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of South Australia.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>17. Definitions</em></p>\r\n<p>In these Conditions unless the context otherwise requires:</p>\r\n<p>17.1 <strong>Australian Consumer Law</strong> means the law as set out in Schedule 2 of the <em>Competition and Consumer Act 2010</em> (Cth).</p>\r\n<p>17.2 <strong>Claim</strong> means any claim, demand, action or cause of action, whether in contract, tort, equity or under statute, and any loss, cost, expense or Liability arising from or in connection with such claim, demand, action or cause of action.</p>\r\n<p>17.3 <strong>Conditions </strong>means these terms and conditions as amended from time to time.</p>\r\n<p>17.4 <strong>Consumer </strong>means a &ldquo;consumer&rdquo; as that term is defined in Section 3 of the Australian Consumer Law.</p>\r\n<p>17.5 <strong>Consumer Contract </strong>means a contract for supply of Products by us to the Buyer as a Consumer.</p>\r\n<p>17.6 <strong>Consumer Guarantee </strong>means the consumer guarantees under the Australian Consumer Law.</p>\r\n<p>17.7 <strong>Consequential Loss </strong>means loss of data or profits, loss of anticipated savings, economic loss or interruption of business or any other indirect or consequential loss.</p>\r\n<p>17.8 <strong>Contract </strong>means a contract for the supply of Products in accordance with these Conditions, as evidence by our acceptance of any Order.</p>\r\n<p>17.9 <strong>Delivery Address </strong>means the Australian delivery address specified in an Order.</p>\r\n<p>17.10 <strong>GST </strong>means the goods and services tax imposed under <em>A New Tax System (Goods And Services Tax) Act 1999</em> (Cth).</p>\r\n<p>17.11 <strong>Health Information </strong>has the meaning set out in the Privacy Act. It includes Personal Information about an individual&rsquo;s health, including disability or injury.</p>\r\n<p>17.12 <strong>Health Practitioner</strong> means a health practitioner registered with the Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency.</p>\r\n<p>17.13 <strong>Implied Term </strong>means any guarantees, conditions, warranties or other terms implied by any Australian Commonwealth, State or Territory laws (excluding the Australian Consumer Law), or the laws of any other jurisdiction.</p>\r\n<p>17.14 <strong>Liabilities </strong>means liabilities, losses, damages, actions, causes of action, arbitrations, claims, orders, judgments, outgoings, costs (including legal costs calculated on a solicitor and own client basis) and expenses, whether present or future, actual or contingent.</p>\r\n<p>17.15 <strong>Medic Alert Identification Number </strong>means a unique Medic Alert Identification Number provided to you upon becoming a member in accordance with our terms and conditions of membership from time to time.</p>\r\n<p>17.16 <strong>Member </strong>means a Member in accordance with our Terms and Conditions of Membership.</p>\r\n<p>17.17 <strong>Order</strong> means any order for the supply of Products by us to you from time to time.</p>\r\n<p>17.18 <strong>Personal Information </strong>has the meaning set out in the Privacy Act. It includes information that can be used to identify an individual.</p>\r\n<p>17.19 <strong>Privacy Act</strong> means the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth).</p>\r\n<p>17.20 <strong>Personalised Medic Alert Products</strong> means Products which include or which have affixed to the Products your Health Information or your Medic Alert Identification Number.</p>\r\n<p>17.21 <strong>Products </strong>means the Products supplied by us to you from time to time and includes gift cards and Products which are the subject of an Order.</p>\r\n<p>17.22 <strong>Responsible Person</strong> has the meaning set out in the Privacy Act. It includes in respect of an individual, a guardian of that individual, close relatives of that individual who are over the age of 18 and any person nominated by that individual to be contacted in case of emergency.</p>\r\n<p>17.23 <strong>Terms and Conditions of Membership</strong> means our terms and conditions of membership published from time to time.</p>\r\n<p>17.24 <strong>Website</strong> means the website at <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au/&quot;>www.medicalert.org.au</a> and includes all information tools and other material posted or accessible from that website.</p>\r\n<p>17.25 <strong>We</strong>, <strong>our</strong> and <strong>us</strong> refers to Australia Medic Alert Foundation, Level 1, 210 Greenhill Road Eastwood SA 5063.</p>\r\n<p>17.26 <strong>You</strong>,<strong> yours</strong> and <strong>yourself</strong> refers to any person purchasing Products from us or placing an order for the purchase of Products from us and includes a person on behalf of whom you may be purchasing Products or placing an Order as permitted under these Conditions and a person making a payment under these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p><em>18. Interpretation</em></p>\r\n<p>In these Conditions unless the context otherwise requires:</p>\r\n<p>18.1 headings do not affect interpretation;</p>\r\n<p>18.2 singular includes plural and plural includes singular;</p>\r\n<p>18.3 words of one gender include any gender;</p>\r\n<p>18.4 a reference to a party includes its employees, officers, contractors, executors, administrators, successors, agents and permitted agents and assigns;</p>\r\n<p>18.5 a reference to a person includes a partnership, corporation, association, government body and any other entity;</p>\r\n<p>18.6 a reference to legislation includes any amendment to it, any legislation substituted for it, and any subordinate legislation made under it;</p>\r\n<p>18.7 a provision is not to be construed against us only because we prepared it;</p>\r\n<p>18.8 an unenforceable provision or part of a provision may be severed, and the remainder of these Conditions continues in force, unless this would materially change the intended effect of these Conditions;</p>\r\n<p>18.9 the meaning of general words is not limited by specific examples introduced by &lsquo;including&rsquo;, &lsquo;for example&rsquo; or similar expressions.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<h3>WEBSITE TERMS AND CONDITIONS</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>1. Introduction</em></p>\r\n<p>1.1 These Conditions are in effect at all times while you are using the Website. By using the Website, you agree to these Conditions. Please read them carefully.</p>\r\n<p>1.2 We reserve the right to amend these Conditions at any time.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>2. Our Website</em></p>\r\n<p>2.1 While we take all reasonable care in the construction, operation and content of the Website, we make no guarantee or warranty that:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>2.1.1 the use of the Website will be uninterrupted or virus and error free;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>2.1.2 any information contained in the Website is complete, accurate or up to date.</p>\r\n<p>2.2 Where the Website contains information, opinions or advice of or given by third parties, we do not endorse such information, opinions or advice or give any guarantee or warranty as to the accuracy or reliability of such information, opinions or advice.</p>\r\n<p>2.3 You must take your own precautions to ensure that the process which you employ for accessing the Website does not expose you to the risk of viruses, malicious computer code or other forms of interference which may damage your computer system. We are not responsible for any interference or damage to your computer system which arises in connection with your use of the Website or any other website linked to the Website.</p>\r\n<p>2.4 We may ask other people to analyse traffic on the Website and they may use cookies to do so. Cookies are small text files that are transferred to a user&rsquo;s hard drive by a website for the purpose of collecting information about a user&rsquo;s identity, browser type or website visiting patterns.</p>\r\n<p>2.5 Access to the Website may be terminated at any time by us without notice.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>5. Links To Other Websites</em></p>\r\n<p>Any links to third party websites located on the Website are provided for your convenience only. We have not reviewed each third party website and have no responsibility for such third party websites or their content. We do not endorse the third party websites or make representations about them or any material contained in them. If you choose to access a third party website linked to the Website, you do so at your own risk.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>4. Your Conduct</em></p>\r\n<p>4.1 You must not post or send to or from the Website any information or other material:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>4.1.1 that is inaccurate or misleading or deceptive in any material respect;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>4.1.2 that contains images of another person without that person&#039;s permission (or in the case of a minor, the minor&#039;s parent or legal guardian);</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>4.1.3 for which a third party holds the Intellectual Property Rights where you have not obtained all necessary consents to copy, disclose, distribute, incorporate or otherwise use the material for any purpose;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>4.1.4 that is discriminatory, obscene, pornographic, defamatory, liabile to incite racial hatred, in breach of confidentiality or privacy, which may cause annoyance or inconvenience to others, which encourages or constitutes conduct that would be deemed a criminal offence, give rise to a civil liability, or otherwise is contrary to the law in Australia;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>4.1.5 that is harmful in nature including computer viruses, Trojan horses, corrupted data, or other potentially harmful software or data; or</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>4.1.6 that may be used in connection with spamming, spimmin, phishing, trolling or similar activities.</p>\r\n<p>4.2 You must not use the Website for the advertising, promotion or sale of goods or services or any other commercial activity nor may you solicit any Other User for such purposes.</p>\r\n<p>4.3 You must not through the Website or in any other manner, harass, annoy, intimidate or threaten us or our employees or agents or any Other Users.</p>\r\n<p>4.4 We will fully co-operate with any law enforcement authorities or court order requiring us to disclose the identity or other details of any person contravening this clause.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>5. Our Liability</em></p>\r\n<p>5.1 Except to the extent permitted by the Australian Consumer Law, this clause does not limit our liability in respect of any Consumer Guarantees.</p>\r\n<p>5.2 Except where otherwise required by law (including the Australian Consumer Law):</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>5.2.1 all guarantees, conditions, warranties or other terms which may be implied by law or otherwise in connection with these Conditions or your use of the Website and the licence in clause 7.3 are excluded;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>5.2.2 we are not liable in tort for any loss or damage suffered by you or by any other person;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>5.2.3 we do not accept responsibility for any Liabilities which you may incur in connection with these Conditions or your use of the Website or any linked website and the licence in clause 7.3 and you release us from any Claim relating to such Liabilities;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>5.2.4 in no circumstances will we be responsible for any loss of profits or interruption to business or other indirect economic or other consequential loss suffered by you or any third party in connection with these Conditions or your use of the Website and the licence in clause 7.3<em>;</em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>5.2.5 you indemnify us against all Liabilities which we may incur and release us from any Claim in connection with these Conditions or your use of the Website and the licence in clause 7.3.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>6. Privacy</em></p>\r\n<p>6.1 We are committed to protecting your privacy. We collect Personal Information to provide and market our products and services and may disclose that information to our authorised staff, agents, contractors or service providers contractors with whom we have a contractual arrangement, in the course of them undertaking their legitimate duties in providing a given product or service. We may also provide Personal Information to MedicAlert Foundation United States, Inc (based in the United States of America) and to other overseas recipients in accordance with our Privacy Policy.</p>\r\n<p>6.2 If you do not provide us with any Personal Information we may request from you, we may not be able to provide you with our products and services or otherwise assist you.</p>\r\n<p>6.3 Our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot;>Privacy Policy</a> contains information about how you may access or correct information we hold about you, how you can complain about a breach of privacy and how we will deal with such complaints.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>7. Intellectual Property</em></p>\r\n<p>7.1 Except as expressly provided in this clause, you acquire no Intellectual Property Rights in using the Website.</p>\r\n<p>7.2 Copyright and other Intellectual Property Rights in all material on the Website and underlying software codes and programs are held by us or licensed by us.</p>\r\n<p>7.3 We grant you a non exclusive non transferrable royalty free licence to print and download material from the Website for the purpose of comparing or reviewing our products or services or recording your purchase of our products or services, provided that you do not modify such material without our consent.</p>\r\n<p>7.4 The licence in clause 7.3 terminates automatically and without the requirement for notice in the event you breach any of your obligations under these Terms and Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>7.5 Subject to the limited licence in clause 7.3, other than for the purposes of, and subject to the conditions prescribed under the <em>Copyright Act 1968</em> (Cth) and equivalent legislation which applies in your location, you may not, in any form or by any means:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>7.5.1 download, print, display, perform, reverse engineer, modify, reproduce, transmit, disseminate or publish such material; or</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>7.5.2 create derivative works from any part of such material;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>7.5.3 commercialise any information, products or services obtained from any part of the material</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>without our consent or, in the case of third party material, the consent of the owner of the copyright in that material.</p>\r\n<p>7.6 With the exception of Personal Information, the use of which is covered under our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot;>Privacy Policy</a>, any material you send or post to the Website or you otherwise provide to us will be considered non-proprietary and not confidential.</p>\r\n<p>7.7 By posting or sending material to or from the Website or otherwise providing material to us, you:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>7.7.1 warrant to us that such material does not infringe any Intellectual Property Rights of any person; and</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;padding-left: 35px;&quot;>7.7.2 grant us an irrevocable, perpetual non-exclusive royalty free license to download, print, display, perform, reverse engineer, modify, adapt copy, reproduce, transmit, disseminate and publish such material and to create derivative works from any part of such material for any purpose and to grant sublicenses of the same.</p>\r\n<p>7.8 You must notify us as soon as practicably possible, in the event you believe that any material on the Website constitutes an infringement of any Intellectual Property Rights and provide us with details and supporting evidence as we may reasonably request.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>8. Reservation of Rights</em></div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>8.1 We reserve the right to remove or modify any material on the Website at any time.</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>8.2 We reserve the right to carry out our own investigations by various means for the purposes of verifying any information which you send or post to or from the Website and you consent to us carrying out such investigations. However, we make no warranties or representations about the conduct of such enquiries and will not be responsible to you for any information incorrectly verified.</div>\r\n<div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<p><em>9. Your Breach</em></p>\r\n<p>9.1 You indemnify us against all Liabilities which we may incur in respect of your breach of these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>9.2 Any breach or threatened breach of these Conditions entitles us to apply for and obtain injunctive relief in any court of competent jurisdiction in addition to all other available remedies.</p>\r\n<p><em>10. Contact Us</em></p>\r\n<p>Please do not hesitate to send us any queries, comments or requests for information you may have regarding these Terms and Conditions. Please email <a href=&quot;mailto: enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a>.</p>\r\n<p><em>11. General</em></p>\r\n<p>11.1 Unless otherwise provided, we may in our discretion give (conditionally or unconditionally) or withhold any approval or consent under these Conditions.</p>\r\n<p>11.2 You must not assign or otherwise deal with these Conditions or any right or obligation under these Conditions without our written consent.</p>\r\n<p>11.3 These Conditions cover the entire agreement and understanding between you and us with respect to your use of the Website and supersede any prior agreement or understanding.</p>\r\n<p>11.4 If there is any conflict between anything in these Conditions and anything else in the Website, these Conditions prevail.</p>\r\n<p>11.5 A waiver of a provision of or right under these Conditions by us must be in writing signed by us and is effective only to the extent set out in the written waiver.</p>\r\n<p>11.6 The failure, delay, relaxation or indulgence in exercising a power or right under these Conditions is not a waiver of that power or right.</p>\r\n<p>11.7 An exercise of a power or right under these Conditions does not preclude a further exercise of it or the exercise of another right or power.</p>\r\n<p>11.8 Any indemnity or release in these Conditions survives termination of access to or closure of the Website. Any other provision in these Conditions intended to do so, survives the suspension or termination of access to or closure of the Website.</p>\r\n<p>11.9 The validity and interpretation of these Conditions are governed by the laws of South Australia. Any dispute in connection with these Conditions is subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of South Australia.</p>\r\n<p><em>12. Definitions</em></p>\r\n<p>In these Conditions unless the context otherwise requires:</p>\r\n<p>12.1 <strong>Australian Consumer Law</strong> means the law as set out in Schedule 2 of the <em>Competition and Consumer Act 2010</em> (Cth).</p>\r\n<p>12.2 <strong>Claim</strong> means any claim, demand, action or cause of action, whether in contract, tort, equity or under statute, and any loss, cost, expense or Liability arising from or in connection with such claim, demand, action or cause of action.</p>\r\n<p>12.3 <strong>Conditions</strong> means these Conditions as amended from time to time.</p>\r\n<p>12.4 <strong>Consumer Guarantees</strong> means the consumer guarantees under the Australian Consumer Law.</p>\r\n<p>12.5 <strong>Intellectual Property</strong> and <strong>Intellectual Property Rights </strong>includes property and rights in connection with copyright (including future copyright and rights in the nature of or analogous to copyright), know-how, trade mark, service mark, design, inventions (including patents), semi-conductor or circuit layout rights, trade, business or company names, or other proprietary rights, or any rights to registration of such rights (including all renewals and extensions).</p>\r\n<p>12.6 <strong>Liabilities </strong>means liabilities, losses, damages, actions, causes of action, arbitrations, claims, orders, judgments, outgoings, costs (including legal costs calculated on a solicitor and own client basis) and expenses, whether present or future, actual or contingent.</p>\r\n<p>12.7 <strong>Other Users</strong> means a third party using the Website.</p>\r\n<p>12.8 <strong>Personal Information</strong> has the meaning set out in the Privacy Act.</p>\r\n<p>12.9 <strong>Privacy Act</strong> means the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth).</p>\r\n<p>12.10 <strong>Website</strong> means the website at <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au/&quot;>www.medicalert.org.au</a> and includes all information tools and other material posted or accessible from that website.</p>\r\n<p>12.11 <strong>We</strong>, <strong>our</strong> and <strong>us</strong> refers to Australia Medic Alert Foundation, Level 1, 210 Greenhill Road Eastwood SA 5063.</p>\r\n<p>12.12 <strong>You</strong>,<strong> your </strong>and <strong>yourself</strong> refers to any person viewing or using the Website, including any links from the Website, either wholly or in part and includes a person who places an order for a product through the Website or who makes a payment in connection with the use of the Website.</p>\r\n<p><em>13. Interpretation</em></p>\r\n<p>In these Conditions unless the context otherwise requires:</p>\r\n<p>13.1 headings do not affect interpretation;</p>\r\n<p>13.2 singular includes plural and plural includes singular;</p>\r\n<p>13.3 words of one gender include any gender;</p>\r\n<p>13.4 a reference to a party includes its employees, officers, contractors, executors, administrators, successors and permitted agents and assigns;</p>\r\n<p>13.5 a reference to a person includes a partnership, corporation, association, government body and any other entity;</p>\r\n<p>13.6 a reference to legislation includes any amendment to it, any legislation substituted for it, and any subordinate legislation made under it;</p>\r\n<p>13.7 a provision is not to be construed against us only because we prepared it;</p>\r\n<p>13.8 an unenforceable provision or part of a provision may be severed, and the remainder of these Conditions continues in force, unless this would materially change the intended effect of these Conditions;</p>\r\n<p>13.9 the meaning of general words is not limited by specific examples introduced by &lsquo;including&rsquo;, &lsquo;for example&rsquo; or similar expressions.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Version 6.0 | Date: 31 October 2016</p>\r\n</div>','<div id=&quot;gift-certificates&quot; class=&quot;text-left&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;h1&quot; style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>GIFT CERTIFICATE TERMS AND CONDITIONS</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;h1&quot; style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Acceptance of terms and conditions</div>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>By purchasing, redeeming or attempting to redeem a Gift Certificate, you accept and become bound by the terms and conditions below as varied from time to time.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Purchasing Gift Certificates</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>You may purchase Gift Certificates by completing all mandatory fields.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>We will send Gift Certificates electronically to the Recipient&rsquo;s Email Address immediately upon purchase, or at 9:00am Australian Eastern Standard Time on the date you select at the time of purchase.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>We will email to Your Email Address confirmation of your purchase and confirmation that the Gift Certificate has been sent to the Recipient. These confirmations will be sent at the time of purchase and sending of the Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Notwithstanding the above, we will not be responsible for any delay in sending a Gift Certificates or any delay in sending confirmation of purchase or sending of a Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Please correctly complete all mandatory fields on purchase of a Gift Certificate as we will not be responsible for any lost or incorrect Gift Certificates due to incorrect or incomplete information being provided.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Pricing and payment</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>All prices for Gift Certificates are in Australian dollars and all payments must be made in Australian dollars. We are not responsible for any losses associated with currency exchange or exchange rate fluctuations.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Gift Certificates may only be purchased using an acceptable debit or credit card. Debit and credit card details provided at the time of purchase are stored until the purchase has been processed.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>How and when you can redeem a Gift Certificate</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>You may redeem a Gift Certificate by the purchase of goods or services from us through our website, over the phone or at our National Office.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>You will be required to provide the unique identification number printed on the Gift Certificate at the point of redemption.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>A Gift Certificate may only be redeemed by the purchase of goods and services up to the value specified on the Gift Certificate. If you wish to make a purchase that exceeds that value, you must pay the excess using another method of payment.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>A Gift Certificate may only be redeemed in one transaction. A Gift Certificate will not be debited, reissued or replaced with a new Gift Certificate with a lower value as a consequence of purchases that are below the value specified on the Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Once your Gift Certificate is redeemed, it should be destroyed.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Reversal of redemption</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>The redemption of Gift Certificates may not be cancelled or reversed except with our approval which we may give or withhold at our discretion. This does not affect your rights under the Australian Consumer Law or under our returns policy in respect of goods or services purchased on redemption of a Gift Certificate.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>No exchange</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Gift Certificates cannot be exchanged or redeemed for cash.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Expiry of Gift Certificates</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Gift Certificates will expire 36 months from their date of issue if they are not redeemed in accordance with these terms and conditions.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Lost or stolen Gift Certificates</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Gift Cards should be treated like cash. Lost or stolen Gift Certificates will not be replaced or refunded.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Your responsibilities</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>You are responsible for the use and safety of your Gift Certificate. We are not responsible for any transactions using your Gift Certificate except to the extent that there has been fraud or negligence by us or by any of our employees.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Disclaimer</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>To the extent permitted by law, we exclude all responsibility for any harm to any person or property or for any loss of profits or other indirect or consequential loss relating to the purchase, redemption or attempted redemption of Gift Certificates, including any delay in sending Gift Certificates.</p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Privacy</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>We collect personal information to provide and market our products and services. That information may be disclosed to our contractors who assist us with these activities and to our affiliate in the United States of America, MedicAlert Foundation United States, Inc. Our <a href=&quot;/privacy-policy&quot;>privacy policy</a> contains information about how an individual may access or correct information we hold about the individual, how complaints about a breach of privacy can be made to us and how such complaints will be dealt with. If you do not consent to us using your personal information to market products and services, please email <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au.</a> <strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Contact us</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Please do not hesitate to email <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a> about any queries, comments or requests for information you may have regarding Gift Certificates or these terms and conditions.</p>\r\n</div>','<div id=&quot;service-communication&quot; class=&quot;text-left&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;h1&quot;>COMMUNICATION SERVICE GUARANTEE</div>\r\n<p>The Australia Medic Alert Foundation (AMAF) is committed to providing high quality services, and adopts the following service standards, guided by our core values of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Accountability</li>\r\n<li>Commitment</li>\r\n<li>Community</li>\r\n<li>Equity and Diversity</li>\r\n<li>Integrity</li>\r\n<li>WH&amp;S</li>\r\n<li>Innovation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>When you contact us</h1>\r\n<h2>Telephone enquiries</h2>\r\n<p>If you call us we will answer your calls promptly and courteously and aim to answer your queries on the spot.</p>\r\n<p>We recognise that you may have queries that are unique to your own specific</p>\r\n<p>circumstances or are complex. In these instances we may need to arrange a call back so that we can research the query sufficiently to ensure a specific and thorough response is given.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, if your query is not straight forward, please email us. We aim to provide you with a response within 3 business days for queries sent to <a href=&quot;mailto:enquiry@medicalert.org.au&quot;>enquiry@medicalert.org.au</a></p>\r\n<h2>Correspondence (letter or email)</h2>\r\n<p>We will acknowledge your correspondence within 24 hours of receipt (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply). We aim to give you a full response to general correspondence within 3 business days of receiving all of the required information. In some cases, we may request further information from you to ensure that we understand your reason for contact fully and to give you a full response.</p>\r\n<p>For more complex correspondence, the exact timing and content of our response will depend on each case and the request.</p>\r\n<h2>Social Media Channels</h2>\r\n<p>We will acknowledge your correspondence within 4 - 6 hours of receipt during</p>\r\n<p>business hours (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply). We aim to give you a full response to general correspondence within 3 business days of receiving all of the required information. In some cases, we may request further information from you to ensure that we understand your reason for contact fully and to give you a full response.</p>\r\n<p>For more complex correspondence, the exact timing and content of our response will depend on each case and the request.</p>\r\n<h2>AMAF membership application forms</h2>\r\n<p>When you lodge a form to become a member or update your details we aim to process the request within 3 business days of receipt of all of the required information.</p>\r\n<h1>When you provide us with feedback</h1>\r\n<h2>General</h2>\r\n<p>We take your feedback seriously. We will listen and work with you to reach a resolution where we can.</p>\r\n<p>If you provide feedback, we will act immediately where there is a serious risk to public trust and confidence and/or they relate to AMAF&rsquo;s compliance requirements.</p>\r\n<p>We aim to provide a substantive response to your feedback within 3 business days.</p>\r\n<h2>Product</h2>\r\n<p id=&quot;product_warranty&quot;>All AMAF products offered to our members are supported by <a href=&quot;/uploads/documents/product_warranty_statement_v1.1_a4_jan14_copy1.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Product Warranty Statement</a>.</p>\r\n<p>If you provide feedback about a product we will work with you to reach a resolution where we can within the warranty guidelines.</p>\r\n<p>We aim to address any product queries or concerns on the spot, but where the issue is unique or complex we may need to arrange a call back so that we can research the query sufficiently to ensure a specific and thorough response is given. In all cases, we aim to address the issue within 3 business days.</p>\r\n<h1>When you request information we hold</h1>\r\n<h2>General information requests</h2>\r\n<p>We aim to acknowledge all requests for access to information within 24 hours receipt (excluding weekends and public holidays, when the next business day would apply).</p>\r\n<p>We aim to provide a response to requests not falling under the Freedom of Information Act and Privacy Act within 14 business days.</p>\r\n<h2>Freedom of Information Act requests</h2>\r\n<p>We aim to respond to requests for information falling under the Freedom of Information Act within 30 calendar days (plus statutory extensions). Where third party consultation is required; we aim to provide you with a full response within 60 calendar days.</p>\r\n<h2>Privacy Act requests</h2>\r\n<p>If you raise an issue with us that falls under the Privacy Act, we aim to provide a response within 30 calendar days.</p>\r\n</div>','<h1 id=&quot;auto-renewal&quot; style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>DIRECT DEBIT REQUEST (DDR)</h1>\r\n<h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Australia Medic Alert Foundation (455996)</h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>By agreeing to the Terms and Conditions of Auto Renewal via Direct Debit you authorise Australia Medic Alert Foundation (455996) to arrange, through its own financial institution,</p>\r\n<ol style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<li>a debit to your nominated account any amount Australia Medic Alert Foundation (455996), has deemed payable by you. This debit or charge will be made through the Bulk Electronic Clearing System (BECS) from your account held at the financial institution you have nominated and will be subject to the terms and conditions of the Customer Direct Debit Request (DDR) Service Agreement.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Or</p>\r\n<ol style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot; start=&quot;2&quot;>\r\n<li>to arrange for funds to be debited from your nominated credit card according to the schedule specified below and Customer Direct Debit Request (DDR) Service Agreement.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Schedule</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong>Date of First Payment:</strong> Payment will coincide with your current Annual Renewal schedule.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong>Frequency:</strong> Once per year</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong>Payment Amount:</strong> ==membership_fee==.00 (incl. GST) for each debit</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong>Number of Payments:</strong> Continue until further notice</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>If the scheduled date is not a banking day, the debit will take place on the next banking day.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </h3>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong>Customer Direct Debit Request (DDR) Service Agreement</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>This is your Direct Debt Service Agreement with Australia Medic Alert Foundation (455996) 31 140 801 427. It explains what your obligations are when undertaking Direct Debt arrangement with us. It also details what your obligations are to us as your Direct Debt provider.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Please keep this agreement for future reference. It forms part of the terms and conditions of your Direct Debit Request (DDR) and should be read in conjunction with your DDR authorisation.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>How to Contact Us</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong>Enquiries </strong></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>You can contact us directly or alternatively contact your financial institution. These should be made at least 7 working days prior to the next scheduled drawing date. You may contact us as follows:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>Phone: 1800 88 22 22</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>Email: <a href=&quot;mailto:ddenquiries@medicalert.org.au&quot;>ddenquiries@medicalert.org.au</a></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>Mail: GPO Box 99 63, ADELAIDE SA 5001</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>All communication addressed to us should include your Membership Number.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Definitions</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong><em>Account</em></strong> means the account held at your financial institution from which we are authorised to arrange for funds to be debited.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong><em>Agreement</em></strong> means this Direct Debit Request Service Agreement between you and us.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong><em>Banking day</em></strong> means a day other than a Saturday or Sunday or a public holiday listed throughout Australia.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong><em>Debit day</em></strong> means the day that payment by you to us is due.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong><em>Debit payment</em></strong> means a particular transaction where a debit is made.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong><em>Direct debit request</em></strong> means the Direct Debit Request between us and you.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong><em>Us</em></strong> and <strong><em>we</em></strong> means Australia Medic Alert Foundation (455996) you have authorised by requesting a Direct Debit Request.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong><em>You</em></strong> means the member who signed or authorised by other means the Direct Debit Request.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><strong><em>Your financial institution</em></strong> means the financial institution nominated by you on the DDR at which the account is maintained.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Debiting your account</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>By signing a <em>Direct Debit Request</em> or by providing <em>us</em> with a valid instruction, <em>you</em> have authorised <em>us</em> to arrange for funds to be debited from your <em>account</em>. <em>You</em> should refer to the <em>Direct Debit Request</em> and this <em>agreement</em> for the terms of the arrangement between <em>us</em> and <em>you</em>.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>We</em> will only arrange for funds to be debited from <em>your account</em> as authorised in the <em>Direct Debit Request</em>.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>OR</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>We will only arrange for funds to be debited from <em>your account</em> if we have sent to the address nominated by you in the <em>Direct Debit Request</em>, a billing advice which specifies the amount payable by you to us and when it is due.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>If the <em>debit day</em> falls on a day that is not a <em>banking day</em>, we may direct your <em>financial institution</em> to debit your <em>account</em> on the following <em>banking day</em>. If you are unsure about which day your <em>account</em> has or will be debited <em>you</em> should ask your <em>financial institution</em>.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Amendments by <em>us</em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>We may vary any details of this arrangement or a Direct Debit Request at any time by giving<em> you</em> at least <strong>thirty (30) days</strong> written notice.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Amendments by <em>you</em></p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>You</em> may change, stop or defer a <em>debit payment</em>, or terminate this agreement by providing<em> us</em> with at least 7 days notification by writing to:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>GPO Box 9963</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>ADELAIDE SA 5001</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>OR</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>By telephoning <em>us</em> on 1800 88 22 22 during business hours;</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>OR</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>Arranging it through <em>your financial institution</em>, which is required to act promptly on your instructions.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Your obligations</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>It is <em>your</em> responsibility to ensure that there are sufficient clear funds available in <em>your</em> <em>account</em> to allow a <em>debit payment</em> to be made in accordance with the <em>Direct Debit Request</em>.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>If there are insufficient clear funds in your account to meet a <em>debit payment</em>:</p>\r\n<ul style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<li><em>you</em> may be charged a fee and/or interest by your <em>financial institution</em>;</li>\r\n<li><em>you</em> may also incur fees or charges imposed or incurred by <em>us</em>; and</li>\r\n<li><em>you</em> must arrange for the <em>debit payment</em> to be made by another method or arrange for sufficient clear funds to be in <em>your</em> <em>account</em> by an agreed time so that <em>we</em> can process the <em>debit payment</em>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>You</em> should check <em>your account</em> statement to verify that the amounts debited from <em>your account</em> are correct.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Dispute</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>If you believe that there has been an error in debiting your account, you should notify <em>us</em> directly on 1800 88 22 22 and confirm that notice in writing with <em>us</em> as soon as possible so that <em>we</em> can resolve your query more quickly. Alternatively <em>you</em> can take it up with <em>your financial institution</em>.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>If <em>we</em> conclude as a result of our investigations that <em>your account</em> has been incorrectly debited we will respond to <em>your</em> query by arranging for <em>your financial institution</em> to adjust <em>your account</em> (including interest and charges) accordingly. <em>We</em> will also notify <em>you</em> in writing of the amount by which <em>your account </em>has been adjusted.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>If <em>we</em> conclude as a result of our investigations that <em>your account</em> has not been incorrectly debited <em>we</em> will respond to<em> your</em> query by providing <em>you</em> with reasons and any evidence for this finding in writing.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Accounts</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>You</em> should check:</p>\r\n<ul style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<li>with <em>your financial institution</em> whether direct debiting is available from <em>your account</em> as direct debiting is not available on all accounts offered by financial institutions.</li>\r\n<li><em>your account</em> details which <em>you</em> have provided to <em>us</em> are correct by checking them against a recent account statement; and</li>\r\n<li>with <em>your financial institution</em> before completing the <em>Direct Debit Request</em> if <em>you</em> have any queries about how to complete the <em>Direct Debit Request</em>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Confidentiality</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>We</em> will keep any information (including <em>your account</em> details) in your <em>Direct Debit Request</em> confidential. <em>We</em> will make reasonable efforts to keep any such information that we have about <em>you</em> secure and to ensure that any of<em> our</em> employees or agents who have access to information about <em>you</em> do not make any unauthorised use, modification, reproduction or disclosure of that information.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>We</em> will only disclose information that we have about <em>you</em>:</p>\r\n<ul style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>\r\n<li>to the extent specifically required by law; or</li>\r\n<li>for the purposes of this agreement (including disclosing information in connection with any query or claim).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<h3 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Notice</h3>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>If <em>you</em> wish to notify <em>us</em> in writing about anything relating to this <em>agreement</em>, <em>you</em> should write to:</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>Australia Medic Alert Foundation</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>Finance Department</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>GPO Box 9963</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>ADELAIDE SA 5001</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;><em>We</em> will notify <em>you</em> by sending a notice in the ordinary post to the address <em>you</em> have given <em>us</em> in the <em>Direct Debit Request</em>.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;>Any notice will be deemed to have been received on the third <em>banking day</em> after posting.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;> </p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Terms and Conditions - Australia Medic Alert Foundation | MedicAlert','Read the terms &amp; conditions of the MedicAlert Foundation website and MedicAlert membership here.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-04 15:37:14','2018-05-24 07:34:31',NULL),(265,107,1,0,0,'Member partners','MedicAlert&rsquo;s member partners',NULL,'member-partners',1,'<p>At MedicAlert we&#039;re passionate about doing all we can to help Australians stay protected in an emergency. That&#039;s why we&#039;re proud to partner with a range of organisations across the country to ensure our members receive additional benefits with their MedicAlert membership.</p>\r\n<p>These dynamic partnerships allow us to provide more support, better value, discounted rates and other special offers, along with vital education about the importance of MedicAlert membership.</p>','<p>If your business is interested in becoming a member partner, we&#039;d love to hear from you.</p>\r\n<p><a title=&quot;Click to contact us&quot; href=&quot;/contact-us&quot;>Contact us</a> today to get started.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'MedicAlert&rsquo;s Member Partners | MedicAlert','MedicAlert Foundation is proud to partner with a range of organisations across Australia. Learn more about MedicAlert&#039;s corporate partners. ',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/corp-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:37:15','2016-10-26 05:59:28',NULL),(266,107,1,0,0,'Member partners','MedicAlert&rsquo;s member partners',NULL,'member-partners',1,'<p>At MedicAlert we&#039;re passionate about doing all we can to help Australians stay protected in an emergency. That&#039;s why we&#039;re proud to partner with a range of organisations across the country to ensure our members receive additional benefits with their MedicAlert membership.</p>\r\n<p>These dynamic partnerships allow us to provide more support, better value, discounted rates and other special offers, along with vital education about the importance of MedicAlert membership.</p>','<p>If your business is interested in becoming a member partner, we&#039;d love to hear from you.</p>\r\n<p><a title=&quot;Click to contact us&quot; href=&quot;/contact-us&quot;>Contact us</a> today to get started.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'MedicAlert&rsquo;s member partners - we partner with a range of organisations across the country',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/corp-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:37:15','2018-01-29 02:38:12','2018-01-29 13:08:12'),(267,706,10,1,6,'Chain bracelets',NULL,NULL,'chain-bracelets',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'MedicAlert Chain Bracelets | MedicAlert','Browse our range of medical alert chain bracelets.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1,'2016-10-24 14:28:36','2016-10-26 05:28:37',NULL),(268,95,1,0,0,'Who needs membership','Who needs membership?',NULL,'who-needs-membership',1,'<p>Please click any of the categories below to see a more comprehensive list of medical conditions, allergies and special needs that we help cover in an emergency.</p>','<p>MedicAlert membership is also ideal for organ donors, travellers, identification assistance, or those who want to store their personal and health records.</p>\r\n<p>Don&#039;t wait until it&#039;s too late. Become a MedicAlert member today.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Who needs a MedicAlert membership',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/who-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:18:42','2016-10-24 05:22:51','2016-10-24 15:52:50'),(269,95,1,0,0,'Who needs membership','Who needs membership?',NULL,'who-needs-membership',1,'<p>Please click any of the categories below to see a more comprehensive list of medical conditions, allergies and special needs that we help cover in an emergency.</p>','<p>MedicAlert membership is also ideal for organ donors, travellers, identification assistance, or those who want to store their personal and health records.</p>\r\n<p>Don&#039;t wait until it&#039;s too late. Become a MedicAlert member today.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Who needs a MedicAlert membership',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/who-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:18:42','2016-10-24 05:24:44','2016-10-24 15:54:44'),(270,95,1,0,0,'Who needs membership','Who needs membership?',NULL,'who-needs-membership',1,'<p>Please click any of the categories below to see a more comprehensive list of medical conditions, allergies and special needs that we help cover in an emergency.</p>','<p>MedicAlert membership is also ideal for organ donors, travellers, identification assistance, or those who want to store their personal and health records.</p>\r\n<p>Don&#039;t wait until it&#039;s too late. Become a MedicAlert member today.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Who needs a MedicAlert membership',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/who-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:18:42','2016-10-24 05:24:44','2016-10-24 15:54:44'),(271,105,1,0,0,'Refer your patients','One piece of advice could help save your clients&#039; life',NULL,'refer-your-patients',0,'<p>MedicAlert<sup>&reg;</sup> Foundation provides Australia&#039;s most trusted and recognised medical ID. By referring your clients to become a member, you can help to ensure they&#039;re protected in an emergency.</p>','<h3>It&#039;s easy to refer your clients</h3>\r\n<p> </p>','<p>As a not-for-profit organisation, we rely on your support to help us spread the word about our service. By simply telling your clients and colleagues about the importance of MedicAlert Foundation in an emergency, you&#039;re doing your part to help protect all Australians living with medical conditions.</p>\r\n<p>Your clients can become a member by visiting <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au&quot;>medicalert.org.au</a> or calling <a href=&quot;tel://1800 88 2222&quot;>1800 88 2222</a>.</p>','<h3>Protection when seconds count</h3>\r\n<p>Our national Board of Directors volunteer their time to ensure we can provide the best possible service for our members</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert members wear the genuine MedicAlert medical ID. Emergency services and medical personnel are trained to look for our internationally recognised IDs. Each ID provides a 24/7 emergency hotline number which first responders can call to access clients&#039; vital medical files. By having this information at hand, they can make a more accurate diagnosis and provide the fastest and most effective treatment when seconds count.</p>\r\n<p>Order your FREE sample medical ID by emailing <a href=&quot;mailto:kreek@medicalert.org.au&quot;>marketing@medicalert.org.au</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Refer your patients to MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/refer-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:36:08','2016-10-24 05:43:02','2016-10-24 16:13:02'),(272,105,1,0,0,'Refer your patients','One piece of advice could help save your clients&#039; life',NULL,'refer-your-patients',0,'<p>MedicAlert<sup>&reg;</sup> Foundation provides Australia&#039;s most trusted and recognised medical ID. By referring your clients to become a member, you can help to ensure they&#039;re protected in an emergency.</p>','<h3>It&#039;s easy to refer your clients</h3>\r\n<p> </p>','<p>As a not-for-profit organisation, we rely on your support to help us spread the word about our service. By simply telling your clients and colleagues about the importance of MedicAlert Foundation in an emergency, you&#039;re doing your part to help protect all Australians living with medical conditions.</p>\r\n<p>Your clients can become a member by visiting <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au&quot;>medicalert.org.au</a> or calling <a href=&quot;tel://1800 88 2222&quot;>1800 88 2222</a>.</p>','<h3>Protection when seconds count</h3>\r\n<p>Our national Board of Directors volunteer their time to ensure we can provide the best possible service for our members</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert members wear the genuine MedicAlert medical ID. Emergency services and medical personnel are trained to look for our internationally recognised IDs. Each ID provides a 24/7 emergency hotline number which first responders can call to access clients&#039; vital medical files. By having this information at hand, they can make a more accurate diagnosis and provide the fastest and most effective treatment when seconds count.</p>\r\n<p>Order your FREE sample medical ID by emailing <a href=&quot;mailto:marketing@medicalert.org.au&quot;>marketing@medicalert.org.au</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Refer your patients to MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/refer-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:36:08','2016-10-24 05:43:02','2016-10-24 16:13:02'),(273,105,1,0,0,'Refer your patients','MedicAlert protects you and your patients 24/7',NULL,'refer-your-patients',0,'<p>MedicAlert is more than Australia&rsquo;s most trusted ID in an emergency. It also provides an Emergency Response Service that GPs like you can access day or night, with vital information about a patient&rsquo;s conditions, allergies, medications and medical history.</p>\r\n<p>The benefits include:</p>\r\n<ul id=&quot;refer-list&quot; style=&quot;list-style-position: inside; padding-left: 30px;&quot;>\r\n<li>Assistance with accurate diagnosis</li>\r\n<li>Understanding and determining a patient&#039;s special needs</li>\r\n<li>Accessing medication and allergy information</li>\r\n<li>Easier, more accurate medication management</li>\r\n<li>Greater peace of mind for you and your patient</li>\r\n</ul>','<h3>Why refer patients to MedicAlert?</h3>\r\n<p class=&quot;p1&quot;><span class=&quot;s1&quot;>When you refer a patient to MedicAlert, you&rsquo;re protecting them 24/7, not just in an emergency. A MedicAlert membership provides patients with unlimited wallet cards containing important information about medical conditions, allergies and special needs, an electronic health record to store more detail on conditions, medications, doctor and emergency contacts, and our life saving 24/7 Emergency Response Service with fully trained response team who can access this record for emergency personnel and healthcare professionals. One piece of advice could save a patient&rsquo;s life.</span></p>','<p>As a not-for-profit organisation, we rely on your support to help us spread the word about our service. By simply telling your patients and colleagues about the importance of MedicAlert Foundation, you&#039;re doing your part to help protect all Australians living with medical conditions.</p>\r\n<p>Your patient can become a member by visiting <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au&quot;>medicalert.org.au</a> or calling <a href=&quot;tel://1800 88 2222&quot;>1800 88 2222</a>.</p>','<h3>Protection when seconds count</h3>\r\n<p class=&quot;p1&quot;><span class=&quot;s1&quot;>MedicAlert members wear the genuine MedicAlert ID. Emergency personnel and healthcare professionals are trained to look for our internationally recognised IDs. Each ID is upported by a 24/7 Emergency Response Service number, which first responders can also call to access clients&#039; vital health and personal information. By having this information at hand, they can make a more accurate diagnosis and provide the fastest and most effective treatment when seconds count.</span></p>\r\n<p class=&quot;p1&quot;><span class=&quot;s1&quot;>If you would like a sample ID, please email <a href=&quot;mailto:marketing@medicalert.org.au&quot;><span class=&quot;s2&quot;><strong>marketing@medicalert.org.au</strong></span></a> who will arrange for this to be sent to you.</span></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,99,'Refer your patients to MedicAlert Foundation | MedicAlert','Refer your patients to join MedicAlert Foundation and help them stay protected in a medical emergency. ',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/refer-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:36:08','2018-02-06 01:26:24',NULL),(274,95,1,0,0,'Who needs membership','Who needs membership?',NULL,'who-needs-membership',1,'<p>Please click any of the categories below to see a more comprehensive list of medical conditions, allergies and special needs that we help cover in an emergency.</p>','<p>MedicAlert membership is also ideal for organ donors, travellers, identification assistance, or those who want to store their personal and health records.</p>\r\n<p>Don&#039;t wait until it&#039;s too late. Become a MedicAlert member today.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Who needs a MedicAlert membership | MedicAlert','See a comprehensive list of medical conditions, allergies and special needs that we help cover in an emergency.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/who-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:18:42','2016-10-26 05:42:51',NULL),(275,2,1,0,0,'About MedicAlert Foundation','How MedicAlert Foundation makes a difference',NULL,'about-medicalert-foundation',1,'<p><br />At MedicAlert Foundation we are dedicated to helping our members feel safe knowing they&rsquo;re protected in an emergency.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>For over 45 years, our trusted organisation has been protecting Australians in emergency situations, allowing emergency services or healthcare professionals to quickly identify their medical needs and provide the fastest, most effective treatment when seconds count. As part of our service, we invest in vital training programs for healthcare professionals each year, ensuring they are aware that they should always check for MedicAlert identification jewellery.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Internationally recognised and recommended by the World Health Organisation and World Allergy Organisation, the genuine MedicAlert medical ID is proudly worn by a global community of more than four million people from around 40 different countries.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>We are passionate about supporting the wellbeing of our members and work to deliver innovative, reliable and cost-effective products and services that meet their ongoing needs.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Did you know that MedicAlert receives no government funding? As a not-for-profit organisation, we rely on the support of donations so we can continue to protect the thousands of Australians living with medical conditions and keep membership fees to a minimum. If you&rsquo;d like to make a donation, no matter how big or small, visit our <a href=&quot;/donate&quot;>donations page</a>.</p>','<p>The genuine MedicAlert medical ID has been protecting members worldwide since 1953. Our Foundation was first founded by Dr Marion Collins in California, as a way to alert medical personnel to his daughter&rsquo;s potentially fatal anaphylaxis. MedicAlert was introduced into Australia by Rotary and St John Council in 1971, and a national office in Adelaide was established to provide comprehensive support to all members, which still operates today.</p>\r\n<p>As Australia&rsquo;s only not-for-profit organisation of its kind, today MedicAlert Foundation remains dedicated to providing peace of mind to hundreds of thousands of people across Australia - and the world - living with medical conditions.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'About MedicAlert Foundation in Australia | MedicAlert','About MedicAlert Foundation - Australia&#039;s only not-for-profit organisation dedicated to providing a 24/7 personal medical emergency information and identification service.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/MedicAlert%20staff%20-%20image.jpg','/uploads/about-img.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-04 15:23:54','2018-03-21 04:52:51',NULL),(276,2,1,0,0,'About MedicAlert Foundation','How MedicAlert Foundation makes a difference',NULL,'about-medicalert-foundation',1,'<p><br />At MedicAlert Foundation we are dedicated to helping our members feel safe knowing they&rsquo;re protected in an emergency.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>For over 45 years, our trusted organisation has been protecting Australians in emergency situations, allowing emergency services or healthcare professionals to quickly identify their medical needs and provide the fastest, most effective treatment when seconds count. As part of our service, we invest in vital training programs for healthcare professionals each year, ensuring they are aware that they should always check for MedicAlert identification jewellery.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Internationally recognised and recommended by the World Health Organisation and World Allergy Organisation, the genuine MedicAlert medical ID is proudly worn by a global community of more than four million people from around 40 different countries.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>We are passionate about supporting the wellbeing of our members and work to deliver innovative, reliable and cost-effective products and services that meet their ongoing needs.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Did you know that MedicAlert receives no government funding? As a not-for-profit organisation, we rely on the support of donations so we can continue to protect the thousands of Australians living with medical conditions and keep membership fees to a minimum. If you&rsquo;d like to make a donation, no matter how big or small, visit our <a href=&quot;/donate&quot;>donations page</a>.</p>','<p>The genuine MedicAlert medical ID has been protecting members worldwide since 1953. Our Foundation was first founded by Dr Marion Collins in California, as a way to alert medical personnel to his daughter&rsquo;s potentially fatal anaphylaxis. MedicAlert was introduced into Australia by Rotary and St John Council in 1971, and a national office in Adelaide was established to provide comprehensive support to all members, which still operates today.</p>\r\n<p>As Australia&rsquo;s only not-for-profit organisation of its kind, today MedicAlert Foundation remains dedicated to providing peace of mind to hundreds of thousands of people across Australia - and the world - living with medical conditions.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'About MedicAlert Foundation - Australia&#039;s only not-for-profit organisation dedicated to providing a 24/7 personal medical emergency information and identification service',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/MedicAlert%20staff%20-%20image.jpg','/uploads/about-img.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-04 15:23:54','2017-12-04 23:44:52','2017-12-05 10:14:52'),(277,9,1,0,0,'My dashboard',NULL,NULL,'my-account',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,1,0,NULL,99,'Welcome to My Dashboard | MedicAlert ','Welcome to the MedicAlert Members&#039; Area. View your dashboard and make sure your membership is up to date. \r\n',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,'2016-07-04 15:36:12','2018-07-06 01:19:21',NULL),(278,105,1,0,0,'Refer your patients','One piece of advice could help save your clients&#039; life',NULL,'refer-your-patients',0,'<p>MedicAlert<sup>&reg;</sup> Foundation provides Australia&#039;s most trusted and recognised medical ID. By referring your clients to become a member, you can help to ensure they&#039;re protected in an emergency.</p>','<h3>It&#039;s easy to refer your clients</h3>\r\n<p> </p>','<p>As a not-for-profit organisation, we rely on your support to help us spread the word about our service. By simply telling your clients and colleagues about the importance of MedicAlert Foundation in an emergency, you&#039;re doing your part to help protect all Australians living with medical conditions.</p>\r\n<p>Your clients can become a member by visiting <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au&quot;>medicalert.org.au</a> or calling <a href=&quot;tel://1800 88 2222&quot;>1800 88 2222</a>.</p>','<h3>Protection when seconds count</h3>\r\n<p>Our national Board of Directors volunteer their time to ensure we can provide the best possible service for our members</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert members wear the genuine MedicAlert medical ID. Emergency services and medical personnel are trained to look for our internationally recognised IDs. Each ID provides a 24/7 emergency hotline number which first responders can call to access clients&#039; vital medical files. By having this information at hand, they can make a more accurate diagnosis and provide the fastest and most effective treatment when seconds count.</p>\r\n<p>Order your FREE sample medical ID by emailing <a href=&quot;mailto:marketing@medicalert.org.au&quot;>marketing@medicalert.org.au</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'Refer your patients to MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/refer-banner.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-08-02 06:36:08','2018-02-06 01:29:51','2018-02-06 11:59:51'),(279,708,2,0,17,'Celebrating our 45th Birthday with you!',NULL,NULL,'celebrating-our-45th-birthday-with-you',0,NULL,'<p>To understand just how far the Australia Medic Alert Foundation of Australia has come since it was introduced into Australia in 1971 by Rotary and St John Council, you might like to consider that in the same year the VCR, email and personal computers were only just being invented.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>At the time, databases were mostly kept in filing cabinets and laser engraved jewellery and online membership services were still decades away. But from these humble beginnings, where our &lsquo;product range&rsquo; included one stainless steel option, we&rsquo;ve now grown to offer a suite of more trendy and fashionable yet distinctly recognisable bracelets, necklaces and wristbands made from leather, gold, gemstones, silicone, silver, pearls and more.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>While we couldn&rsquo;t be more proud of our range of products, services and technical advancements, such as our brand new website (which will be launched very soon), it is still the stories of how this progress actually helps our members that truly matters. In fact, as we&rsquo;ve spent time reflecting on just how far we have come in the last 45 years, there is one thing that stands out above all others, and that is the 365,000 mothers, fathers, brothers, sisters, daughters and sons we have supported, protected and saved. The membership records generated by MedicAlert which can be accessed by emergency personnel and our recognised products has saved thousands of lives.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>People like Kurt Byers, who suffered anaphylaxis at a work function as a result of his severe dairy allergy. The then 35-year-old explained that he might not be here today if not for what happened next.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I was struggling to speak and couldn&rsquo;t tell hospital staff what was wrong with me. While they knew it was some sort of reaction they didn&rsquo;t know why &ndash; but I was able to show them my MedicAlert and they immediately gave me the right treatment for my condition,&rdquo; said Kurt.  </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>From allergies to some of the rarest conditions, MedicAlert has always prided itself on protecting Australians from any and every condition under the sun. Take West Australian mum Fiona Smith for example. Since she was diagnosed with &lsquo;von Willebrand&rsquo; - a rare bleeding disorder she discovered while giving birth to her son &ndash; Fiona says MedicAlert has helped her to escape two very close calls.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I have been rushed to hospital twice and on both occasions my MedicAlert membership has let the ambulance crew know immediately so they administer the right treatment,&rdquo; said Fiona.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>But it&rsquo;s not only the lives we&rsquo;ve saved and protected, it&rsquo;s also the lives we&rsquo;ve transformed. Take for instance Peter Richards, a Parkinson&rsquo;s sufferer who&rsquo;d undergone surgery that meant he had metal electrodes implanted in his head and a battery pack in his chest. As an avid traveller, Peter was heart broken after his operation, as he felt his days of exploring the world might be numbered. But thanks to the support from our friendly staff that fear of being trapped was soon replaced with jubilation.   </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;In the wrong situation my implants could pose significant health risks, so it&rsquo;s great to have that peace of mind that comes with wearing a MedicAlert medical ID. And actually, it&rsquo;s allowed us to travel to Asia with confidence, not once or twice, but five times since I had the surgery.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>So while we&rsquo;re proud to boast an incredible array of products and services that utilise the very latest technology, our greatest achievement will always be allowing our members to live long, productive and independent lives.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>So hip, hip, hooray and here&rsquo;s to another 45 years of service, innovation and keeping you safe!!!</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>OUR SPECIAL OFFER &ndash; As you&rsquo;ve just read, this October marks MedicAlert Foundation&#039;s 45th birthday in Australia, so to celebrate this milestone, we&#039;re giving away a free limited edition MedicAlert key ring when you purchase any new medical ID during the month of October. Hurry, there is only a few days left to receive this special offer. Visit <a href=&quot;http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fbit.ly%2F20kMYtc&amp;h=nAQFx8EGRAQElhPx1sI_R0p0IPuaX6OwjNcIEp9hV97iuQA&amp;enc=AZN0hZoHL1SLapTyLHBjlB1mL2S5-QCi7YfXAOl3fYWCJZbyH6VoHQpy19C1tARdMu5zJrcS7cjxixETvY_AD-Nsdw-vjtLVWPhaOicvXFW0gPryX21ZrTZYGAntb8wxmR1a1ffTSUk3Lr1xO-XHMAjXS7UWSi42LQJcAyuRKyhzS_SPPzqdL7nVtgcH1S_CLZfeDLCPUx4InpR4ZlZr0zV0&amp;s=1&quot;>http://bit.ly/20kMYtc</a> to check out our range.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Celebrating our 45th Birthday with you!',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2016-10-28','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-25 09:59:16','2018-01-31 07:13:08','2016-11-04 14:41:14'),(280,709,2,0,17,'Make your wishes known before it&rsquo;s too late',NULL,NULL,'make-your-wishes-known-before-itandrsquos-too-late',0,NULL,'<p>Advanced Care Directives (ACD&rsquo;s) are important documents that represent you and your wishes when you can no longer make decisions due to mental impairment or a lack of consciousness resulting from illness or accident. However, a practical problem inherent in these paper based documents is that they are often not available to your loved ones or doctors at times when you need them most, such as when you arrive in a hospital emergency department. This of course, may lead to treatment being provided to you that does not align with your wishes.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>To solve this problem, you may wish to utilise MedicAlert&rsquo;s <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/Advance_Care_Directive_Management_Service&quot;>Advance Care Directive Management Service</a>, which means all your written Advance Care Directives will be safely and confidentially stored, communicated, and made available when and where they are needed.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>This service, exclusive to members, includes:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Securely holding your Advance Care Directive(s)</li>\r\n<li>Engraving on your medical ID stating you have an Advance Care Directive</li>\r\n<li>An emergency wallet card stating you have an Advance Care Directive on file</li>\r\n<li>24/7 Emergency Response Service service for the medical team to access the directive</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>What exactly is an Advance Care Directive (ACD)?</strong></p>\r\n<p>An Advance Care Directive is a written document, intended to apply to future periods of impaired decision-making capacity, which provides a legal means for a competent adult to instruct a Substitute Decision Maker and/or to record preferences for future health and personal care. ACDs are not clinical care or treatment plans, but clinical care or treatment plans can and should be informed by ACDs. It is important to note that verbally communicated instructions and values also hold weight.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>ACDs can take many forms, and laws regarding <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/Advance_Care_Planning_Resources&quot;>ACDs are different in each state</a>. You should be aware of the laws in your state prior to creating your advance directive.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Although often about end-of-life care (the last 12 months) or terminal care (the last days to weeks of life), a person may also wish to complete an ACD for other reasons (for example, there may be some treatment the patient would never wish to receive) or simply for peace of mind in case of unexpected illness or injury.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>Should I have an Advance Care Directive?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Yes. By creating an Advanced Care Directive, you are making your preferences about medical care known before you&rsquo;re faced with a serious injury or illness. Even if you are in good health, you should consider having an ACD. An accident or serious illness can happen suddenly, and if you already have a signed ACD, your wishes are more likely to be followed.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>Upload Your Advance Care Directive</strong></p>\r\n<p>Secure and safe storage of Advanced Health Care Directives is available to <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/Membership/Membership_Benefits&quot;>members of MedicAlert</a>. If you are a member of the Foundation you can upload your Advanced Health Care Directive via the Members&#039; Area of the website and clicking on the red Health Care Directive button. Alternatively give us a call on 1800 88 22 22 to discuss safe and secure storage of your Advanced Health Care Directive.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Make your wishes known before it&rsquo;s too late',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2016-10-28','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-25 10:04:48','2018-01-31 07:13:08',NULL),(281,710,2,0,17,'Worthy Winner Claims Fitness Pack ',NULL,NULL,'worthy-winner-claims-fitness-pack-',0,NULL,'<p>While the person who walked away with our &lsquo;Spring Fitness Pack&rsquo; valued at $300 wishes to remain anonymous, we can tell you that thankfully they love their fitness and outdoor activities, which means they&rsquo;ll have no trouble utilising their new Garmin VivoFit 3, MedicAlert wristband tags, plus a backpack, towel and water bottle, all of which was offered in the prize pack.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>The NSW resident said they became a member of MedicAlert around three years ago when they were diagnosed with type 1 diabetes. Like all responsible members they said they always wear their MedicAlert jewellery as they go on their often long and arduous bicycle rides and runs.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;When travelling by myself I always wear my MedicAlert as well, as it gives me piece of mind,&rdquo; they said.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Stay tuned for more great offers and promotions via our newsletter and <a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/AustraliaMedicAlertFoundation/?fref=ts&quot;>Facebook page</a>.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Worthy Winner Claims Fitness Pack ',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2016-10-28','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-25 10:05:52','2018-01-31 07:13:08',NULL),(282,712,2,0,17,'Ab Fab Veggie Frittata',NULL,NULL,'ab-fab-veggie-frittata',0,NULL,'<p>This vegetable frittata is an amazing way to get the kids (and adults) eating all their veggies in a tasty and visually stunning way that&rsquo;s sure to impress anyone and everyone.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Serves 4</p>\r\n<p>Cooking and preparation time: 1 hour</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>Ingredients</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>10-12 eggs</li>\r\n<li>1/4 cup almond milk (or milk of your choice)</li>\r\n<li>1 leek, halved length ways and thinly sliced</li>\r\n<li>2 large swiss mushroom, roughly chopped</li>\r\n<li>1 baby bok choy, roughly chopped (separating stalk from leafy greens)</li>\r\n<li>1 zucchini, grated</li>\r\n<li>2 red capsicum, seeds and stalk removed, each cut length ways into 4-6 flattish pieces</li>\r\n<li>2 cups butternut pumpkin, cubed</li>\r\n<li>1-2 Tb fresh flat leaf parsley, chopped</li>\r\n<li>1 Tb mixed dried herbs (oregano, basil, parsley)</li>\r\n<li>1 garlic clove, crushed</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tsp salt</li>\r\n<li>1/4 tsp ground black pepper</li>\r\n<li> Olive oil for cooking</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>Instructions</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Set the oven to a high grill temperature. Place the capsicum on a baking tray, skin side up and slide into the grill. Cook until the skin is well charred and begins to bubble. This will allow the skin to easily peel off. Remove from oven and allow the capsicum to cool before removing skin carefully. Slice the capsicum into thin strips and set aside.</li>\r\n<li>Preheat oven to 250 degrees Celsius.</li>\r\n<li>Place pumpkin on a lined baking tray drizzled with a little oil. Toss with hands to evenly coat and place in oven to bake until just softening. Remove tray from oven and reduce the temperature to 180 degrees. Set pumpkin aside.</li>\r\n<li>Heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on medium temperature. Add the leek and bok choy stalk and cook for several minutes until the leek begins to soften then add in the garlic. Continue cooking for a further few minutes before adding the mushroom and grated zucchini. Allow to cook for approximately a further 5 minutes. Toss through remaining bok choy leaves while still warm. Set aside with other cooked veggies.</li>\r\n<li>Whisk the eggs, milk, herbs, salt and pepper in a large bowl.</li>\r\n<li>Line a large baking dish with paper then arrange all the vegetables evenly so that they are well distributed and cover the bottom off the dish. Pour over the egg mixture evenly. Place baking dish in the oven for approximately 40 minutes or until cooked through.</li>\r\n<li>Remove from oven and allow to cool 5-10 minutes before slicing to serve.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Find this recipe and so much other health related news, recipes and ideas on <a href=&quot;http://www.findyourfeed.com.au/&quot;>Find Your Feed</a>.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Ab Fab Veggie Frittata',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2016-10-28','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-25 10:07:08','2018-01-31 07:13:08',NULL),(283,713,10,1,6,'Stainless Steel',NULL,NULL,'stainless-steel',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'MedicAlert Stainless Steel Range - Stainless Steel Medical IDs | MedicAlert','Browse MedicAlert&reg;  stainless steel medical alert bracelets, necklaces, pendants and other medical ID stainless steel jewellery.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1,'2016-10-25 10:13:34','2016-10-26 05:24:03',NULL),(286,757,2,0,17,'Welcome to our new website!',NULL,NULL,'welcome-to-our-new-website',0,NULL,'<p>In October, MedicAlert&reg; introduced a new responsive website that&rsquo;s accessible on a range of devices, including mobile, desktop computer, tablet or iPad. Designed specifically for our members, we&rsquo;ve introduced some new features and improved some of our existing features to better suit you, including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A new look Members Area page, now called &lsquo;My Membership&rsquo; page that acts as a personal membership dashboard and provides you with access to quick renew features.</li>\r\n<li>The option to save your favourite jewellery pieces to your wishlist for later when logged in as a member.</li>\r\n<li>Refer a friend straight from our website. This is a quick and easy way to introduce a friend or family member you care about to MedicAlert.</li>\r\n<li>Automatically renew your annual membership online. Your details will be securely stored by your bank and re-debited when renewal is due, ensuring you&rsquo;re always protected in an emergency.</li>\r\n<li>An improved shopping process with dynamic and responsive product filtering, to make finding the product you&rsquo;re looking for easier.</li>\r\n<li>Our new look shopping cart that makes purchasing products a more streamlined and efficient process.</li>\r\n<li>The ability to order a gift certificate straight from our website. With the option to set your own value, or choose a standard amount, you no longer have to call us to order a gift certificate.</li>\r\n<li>More great offers added to our list of exclusive MedicAlert <a href=&quot;/member-partners&quot;>Members Benefits</a> including Bupa and Thomas Farms</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Since 1971, we&rsquo;ve been protecting thousands of members when seconds count in an emergency. MedicAlert is always looking at ways to improve the service of 24/7 protection to our members, which includes delivering a more responsive and helpful website. We hope you find the website more user-friendly and look forward to continuing to deliver peace of mind. For more information head to <a href=&quot;http://www.medicalert.org.au&quot;>www.medicalert.org.au</a>.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/news-and-resources/newsletter/new-site.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;new-site.jpg (56 KB)&quot; width=&quot;690&quot; height=&quot;366&quot; /></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Welcome to our new website!',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2016-10-28','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-26 16:06:26','2018-01-31 07:13:08',NULL),(287,758,6,0,0,'New Features',NULL,NULL,'new-features',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'New Features','New Features',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-31 15:46:47','2016-10-31 05:19:04',NULL),(288,708,2,0,17,'Celebrating our 45th Birthday with you!',NULL,NULL,'celebrating-our-45th-birthday-with-you',0,NULL,'<p>To understand just how far the Australia Medic Alert Foundation of Australia has come since it was introduced into Australia in 1971 by Rotary and St John Council, you might like to consider that in the same year the VCR, email and personal computers were only just being invented.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>At the time, databases were mostly kept in filing cabinets and laser engraved jewellery and online membership services were still decades away. But from these humble beginnings, where our &lsquo;product range&rsquo; included one stainless steel option, we&rsquo;ve now grown to offer a suite of more trendy and fashionable yet distinctly recognisable bracelets, necklaces and wristbands made from leather, gold, gemstones, silicone, silver, pearls and more.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>While we couldn&rsquo;t be more proud of our range of products, services and technical advancements, such as our brand new website (which will be launched very soon), it is still the stories of how this progress actually helps our members that truly matters. In fact, as we&rsquo;ve spent time reflecting on just how far we have come in the last 45 years, there is one thing that stands out above all others, and that is the 365,000 mothers, fathers, brothers, sisters, daughters and sons we have supported, protected and saved. The membership records generated by MedicAlert which can be accessed by emergency personnel and our recognised products has saved thousands of lives.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>People like Kurt Byers, who suffered anaphylaxis at a work function as a result of his severe dairy allergy. The then 35-year-old explained that he might not be here today if not for what happened next.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I was struggling to speak and couldn&rsquo;t tell hospital staff what was wrong with me. While they knew it was some sort of reaction they didn&rsquo;t know why &ndash; but I was able to show them my MedicAlert and they immediately gave me the right treatment for my condition,&rdquo; said Kurt.  </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>From allergies to some of the rarest conditions, MedicAlert has always prided itself on protecting Australians from any and every condition under the sun. Take West Australian mum Fiona Smith for example. Since she was diagnosed with &lsquo;von Willebrand&rsquo; - a rare bleeding disorder she discovered while giving birth to her son &ndash; Fiona says MedicAlert has helped her to escape two very close calls.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I have been rushed to hospital twice and on both occasions my MedicAlert membership has let the ambulance crew know immediately so they administer the right treatment,&rdquo; said Fiona.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>But it&rsquo;s not only the lives we&rsquo;ve saved and protected, it&rsquo;s also the lives we&rsquo;ve transformed. Take for instance Peter Richards, a Parkinson&rsquo;s sufferer who&rsquo;d undergone surgery that meant he had metal electrodes implanted in his head and a battery pack in his chest. As an avid traveller, Peter was heart broken after his operation, as he felt his days of exploring the world might be numbered. But thanks to the support from our friendly staff that fear of being trapped was soon replaced with jubilation.   </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;In the wrong situation my implants could pose significant health risks, so it&rsquo;s great to have that peace of mind that comes with wearing a MedicAlert medical ID. And actually, it&rsquo;s allowed us to travel to Asia with confidence, not once or twice, but five times since I had the surgery.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>So while we&rsquo;re proud to boast an incredible array of products and services that utilise the very latest technology, our greatest achievement will always be allowing our members to live long, productive and independent lives.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>So hip, hip, hooray and here&rsquo;s to another 45 years of service, innovation and keeping you safe!!!</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>OUR SPECIAL OFFER &ndash; As you&rsquo;ve just read, this October marks MedicAlert Foundation&#039;s 45th birthday in Australia, so to celebrate this milestone, we&#039;re giving away a free limited edition MedicAlert key ring when you purchase any new medical ID during the month of October. Hurry, there is only a few days left to receive this special offer. Visit <a href=&quot;http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fbit.ly%2F20kMYtc&amp;h=nAQFx8EGRAQElhPx1sI_R0p0IPuaX6OwjNcIEp9hV97iuQA&amp;enc=AZN0hZoHL1SLapTyLHBjlB1mL2S5-QCi7YfXAOl3fYWCJZbyH6VoHQpy19C1tARdMu5zJrcS7cjxixETvY_AD-Nsdw-vjtLVWPhaOicvXFW0gPryX21ZrTZYGAntb8wxmR1a1ffTSUk3Lr1xO-XHMAjXS7UWSi42LQJcAyuRKyhzS_SPPzqdL7nVtgcH1S_CLZfeDLCPUx4InpR4ZlZr0zV0&amp;s=1&quot;>http://bit.ly/20kMYtc</a> to check out our range.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Celebrating our 45th Birthday with you!',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/news-and-resources/images/medic-alert-logo.jpg',NULL,NULL,'2016-10-28','2020-12-31',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-10-25 09:59:16','2018-01-31 07:13:08','2016-11-04 14:41:14'),(289,708,2,0,17,'Celebrating our 45th Birthday with you!',NULL,NULL,'celebrating-our-45th-birthday-with-you',0,NULL,'<p>To understand just how far the Australia Medic Alert Foundation of Australia has come since it was introduced into Australia in 1971 by Rotary and St John Council, you might like to consider that in the same year the VCR, email and personal computers were only just being invented.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>At the time, databases were mostly kept in filing cabinets and laser engraved jewellery and online membership services were still decades away. But from these humble beginnings, where our &lsquo;product range&rsquo; included one stainless steel option, we&rsquo;ve now grown to offer a suite of more trendy and fashionable yet distinctly recognisable bracelets, necklaces and wristbands made from leather, gold, gemstones, silicone, silver, pearls and more.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>While we couldn&rsquo;t be more proud of our range of products, services and technical advancements, such as our brand new website (which will be launched very soon), it is still the stories of how this progress actually helps