d recognised provider of IDs and our 24/7 Emergency Response Service, the MedicAlert Foundation can provide you and your loved ones with the support you need.</p>','<h2>Christmas Party for Special Children offer includes:</h2>\r\n<p>A one year MedicAlert<sup>&reg;</sup> membership and your choice of one of the MedicAlert IDs shown below with free postage.</p>\r\n<p>*Offer valued at up to $123</p>\r\n<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/1.png&quot; alt=&quot;Medical ID&quot; />\r\n<div class=&quot;cost-text&quot;>MedicAlert ID</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/2.png&quot; alt=&quot;Medical ID&quot; />\r\n<div class=&quot;cost-text&quot;>Membership</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/3.png&quot; alt=&quot;Medical ID&quot; />\r\n<div class=&quot;cost-text&quot;>Postage</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','<p>*Selected products only. Price includes standard postage and handling and an Australia MedicAlert Foundation product warranty. Offer extended to Christmas Party for Special Children attendees only and may be subject to authentication.</p>',NULL,NULL,788,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'CPSC Benevolent program','Free 1 year MedicAlert membership and choice of a selected MedicAlert ID for attendees of the 2017 Christmas Party for Special Children.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/Header%20images/christmas-party-landing-page-image-3.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2017-11-15 15:04:28','2017-11-16 00:23:59',NULL),(327,789,6,0,0,'CPSC Benevolent program','MedicAlert&#039;s Benevolent Program',NULL,'cpsc-benevolent-program',0,'<div>\r\n<h1><span class=&quot;highlight&quot;>CHRISTMAS PARTY FOR<br /></span>SPECIAL CHILDREN<br />BENEVOLENT PROGRAM</h1>\r\n<span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;>Free 1 year MedicAlert<sup>&reg;</sup> membership</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;>and choice of a selected MedicAlert ID </span></div>\r\n<div><span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;>for HAE Australasia members.</span></div>\r\n<p><a class=&quot;btn btn-red&quot; title=&quot;Benefits of membership&quot; href=&quot;#products&quot;>Choose product</a></p>','<p>MedicAlert<sup>&reg;</sup> Foundation is passionate about making sure support is available to all Australians who are living with a medical condition. The benevolent program is an important initiative that gives people with special circumstances the opportunity to apply for free one-year MedicAlert membership and a MedicAlert ID.</p>\r\n<p>A MedicAlert membership can help family, friends, work colleagues or healthcare professionals quickly recognise your medical conditions in the case of an emergency. The chosen MedicAlert ID will be personalised to you and contain an engraving of your membership number, key medical information and the 24/7 Emergency Response Service number for easy access by healthcare professionals. When a first responder calls our life-saving Emergency Response Service, they&rsquo;re provided with information about a patients personal and health information, ensuring they&rsquo;re treated quickly and efficiently and returned home safely to their loved ones.</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert members gain access to unlimited updates to membership cards listing their conditions, an electronic health record that they can easily update with any new or relevant medical information and a range of exclusive member benefits.</p>\r\n<p>As Australia&rsquo;s most trusted and recognised provider of our 24/7 emergency response service and medical IDs, the MedicAlert Foundation can provide you and your loved ones with full support in an emergency.</p>','<h2>HAE Australasia member offer includes:</h2>\r\n<p>A one year MedicAlert<sup>&reg;</sup> membership and your choice of one of the MedicAlert IDs shown below with free postage.</p>\r\n<p>*Offer valued at up to $123</p>\r\n<div class=&quot;row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/1.png&quot; alt=&quot;Medical ID&quot; />\r\n<div class=&quot;cost-text&quot;>MedicAlert ID</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/2.png&quot; alt=&quot;Medical ID&quot; />\r\n<div class=&quot;cost-text&quot;>Membership</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-4 text-center&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/3.png&quot; alt=&quot;Medical ID&quot; />\r\n<div class=&quot;cost-text&quot;>Postage</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','<p>*Offer valid until 30/06/18. Selected products only. Price includes standard postage and handling and a standard Australia MedicAlert Foundation product warranty. Offer extended to HAE Australasia members only and may be subject to membership authentication. Australian Residents only.</p>',NULL,NULL,788,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'CPSC Benevolent program','Free 1 year MedicAlert membership and choice of a selected MedicAlert ID for attendees of the 2017 Christmas Party for Special Children.',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/Header%20images/christmas-party-image.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2017-11-15 15:04:28','2017-11-15 04:54:26','2017-11-15 15:24:26'),(328,2,1,0,0,'About MedicAlert Foundation','How MedicAlert Foundation makes a difference',NULL,'about-medicalert-foundation',1,'<p><br />At MedicAlert Foundation we are dedicated to helping our members feel safe knowing they&rsquo;re protected in an emergency.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>For over 45 years, our trusted organisation has been protecting Australians in emergency situations, allowing emergency services or healthcare professionals to quickly identify their medical needs and provide the fastest, most effective treatment when seconds count. As part of our service, we invest in vital training programs for healthcare professionals each year, ensuring they are aware that they should always check for MedicAlert identification jewellery.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Internationally recognised and recommended by the World Health Organisation and World Allergy Organisation, the genuine MedicAlert medical ID is proudly worn by a global community of more than four million people from around 40 different countries.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>We are passionate about supporting the wellbeing of our members and work to deliver innovative, reliable and cost-effective products and services that meet their ongoing needs.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Did you know that MedicAlert receives no government funding? As a not-for-profit organisation, we rely on the support of donations so we can continue to protect the thousands of Australians living with medical conditions and keep membership fees to a minimum. If you&rsquo;d like to make a donation, no matter how big or small, visit our <a href=&quot;/donate&quot;>donations page</a>.</p>','<p>The genuine MedicAlert medical ID has been protecting members worldwide since 1953. Our Foundation was first founded by Dr Marion Collins in California, as a way to alert medical personnel to his daughter&rsquo;s potentially fatal anaphylaxis. MedicAlert was introduced into Australia by Rotary and St John Council in 1971, and a national office in Adelaide was established to provide comprehensive support to all members, which still operates today.</p>\r\n<p>As Australia&rsquo;s only not-for-profit organisation of its kind, today MedicAlert Foundation remains dedicated to providing peace of mind to hundreds of thousands of people across Australia - and the world - living with medical conditions.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,99,'About MedicAlert Foundation - Australia&#039;s only not-for-profit organisation dedicated to providing a 24/7 personal medical emergency information and identification service',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,'/uploads/MedicAlert%20staff%20-%20image.jpg','/uploads/about-img.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2016-07-04 15:23:54','2018-01-29 02:38:15','2018-01-29 13:08:15'),(329,795,1,0,0,'Offers','MedicAlert&rsquo;s Offers',NULL,'offers',1,'<p>At MedicAlert Foundation we&rsquo;re passionate about helping Australians stay protected when it matters most. That&rsquo;s why we&rsquo;re proud to partner with a range of different organisations across the country, that help us make sure our members receive additional benefits, reduced costs for their MedicAlert membership and medical jewellery, and are protected in medical emergencies.</p>','<div class=&quot;partners row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-3&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/news-and-resources/images/health-insurance.png&quot; alt=&quot;health-insurance.png &quot; width=&quot;125&quot; height=&quot;125&quot; /></div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-9&quot;>\r\n<h3>Health Insurance Rebates</h3>\r\n<div class=&quot;description&quot;>\r\n<p>Some health funds provide rebates for full or part of the MedicAlert membership fee and/or MedicAlert ID. To see what you&rsquo;re covered for, please contact your health fund provider.</p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/cost&quot;>Find out more</a></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;partners row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-3&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/logos1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;logos1.jpg (40 KB)&quot; width=&quot;250&quot; height=&quot;250&quot; /></div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-9&quot;>\r\n<h3>Health Insurance Rebates</h3>\r\n<div class=&quot;description&quot;>\r\n<p>Some health funds provide rebates for full or part of the MedicAlert membership fee and/or MedicAlert ID. To see what you&rsquo;re covered for, please contact your health fund provider.</p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/cost&quot;>Find out more</a></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;partners row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-3&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/partners/bupa.jpg?width=250&amp;height=150&amp;crop=1&quot; alt=&quot;Bupa&quot; /></div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-9&quot;>\r\n<h3>Bupa</h3>\r\n<div class=&quot;description&quot;>\r\n<p>A special offer for Bupa members: 2 year MedicAlert<sup>&reg;</sup> membership + medical ID of your choice<sup>*</sup> for just $125</p>\r\n<p>*Selected products only. Price includes standard postage and handling and a 12-month standard Australia MedicAlert Foundation product warranty.</p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/bupa&quot;>Find out more</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;partners row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-3&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/partners/I-heart-NDIS.png&quot; alt=&quot;I-heart-NDIS.png (3.71 MB)&quot; width=&quot;250&quot; height=&quot;250&quot; /></div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-9&quot;>\r\n<h3>National Disability Insurance Scheme (NDIS)</h3>\r\n<div class=&quot;description&quot;>\r\n<p>As a proud registered NDIS provider, your MedicAlert membership and MedicAlert ID can now be covered as part of your NDIS plan. If you&rsquo;re an existing member, please contact us to find out how to receive this benefit.</p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/ndis&quot;>Find out more</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;partners row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-3&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/news-and-resources/images/SC_WelcomeHereWave_2%20colour%20CMYK.JPG?width=250&amp;height=184&amp;crop=1&quot; alt=&quot;Seniors Card&quot; /></div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-9&quot;>\r\n<h3>Seniors Card</h3>\r\n<div class=&quot;description&quot;>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ve partnered with the Australian Government to offer an exclusive discount to seniors card holders. As a senior you will save 20% on your MedicAlert membership and 10% off all products when you use the code <strong>SENIORS</strong> at the checkout.</p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/seniors-card&quot;>Find out more</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;partners row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-3&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/uploads/autism.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;ndis.jpg (19 KB)&quot; width=&quot;250&quot; height=&quot;250&quot; /></div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-9&quot;>\r\n<h3>Safe Return</h3>\r\n<div class=&quot;description&quot;>\r\n<p>If a loved one is living with autism, MedicAlert can help them communicate their needs when it matters most. Our 24 hour Safe Return service will make sure that your loved one is quickly and safely returned home in an emergency.</p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/safe-return&quot;>Find out more</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=&quot;partners row&quot;>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-3&quot;><img class=&quot;img-responsive&quot; src=&quot;/images/cost-ausgov.jpg?width=250&amp;height=150&amp;crop=1&quot; alt=&quot;Tunstall&quot; /></div>\r\n<div class=&quot;col-sm-9&quot;>\r\n<h3>Department of Veterans&rsquo; Affairs</h3>\r\n<div class=&quot;description&quot;>\r\n<p>DVA Gold Card holders are eligible to receive rebates on their annual MedicAlert membership fees and stainless steel MedicAlert ID products.</p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;/contact-us&quot;>Contact us to find out more</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','<p>If your organisation is interested in partnering with us, we&rsquo;d love to hear from you.</p>\r\n<p><a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/contact-us&quot;>Contact us</a> today to get started.+</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Offers | MedicAlert Foundation','MedicAlert Foundation partner with a range of different organisations across the country to help ensure our members receive additional benefits and reduced costs for their MedicAlert membership.',NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2017-12-12 14:55:18','2018-04-05 04:22:44',NULL),(330,798,2,0,17,'Choosing the right ID bracelet for back to school',NULL,NULL,'choosing-kids-id-bracelet',0,NULL,'<p>It&rsquo;s that time of year again. You&rsquo;ve purchased and labelled new school supplies, the school uniforms are organised and you&rsquo;ve stocked the fridge ready to prepare school lunches (or are at least thinking about it). This time of year is spent making sure our kids have everything they need for school. But what about their MedicAlert ID? Wearing a MedicAlert ID gives parents and caregivers peace of mind should an emergency arise, it helps kids to feel safe and the school community to identify and manage a students&rsquo; health issues.</p>\r\n<p>Designed especially for kids, our children&rsquo;s collection offers a large variety of fashionable and practical medical identification jewellery. From vibrant sports bands to gold-filled bracelets, there&rsquo;s a unique product for every boy or girl. Below are some questions to consider when selecting the best ID for your child.</p>\r\n<p>What is the best type of ID?</p>\r\n<p>Necklaces are not recommended for children aged 12 years and under due to choking hazards, therefore we advise a bracelet or band style ID for children under the age of 12.</p>\r\n<p>What type of material?</p>\r\n<p>Kids can be active! That&rsquo;s why MedicAlert IDs are made from the toughest materials. All IDs are made from durable, non-allergenic stainless steel and are designed to be worn 24/7. We have a range of band styles to choose from to suit every child and their activities including stainless steel chains, nylon sports bands, easy-flex silicone bands, rope and braided bands and even 9 carat gold bracelets. We offer a range of materials to ensure kids with metal or fabric allergies are catered for. Bands come in a range of colours and patterns, with some being interchangeable so kids can switch up their look.</p>\r\n<p>What size?</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert IDs come in a range of sizes. It&rsquo;s important to make sure the ID fits your child properly so that it is secure, comfortable and to prevent it from falling off. To ensure an accurate fit, measure your child&rsquo;s wrist using our <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/bracelet-sizing-and-engraving-tips&quot;>measuring instructions</a>. Consider an ID that can be adjusted as your child grows. Sports bands and silicone bands with interchangeable bands can easily be added. Most gold bracelets can also be sized up by adding in extra links. Our curb chain bracelet&rsquo;s also include safety clasps making them more difficult to remove if you&rsquo;re concerned they may try to remove their ID.</p>\r\n<p>What to engrave?</p>\r\n<p>Medical ID engraving is free and customised to your individual needs. Your unique membership number, along with your child&rsquo;s most critical conditions or specials needs and our 24/7 emergency response service phone number will be engraved on the back of their ID. The amount of space for this will be determined by the size of the ID you select. View our <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/bracelet-sizing-and-engraving-tips#engrave-section&quot;>engraving guidelines</a>. MedicAlert has engraving standards and guidelines to ensure that engraving and the terminology of the medical condition, medications or allergies are easy to read and understand in an emergency. This is what makes us different to our competitors as we make sure that the information you provide to us is recognised in emergency situations. To do this we ensure our engraving meets international medical terminology standards.</p>\r\n<p>What does the MedicAlert membership include?</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation offers more than medical identification jewellery. When you purchase a genuine MedicAlert product, you&rsquo;re also investing in a vital MedicAlert membership. Together with your child&rsquo;s jewellery, this provides them with complete protection in an emergency. Your child&rsquo;s membership gives you access to our 24/7 emergency response service. What this means is if healthcare professionals require more information, our response team can provide it by accessing your child&rsquo;s secure MedicAlert<sup>R</sup> electronic health record. This helps to determine appropriate treatment or medication management. Our service ensures that members who have memory loss, special needs and communication challenges and may be prone to wandering are identified, then quickly and safely reunited with loved ones. Membership also provides you with exclusive offers, unlimited wallet and fridge cards listing your child&rsquo;s details, secure online access to their health records and support from our membership services team. By becoming a member, you&rsquo;ll have peace of mind knowing you&rsquo;re taking control of your child&rsquo;s health. <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/benefits-of-membership&quot;>Learn more</a> about the MedicAlert membership benefits.</p>\r\n<p>Need some assistance?</p>\r\n<p>If you still need some advice, feel welcome to contact our helpful team who will clarify any questions you may have to ensure your child loves their ID. Call our member services team on 1800 88 22 22 or email enquiry@medicalert.org.au</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Choosing the right kids ID bracelet | MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2018-01-17','2019-01-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2018-01-17 12:26:13','2018-01-17 01:59:26','2018-01-17 12:29:25'),(331,798,2,0,17,'Choosing the right ID bracelet for back to school',NULL,NULL,'choosing-kids-id-bracelet',0,NULL,'<p>It&rsquo;s that time of year again. You&rsquo;ve purchased and labelled new school supplies, the school uniforms are organised and you&rsquo;ve stocked the fridge ready to prepare school lunches (or are at least thinking about it). This time of year is spent making sure our kids have everything they need for school. But what about their MedicAlert ID? Wearing a MedicAlert ID gives parents and caregivers peace of mind should an emergency arise, it helps kids to feel safe and the school community to identify and manage a students&rsquo; health issues.</p>\r\n<p>Designed especially for kids, our children&rsquo;s collection offers a large variety of fashionable and practical medical identification jewellery. From vibrant sports bands to gold-filled bracelets, there&rsquo;s a unique product for every boy or girl. Below are some questions to consider when selecting the best ID for your child.</p>\r\n<p>What is the best type of ID?</p>\r\n<p>Necklaces are not recommended for children aged 12 years and under due to choking hazards, therefore we advise a bracelet or band style ID for children under the age of 12.</p>\r\n<p>What type of material?</p>\r\n<p>Kids can be active! That&rsquo;s why MedicAlert IDs are made from the toughest materials. All IDs are made from durable, non-allergenic stainless steel and are designed to be worn 24/7. We have a range of band styles to choose from to suit every child and their activities including stainless steel chains, nylon sports bands, easy-flex silicone bands, rope and braided bands and even 9 carat gold bracelets. We offer a range of materials to ensure kids with metal or fabric allergies are catered for. Bands come in a range of colours and patterns, with some being interchangeable so kids can switch up their look.</p>\r\n<p>What size?</p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert IDs come in a range of sizes. It&rsquo;s important to make sure the ID fits your child properly so that it is secure, comfortable and to prevent it from falling off. To ensure an accurate fit, measure your child&rsquo;s wrist using our <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/bracelet-sizing-and-engraving-tips&quot;>measuring instructions</a>. Consider an ID that can be adjusted as your child grows. Sports bands and silicone bands with interchangeable bands can easily be added. Most gold bracelets can also be sized up by adding in extra links. Our curb chain bracelet&rsquo;s also include safety clasps making them more difficult to remove if you&rsquo;re concerned they may try to remove their ID.</p>\r\n<p>What to engrave?</p>\r\n<p>Medical ID engraving is free and customised to your individual needs. Your unique membership number, along with your child&rsquo;s most critical conditions or specials needs and our 24/7 emergency response service phone number will be engraved on the back of their ID. The amount of space for this will be determined by the size of the ID you select. View our <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/bracelet-sizing-and-engraving-tips#engrave-section&quot;>engraving guidelines</a>. MedicAlert has engraving standards and guidelines to ensure that engraving and the terminology of the medical condition, medications or allergies are easy to read and understand in an emergency. This is what makes us different to our competitors as we make sure that the information you provide to us is recognised in emergency situations. To do this we ensure our engraving meets international medical terminology standards.</p>\r\n<p>What does the MedicAlert membership include?</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>MedicAlert Foundation offers more than medical identification jewellery. When you purchase a genuine MedicAlert product, you&rsquo;re also investing in a vital MedicAlert membership. Together with your child&rsquo;s jewellery, this provides them with complete protection in an emergency. Your child&rsquo;s membership gives you access to our 24/7 emergency response service. What this means is if healthcare professionals require more information, our response team can provide it by accessing your child&rsquo;s secure MedicAlert<sup>R</sup> electronic health record. This helps to determine appropriate treatment or medication management. Our service ensures that members who have memory loss, special needs and communication challenges and may be prone to wandering are identified, then quickly and safely reunited with loved ones. Membership also provides you with exclusive offers, unlimited wallet and fridge cards listing your child&rsquo;s details, secure online access to their health records and support from our membership services team. By becoming a member, you&rsquo;ll have peace of mind knowing you&rsquo;re taking control of your child&rsquo;s health. <a href=&quot;https://www.medicalert.org.au/benefits-of-membership&quot;>Learn more</a> about the MedicAlert membership benefits.</p>\r\n<p>Need some assistance?</p>\r\n<p>If you still need some advice, feel welcome to contact our helpful team who will clarify any questions you may have to ensure your child loves their ID. Call our member services team on 1800 88 22 22 or email enquiry@medicalert.org.au</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Choosing the right kids ID bracelet | MedicAlert',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2018-01-17','2019-01-17',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2018-01-17 12:26:13','2018-01-17 02:01:58','2018-01-17 12:31:58'),(332,810,2,0,17,'TEST NEWS',NULL,NULL,'test-news',0,'test','<p>test</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'test',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2018-01-29','2019-01-29',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2018-01-29 12:09:08','2018-01-29 01:40:34','2018-01-29 12:10:34'),(333,811,2,0,17,'test news',NULL,NULL,'test-news',0,'test','<p>test</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'test',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2018-01-29','2019-01-29',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2018-01-29 13:05:41','2018-01-29 02:41:31','2018-01-29 13:11:31'),(334,812,2,0,17,'new test',NULL,NULL,'new-test',0,'test news','<p>test newsx</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'test news',NULL,NULL,1,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2018-01-29','2019-01-29',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2018-01-29 13:09:30','2018-01-29 02:41:26','2018-01-29 13:11:26'),(335,820,1,0,0,'Why renew?',NULL,NULL,'renewal',0,'<h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>A MedicAlert&reg; ID can help first responders quickly identify your pre-existing health conditions in an emergency, but a MedicAlert membership is more than just an ID.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>As a lapsed member, your secure health record may be out of date. It&rsquo;s also important to check that the engraving on your existing ID is legible and accurate.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>MedicAlert 24/7 service provides emergency responders, health professionals and general practitioners with access to your past and present health information, allowing them to accurately manage your ongoing care and provide you with peace of mind.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>As a member, you&rsquo;re also entitled to unlimited membership cards that contain your health information and a range of member only benefits and offers.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Please note: If you choose not to renew your membership within 3 months from the lapsed date, MedicAlert reserve the right to remove your records and personal information from our database. This means that your ID will no longer be linked to your electronic health record and supported by the 24/7 emergency response service.</strong></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,999,'Why Renew?',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,'2018-02-21 16:11:59','2018-02-21 05:43:00','2018-02-21 16:13:00'),(336,820,1,0,0,'Why renew?',NULL,NULL,'renewal',0,'<h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </h2>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>A MedicAlert&reg; ID can help first responders quickly identify your pre-existing health conditions in an emergency, but a MedicAlert membership is more than just an ID.</p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;> </p>\r\n<p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>As a lapsed member, your secure health record may be out of date. It&rsquo;s also important to check th