INSERT INTO `tbl_pcare` VALUES (1,'Standard','<p><strong>Product Care and Cleaning</strong></p>\r\n<p>Taking good care of your identification jewellery, with regular cleaning, will prolong its life and provide years of enjoyable wear. We recommend Connoisseurs Jewellery Wipes.</p>',1,'2016-09-01 18:16:08','2016-09-28 01:24:20',NULL),(2,'9ct Gold &amp; Gold-Filled','<p><strong>9ct Gold &amp; Gold-Filled</strong></p>\r\n<p>9ct gold and gold-filled products can be cleaned by rinsing in warm water and polishing with a soft clean cloth.</p>\r\n<p>Avoid polishing with any compounds containing abrasives. Chemical or abrasive cleaners will erode the finish and could subject your product to tarnishing.</p>\r\n<p>Care should be taken to prevent tarnishing by avoiding the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Showering or swimming with your jewellery on</li>\r\n<li>Body lotions, perfume, hair spray, sunscreen, or oils of any kind on your jewellery</li>\r\n<li>Physical activities (sweat)</li>\r\n<li>Applying hair colours while wearing your jewellery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Various skin types and some medications may also cause your jewellery to tarnish. Heavy physical activity may also make your jewellery vulnerable to scratching, so consider wearing a stainless steel medical ID at these times.</p>',2,'2016-09-01 18:17:51','2016-09-01 08:50:13',NULL),(3,'Stainless Steel','<p><strong>Stainless Steel</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stainless steel jewellery can be cleaned with warm soapy water and a soft brush. Although stainless steel is a durable metal, it will mark with normal wear and tear.</p>',3,'2016-09-01 18:20:33','2016-09-01 08:51:10',NULL),(4,'Sports Bands','<p><strong>Sports Bands</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sports bands can be rinsed in warm soapy water. Ensure the band is completely dry before wearing. Printed sports bands are protected with Scotchguard.</p>',4,'2016-09-01 18:21:14','2016-09-28 01:26:08',NULL),(5,'Braided/Leather Bracelets','<p><strong>Braided/Leather Bracelets</strong></p>\r\n<p>Clean the wax cotton braid or leather with a slightly damp soft cloth. Do not wear in water.</p>',5,'2016-09-01 18:22:07','2016-09-01 08:52:50',NULL),(6,'Neoprene/silicon','<p><strong>Neoprene/silicon</strong></p>\r\n<p>Proper care will prevent neoprene/silicone from drying out and cracking. Avoid the following when wearing your neoprene jewellery: excessive physical activity (sweating), showering or swimming, and applying hair colours, body lotions, perfume, hair spray, suntan lotion or oils.</p>',6,'2016-09-01 18:22:58','2016-09-01 08:53:23',NULL),(7,'Sterling Silver/Rhodium Plating','<p><strong>Sterling Silver/Rhodium Plating</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sterling silver is a soft metal and it requires special care to ensure it always looks its best. It can be cleaned by rinsing in warm water and polishing with a soft cloth. Ensure your silver jewellery is dried very well before storing in a soft pouch.</p>\r\n<p>Avoid polishing with any compounds containing abrasives. Chemical or abrasive cleaners will erode the finish and could subject your product to tarnishing. Over time, oxidation can cause silver to tarnish.</p>\r\n<p>Care should be taken to prevent tarnishing by avoiding the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Showering or swimming with your jewellery on</li>\r\n<li>Body lotions, perfume, hair spray, sunscreen, or oils of any kind on your jewellery</li>\r\n<li>Excessive physical activities (sweat)</li>\r\n<li>Applying hair colours while wearing your jewellery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Various skin types and some medications may also cause your jewellery to tarnish. Heavy physical activity may also make your jewellery vulnerable to scratching, so consider wearing a stainless steel medical ID at these times.</p>',999,'2016-09-28 10:58:03','2016-09-28 01:29:29',NULL),(8,'Swarovski Beads and Crystals','<p><strong>Swarovski Beads and Crystals</strong></p>\r\n<p>Swarovski beads and crystals are delicate and must be handled with special care. Store your crystals in a soft pouch separate from other jewellery to avoid scratches. Crystal bracelets may be polished using a soft clean cloth to maintain its original lustre.</p>',999,'2016-09-28 10:59:46','2016-09-28 01:30:02',NULL);
